title: banana split cake
directions: Lay graham crackers in a glass dish.
Spread prepared pudding over crackers.
Spread drained pineapple over pudding.
Evenly place banana slices over pineapple.
Spread 1 cup Cool Whip Lite over pineapple.
Evenly place sliced strawberries over Cool Whip. Enjoy.

title: russian tea balls
directions: Blend ingredients together and roll into balls the size of quarters.
Bake at 350° to 400° about 7 to 10 minutes.
While hot, roll in powdered sugar.
Let cool and then roll again.

title: tuna spinach braid
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine spinach, tuna, cottage cheese, Parmesan, and garlic.
Set aside.
Unroll crescent roll dough onto waxed paper; do not separate dough.
Press to seal seams and perforations.
Cover with another piece of waxed paper.
Roll dough to form a 10 X 14-inch rectangle.
Transfer dough to a 1 X 10 X 15-inch baking pan, discarding waxed paper.
Spread filling down center of dough lengthwise in a 3 1/2-inch strip.
Top with sliced cheese.
Make cuts in the dough at 1-inch intervals on both long sides of rectangle almost to edge of filling.
Fold dough strips diagonally over filling, overlapping strips and alternating from side to side.
Top will look braided.
Combine egg with water and brush over entire top.
Bake at 375 degrees for 18-20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cut into slices.
Serve warm.
Yield: 10-12 appetizers or 4-6 main-dish servings.

title: party chicken
directions: Grease baking dish.
Line with dried beef.
Wrap bacon strips around each breast and place on dried beef.
Combine sour cream, garlic salt and cream of mushroom soup.
Pour over chicken and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 275° to 300° about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: great aunt louva's oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring raisins to a boil in enough water to cover them in a small pan.
Turn off heat.
Cream sugar, butter and lard.
Add eggs.
Dissolve baking soda in 5 tablespoons hot raisin water. Add to mixture.
Drain raisins; discard rest of liquid.
Add oatmeal, flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop on greased cookie sheets, allow some room for spreading.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Combine milk, biscuit mix and eggs. Mix for 1 minute with electric mixer.
Spread sausage in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan and cover with biscuit and egg mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: down home cabbage
directions: Stir-fry ham (or bacon) and onion.
Add cabbage.
Add water to cover cabbage.
Bring to a boil.
Season.
Stir as needed.
Boil until cabbage is soft.
Serve.

title: corn flake trout
directions: Coat each trout fillet in mayonnaise, then roll in corn flakes.
Heat oil in skillet and fry trout 4 minutes on each side or until golden brown.

title: creamed chicken in patty shells
directions: In a large kettle, bring chicken, water, 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon pepper to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until chicken is tender. Remove chicken from broth; cool. Remove meat from bones; cut into cubes and set aside. Discard skin and bones. Strain broth and skim fat. Set aside 1 cup broth. (Refrigerate remaining broth for another use.) Bake pastry shells according to package directions.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender; debone; discard bay leaves.
Mix chicken, soup, and sour cream together.
Put in square baking dish.
Mix melted margarine and crushed crackers.
Place over chicken mixture.
Bake at 375° until brown and bubbly.

title: sour cream drops
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add beaten eggs, sour cream, vanilla and melted chocolate.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and soda together and add to above.
Drop by spoonfuls on baking sheet and bake at 350° until leaves no indentation.
(Don't overbake.)

title: apple crunch salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and cinnamon in boiling water.
Add cold water and chill until thickened.
Fold in apple, celery, pineapple and 1/4 cup chopped nuts, if desired.
Spoon into 6 cup mold or bowl. Chill until firm.
Makes 5 cups or 10 servings.

title: apple-nut torte
directions: Combine egg, sugar and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients; add to egg mixture and blend well.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Spread in square baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt together 2 sticks oleo.
Mix with peanut butter mixture; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1 stick oleo and the chocolate chips; pour over mixture in pan.
Spread.
Refrigerate to harden topping.
Cut into squares before completely hardened.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Bring sugar, water and cocoa to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick over medium heat.
Cool and pour into pie shell.
Add meringue.

title: swiss chard frittata
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: gift for man's best friend(dog biscuits)
directions: In large bowl combine oats, margarine and boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in cornmeal, sugar, bouillon, milk, cheese and egg.
Mix well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup, level off.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, mixing well after each addition to form stiff dough.
On floured surface, knead in remaining flour until no longer sticky.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with bone shaped cutter.
Place on greased baking sheet and bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container.
Dogs love them!

title: feta cheese sticks
directions: Knead cheese with flour, butter and cayenne for about 15 minutes.
(Dough should be soft but not sticky.)
Roll dough into rectangular shape and cut into 5 x 12-inch strips.
Twist as in cheese straws.
Place on cookie sheets.
Brush cheese sticks with beaten egg whites and sprinkle with caraway seed.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Let bread dough rise.
Prepare filling:
Cook meat with onions, mushrooms, salt and pepper in large skillet.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, paprika, oregano and garlic salt.
Bring to a boil, lower heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cool. punch down dough.
Press out onto a 15 x 12 greased cookie sheet.
Spoon meat filling down center third of dough.
Sprinkle cheeses on filling.
Make diagonal cuts in dough, 1 1/2 inches apart down each side, to within 1/2 inch of filling.
Criss cross srtips over filling, pressing down and sealing with a drop of water.
Brush top of loaf with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut in thick slices to serve. Serves 6.

directions: Drain

Fold in whipped topping and the pineapple.
Chill again, if necessary, until mixture will mound.
Spoon into serving bowl or

dessert dishes. Garnish with Mandarin orange sections, maraschino cherries or nuts, if desired.
Makes 5 cups or 10 servings.

title: egg bake
directions: Slightly beat eggs and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Good with chili sauce.

title: chocolate chip pie (with coconut)
directions: Combine butter, sugar and vanilla in a bowl; beat well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in flour.
Gradually stir in pecans and coconut.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: salmon ball
directions: Remove all skin and bones from salmon.
Blend all ingredients. Form a ball.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: raspberry sherbet
directions: Thaw raspberries until slushy.
Let sherbet thaw partially. Mix in Mixmaster.
Add bananas any time.
This is very good when not quite frozen.
Can freeze and keep.

title: col. marty's cold pack deer meat
directions: After cutting deer meat into cubes, pack into quart jar, sprinkling salt and pepper throughout.
Add 1 or 2 garlic cloves to each quart.
Remember to leave 1 inch headspace before sealing. After sealing place quart jars in cold water bath.
Start timing after water boils.
Cook for 4 hours.
After time is up, remove jars from water and allow to cool in a draft-free area.
Do not re-tighten bands! This makes a quick dinner idea.
The meat cooks in its own juice.

title: vegetarian lasagna
directions: Prepare meat sauce by combining tomato sauce with ground Grillers and onion powder in 12-inch saucepan; simmer on low heat for 3 minutes.

title: texas torte
directions: Add flour, salt and milk to eggs and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a well-greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Cut into bite size squares and serve hot.
Makes about 96 squares.

title: sweet potato surprise cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar, egg yolks and water.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer, just until combined.
Combine dry ingredients and add to oil mixture.
Mix just until moistened.
Stir in sweet potatoes, pecans and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Spoon batter into 3 greased, 9-inch cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until cake tests done.
Immediately invert layers on wire cooling racks.
Cool 5 minutes and remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Spread cream coconut frosting.
Yields 20 servings.

title: beth's bean salad
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.
I usually triple this recipe.

title: graham toffee squares
directions: Microwave 1 tablespoon butter in 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish at High 1/2 to 1 minute.
Line dish with crackers.
Set aside.

title: spinach balls
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients. Chill. Shape into little balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve warm. Makes about 70.

title: pineapple spread
directions: Drain pineapple (save
juice).	Mix
eggs, flour, sugar and juice; cook on medium until thick, stirring often.	Remove from heat
and
cool.
Beat
mayonnaise	into
mixture
after cooled. Add pineapple.
Use
little
hand mixer to beat eggs, flour and sugar until thick; cool before adding mayonnaise and pineapple. Will keep several days for sandwiches.

title: avocado cheesecake
directions: In a large bowl, empty 1 of the 2 bags of graham cracker crumbs.
Add the crushed pretzels, the butter and 1/2 cup sugar and stir until well moistened.
Press into the bottom and up the sides of a 10 x 2 1/2-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Blend cheese, milk and vanilla.
Gradually add sugar, beating until frosting is smooth and of spreading consistency.
If necessary, stir in additional milk 1 teaspoon at a time.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Make cake mix according to directions.
Pour batter over marshmallows in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix strawberries and Jell-O.
Pour over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cut into squares and top with Cool Whip.

title: sweet potato-nut casserole(makes 8 to 12 servings)
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, salt, 1/4 cup margarine, milk and vanilla.
Place in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine the flour, cocoa and baking powder; sift twice.
Set aside.

title: creamed fruit
directions: Cut up all kinds of fruit, any kind you like.
Mix Cool Whip, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over fruit and mix.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: tuna salad
directions: Bring water and sugar to boil for 1 minute.
Let cool and add salad dressing.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crumbs and oleo.
Place in 2-quart buttered casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Drizzle with melted oleo.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a bowl and marinate with buttermilk, salt, pepper, parsley, tarragon, thyme and crushed bay leaves for 2 to 3 hours.
Mix in a bowl, sesame seed, parsley and bread crumbs. Roll chicken pieces in bread crumb mixture and arrange in a shallow baking dish.
Bake the chicken at 350°, basting with 4 tablespoons melted butter until it is golden brown and done, 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve immediately or cool to room temperature before eating.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken breasts.
Pour all ingredients over layered chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients first, then add all other ingredients. Refrigerate 6 hours before baking at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mom's best sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs, and Crisco.
Add flour and sour cream and salt and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: frozen chocolate eclair
directions: Beat pudding and milk for 2 minutes; let rest 1 minute.
Add Cool Whip.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers. Pour in half the pudding mixture.
Add another layer of crackers, then the remainder of the pudding.
Top with another layer of crackers.
Frost, then freeze.

title: strawberry sour cream salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to directions.
Add bananas and pineapple together.
Divide into 2 sections.
Jell first half and spread on sour cream.
Layer strawberries and marshmallows.
Pour other half of jello on top and jell until serving time.
Garnish with Cool Whip and strawberries or sour cream and berries.

title: court street french toast
directions: Place 1/2 the bread cubes in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Place cream cheese cubes on top of the bread cubes. Top with the remaining bread.

title: party peas(colorful, tasty and different)
directions: In a saucepan, boil peas just until defrosted (do not cook). Drain and turn into a 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish; set aside.

title: eleanore alborano's microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: In a 4-cup glass measure, melt butter in microwave 1 minute on High.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add milk, salt and pepper.
Stir until smooth.
Heat 6 to 7 minutes on power level 7 until sauce is smooth, stirring twice.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, mix the potatoes and onion.
Add sauce.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Slice a cut in the plastic.
Microwave on power 7 for 35 minutes.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions and salt.
Let set at room temperature for 3 hours.
Drain well.
Then dissolve the sugar, vinegar and seed and pour over the pickles.
Refrigerate for 8 hours, then pack and freeze.

title: party salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Mix other ingredients and stir well.
Add to jello mixture.
Chill.

title: cheese, broccoli and mushroom quiche
directions: Saute broccoli and mushrooms in butter.
Add flour and spices. Mix together.
Add heavy cream and bring to boil.
Add beaten eggs.
Turn off heat.
Pour the above mixture into pie crust.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: asparagus vegetable soup
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Add hot water to dissolve.
Add vinegar, salt, sugar, lemon juice and green coloring.
Mix thoroughly.
Let stand in refrigerator until it begins to set. Add rest of ingredients.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: lo-cal orange carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients in a skillet.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer until carrots are tender.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients, except flour, then add flour gradually. Chill overnight for best results when rolling out for cutout cookies.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: malasadas(portuguese doughnuts)
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Beat eggs until thick.
Measure flour into a large bowl. Make a well in the center.
Add yeast, eggs and remaining ingredients.
Beat thoroughly to form a soft, smooth dough. Cover and let rise until double.
Punch down and let rise again.
Spoon teaspoonfuls of dough into hot oil (375°).
Fry until brown. Drain and shake in a bag with granulated sugar.
Serve hot.

title: tuna cheese loaf
directions: *Set aside 1 cup of flour.
Mix remaining flour, sugar, salt, dill and yeast.
Stir in hot water and margarine.
Mix enough reserved flour to make a soft dough; knead 4 minutes.
Roll dough in an 18-inch circle.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix tuna, mayonnaise and onion.
Spoon over dough.
Gather dough edges to center; seal. Place, seam-side down, on greased baking sheet.
Cut an X on top and fold back points.
Cover.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil and mash potato. Mix potato with sugar. Roll mixture out flat. Spread peanut butter onto mixture. Add pecans.
Roll into shape of a log. Cool. Cut and enjoy!

title: super burgers
directions: Saute beef and onion.
Spoon off fat.
Add sauce and cook over low heat.
Stir.
Serve on buns.

title: danish potato soup
directions: In kettle, bring ham bone and 2 quarts water to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer one hour.
Remove meat from bone when cools. Return meat to kettle along with rest of ingredients.
Cook 40 minutes.
Stir together flour and 1/4 cup water.
Slowly pour into soup, stirring constantly.
Bring soup to a boil and cook 2 minutes.
Reduce heat and stir in cream.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: easy dump cake
directions: Pour cherries in bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle cake mix over cherries.
Pour butter over cake mix.
Pour pineapple next. Sprinkle coconut, then pecans.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: onion-tomato soup
directions: Saut onions in butter.
Add tomatoes, broth, basil, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat for 1 hour.
Serve with toasted french bread.

title: surprise cake
directions: Melt the butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix in the graham cracker crumbs.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: brickle crunch
directions: Line a 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet with foil.
Lay out crackers on cookie sheet, packing tightly.
In a saucepan, melt butter.
Add sugar and boil, stirring frequently for 2 to 3 minutes until sugar is dissolved.
Immediately pour over crackers and bake 7 minutes. Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle chocolate and peanut butter chips over crackers.
Spread evenly with spatula. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Break into pieces.
Serve immediately or refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cheese melts
directions: Chop eggs finely.
Cook bacon until very crisp.
Crumble into small pieces.
Combine chopped eggs, bacon, onion, Cheez Whiz and seasonings.
Mix well and spread on Melba rounds.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until cheese melts.

title: mary bowden's banana bread
directions: Cream together the oleo and sugar.
Set aside!
Sift together the flour, salt and soda.
Add flour mixture to oleo and sugar mixture.
Add eggs, bananas and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: jello punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in small amount of hot water.
Add other ingredients and finish filling gallon with water.
Add ice and ginger ale or Santiba just before serving.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in bottom of a 9-inch square baking dish. Dish should be about 1/2 full of apples.
Combine cinnamon, nutmeg and sugar; sprinkle over the apples.
Pour water over all.
Combine butter, sugar and flour until it is a crumbly mass.
Sprinkle over the apple mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Allow to cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: nut and poppy seed rolls
directions: Crumble yeast into cup and add sugar and lukewarm water.
Let stand while mixing butter and flour.
(Use hands or pastry blender.)
Blend in butter as for pastry until mixture is texture of coarse cornmeal.
Make a "well" in center of mixture and drop in unbeaten egg yolks.
Add yeast mixture at the same time and mix dough thoroughly until dough leaves the sides of the bowl.
Mix for 5 minutes.
Place dough on lightly floured board and cut into 4 pieces and let rest while making filling.
(Resting makes it tender.)
When filling is made, roll one part of the dough as thin as possible into a 15-inch circle.
Spread circle with thin layer of filling.
Roll it up like a jelly roll.
Place rolled dough on lightly greased pans, 15 x 15-inch.
Brush tops with egg whites and let rest for 20 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes until brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Grease bottoms of 5 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Fill half full of batter and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from cans.

title: italian beef supper
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add salt, tomato, water and vegetables.
Bring to a full boil, separating vegetables with a fork and stirring frequently until sauce cubes are blended.
Cover and simmer 2 minutes.
Bring again to a boil.
Stir in rice. Cover; remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.

title: eggsaronious
directions: Pour noodles into boiling water and cook until done.
Drain noodles.
Pour 1/2 of noodles into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle 1/2 to 3/4 pound cheese over noodles.
Cover with remainder of noodles and cover with rest of cheese.
Pour 1 cup of milk into pan.
Place in preheated oven at 350°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool 5 to 10 minutes and serve.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix crumbs with milk and add to meat, pepper, salt and onion. Mix and shape into balls.
Roll in flour.
Fry in hot oil until brown.
Drain off grease and pour the remaining ingredients over the meatballs.
Heat gently.
Serves 4.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cover bottom of pan (9x13) with browned hamburger.
Add salt and pepper.
Spread onions over beef.
Cover with cheese slices, Mix cream of celery soup with 1/2 cup milk and pour over top. Cover with frozen tater tots.
Bake at 350 degree for 1 hr.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix and freeze in oblong Pyrex dish.
Slice and serve.

title: never fail pie crust(four 9-inch crusts)
directions: Mix flour, salt and Crisco with pastry blender or knives until fine and crumbly.
Beat egg, water and vinegar together; work into dry mix; may need a few more drops water.
Form into 4 balls. Freezes well.

title: paula's rhubarb custard cake
directions: Prepare batter of a 2 layer yellow cake mix according to package directions.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover batter with the chopped rhubarb.
Sprinkle sugar on top. Pour whipping cream over ingredients in pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
The cream and rhubarb will sink to the bottom, forming a lush custard.
Store in refrigerator.
Serve warm or cold.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together cake mix, oil, and eggs until dough forms.
Dust hands with powdered sugar.
Shape into 1 in. balls.
Roll in powdered sugar; place 2 in. apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Cool.
About 2 1/2 dozen.

title: half-a-pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and shortening. Add eggs and vanilla. Combine flour and baking powder. Add to creamed mixture. Add milk and beat for 5 minutes. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli, onion and celery until tender, 10 to 15 minutes in small amount of water.
Add cheese, soup, milk and margarine. Thicken to taste.
Heat on medium until hot (do not boil).
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pound cake
directions: Add sugar to softened margarine.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs; beat.
Gradually add flour and blend well.
Add vanilla. Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured angel food pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: easy kahlua
directions: Mix berries and sugar and let stand at least 20 minutes; stir occasionally.
Mix cold water and Sure-Jell and bring to a boil for 1 minute, then add to strawberry mixture.
Mix well.
Pour in jars and let set for 24 hours in refrigerator or cool place.
Cover and freeze.

title: a wild turkey
directions: Fill tall glass with ice and 3/4 full with lemon lime soda. Then add wild turkey and hazelnut.

title: french onion soup
directions: Simmer onions and oleo for 30 minutes.
Add flour and bouillon.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer on low for 20 minutes. Pour over croutons in 6 oven-safe bowls.
Lay slices of Swiss cheese on top.
Broil until cheese bubbles.
Serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hamburger meal
directions: Fry or broil hamburger patties.
Saute chopped vegetables. Spread cream cheese on top of hamburger patties.
Put some sauteed veggies on patties, then top with grated or sliced cheese.
Add more veggies.
Pop in microwave to melt cheese.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients, except oil for frying, in medium bowl.
Mix well.
Let stand 1 hour.
Heat 2 to 3 inches of oil in deep fryer.
Drop batter by heaping tablespoonfuls into hot oil. Fry a few at a time for 5 to 6 minutes or until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.
Repeat with remaining batter.
Serve immediately or keep warm in 175° oven.

title: blackberry dumpling
directions: Let come to a hard boil.
Make up biscuit dough as if you were making biscuits.
Drop in dough the size of biscuits; let come to a rolling boil.
Turn heat down; cover with lid and let simmer until ready to serve.
You may serve with or without cream.

title: barge rice
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add 1/2 small carton sour cream and grated cheese to taste; simmer.
While cooking mixture, cook rice (2 cups).
Mix cooked rice and meat mixture together.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar thoroughly.
Add 1 cup flour and 2 eggs at a time, blending well after each addition.
Add vanilla, lemon extract and sour cream last.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Start in cold oven set at 325°.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies(sugar-free)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Measure oatmeal into bowl.
Stir in melted margarine; mix well.
Stir in eggs and sweetener.
Add mixture of flour, baking powder and salt alternately with the combined milk and vanilla.
Add raisins.
Drop onto cookie sheet from level teaspoon.
Bake until golden brown (about 10 to 15 minutes).

title: ravishing rice
directions: Cook sausage; crumble and drain.
Boil water; add soup mix and rice.
Continue to boil and stir for 10 minutes.
Add onion, celery, bell pepper and sausage.
Pour into 2 or 3-quart flat baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.
This freezes well.

title: sausage bread
directions: Remove sausage from skin and panfry until brown, adding oregano, parsley and cheese.
Dice Mozzarella and combine with sausage, allow to cool.
Roll out pizza dough like pizza.
Spread sausage mixture on dough leaving 1 inch around edges.
Roll dough like a jelly roll and shape into a horseshoe.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
If desired, brush top with beaten egg.

title: rich layer fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in four layers.

title: wedding soup
directions: Cook chicken in water until done with carrot, onion and celery.
Remove meat from bone.
Save 1/2 to 1 cup chicken for soup.
Use the rest for salad, etc.
The broth is the base for the soup.
Add thyme to broth.
Squeeze spinach dry.
Add to soup. Add eggs to soup.
Heat and serve.

title: banana split pie
directions: Beat cream cheese.
Beat in powdered sugar, then beat in vanilla.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Put in freezer for 1 hour.
Slice banana on top.
Add pineapple and top with Cool Whip. Keep refrigerated.

title: cloud 9 meringue cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar with electric mixer until they do not slide when bowl is tilted.
Add sugar 1 tablespoon at a time, beating constantly.
Beat 1 minute more after all sugar is in.
Fold gently the remaining ingredients. Drop by large teaspoon on foil lined sheet.
Put in oven and turn off heat.
Leave overnight or 3 hours.

title: crescent cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, mushrooms, parsley, salt and pepper; set aside.
Unroll 1 package rolls and separate dough into triangles.
In lightly greased 9-inch pie pan, arrange triangles with pointed ends to the center and press edges together to form a pie shell.
Separate eggs; beat together whites from 3 eggs plus yolks from 2 eggs.
Pour half of beaten egg mixture over pie shell.
Spoon meat mixture into shell.
Arrange cheese slices on top.
Spread with remaining beaten egg mixture; mix reserved egg yolk with water and set aside.

title: double chocolate nog
directions: In a large bowl, beat together pudding mix according to directions.
Stir in chocolate milk and vanilla, chill for several hours, pour into tall glasses, top with whipped cream.

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: In a sauce pan put butter, brown sugar, and corn syrup. Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Stir in milk.
Simmer, stir constantly.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over pop corn, stir until coated.
Butter hands lightly, shape into balls.
Makes 15 balls.

title: dutch pea soup
directions: Put all ingredients in a 4 to 6-quart pot and bring to boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Remove meat from bone.
Makes 8 cups of soup.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat three minutes; pour in a 10-inch tube pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ham loaf
directions: Have ham and pork mixed at store (call ahead).
Mix meat, cracker crumbs, milk and eggs.
Make into two equal loaves. Place into baking dish.

title: cream of fresh vegetable soup
directions: Cook vegetables and onions in broth until tender (15 to 30) minutes.
Blend in blender until smooth.
Melt butter.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add blended vegetables; heat through. Add seasonings such as parsley, basil or dill to taste.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
You should have enough for 2 nice size cheese balls.
Allow to rest in the refrigerator a couple of hours.
Chop 1 cup of pecans; divide the cheese ball in half. Roll each ball in chopped pecans; wrap in plastic.
Place in the refrigerator until time to serve.
Serve with party crackers.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush Oreos.
Reserve some for topping.
Melt margarine and mix with Oreos.
Put in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate. Mix softened cream cheese, 1/2 Cool Whip and powdered sugar until smooth.
Spread on top of Oreo mixture.
Prepare pudding according to box and spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Sprinkle remaining Oreos over the top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters.
Shake in sugar and cinnamon.
Place a layer in greased tube pan. Sprinkle nuts over.
Add 2 more layers of biscuits. Sprinkle remaining nuts over.
Melt brown sugar and oleo. Bring to a boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: christmas wreaths
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows.
Remove from heat and add cornflakes, vanilla and food coloring.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper with buttered fingers.
Shape into wreaths.

title: chili con queso
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter until tender.
Add cheese and stir over very low heat to melt.
Stir in drained pimentos, chili powder and garlic salt.
Serve warm with corn chips.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain small can pineapple well. Wash lettuce. Drain. Using a large platter, start by placing leaves of lettuce in platter. Place pineapple rings around on top of lettuce. Place grated sharp cheese in middle of each pineapple. Place a little mayonnaise on top of cheese. Place a drained maraschino cherry on top. Cover and chill well. Makes a great lite dessert.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Boil shrimp in well seasoned water.
Peel and grind or blend. Mix with other ingredients.
Keep refrigerated several hours before serving.
Serve with crackers of your choice.
Yields 8 servings.

title: jalapeno dip
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add tomatoes and onion.
Simmer and drain off grease.
Melt Velveeta cheese in double boiler and stir in hamburger mixture.
Add hot jalapeno relish, 1 tablespoon at a time, until hot enough for taste.
Serve in fondue pot.
Excellent dip for Fritos.

title: spring macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and mix ingredients, onion and celery, to your liking, while macaroni is hot.
Let stand 24 hours and it will thicken.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In a medium bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill 2 hours.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Makes 1 pie.

title: c2c and pscc chili mac
directions: Brown ground meat.
Cook macaroni according to directions; drain.
To meat brown onion, green pepper and celery.
Add small amount of oil, if needed.
After sauteeing veggies, add tomato sauce.
Pour all into pan with drained macaroni.
Warm.
Serve with grated cheese and enjoy.
(This dish can be personalized with various ground meat, different pasta and more or less chili seasoning.)

title: alan's chicken
directions: Combine tabasco and milk.
Dip chicken breast in milk mixture then dredge in flour.
Saute in 1 tablespoon of olive oil and 1 tablespoon butter, for 3 minutes on each side.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Add 1 tablespoon olive oil to skillet and saute leeks.
Add remaining ingredients and pour over chicken breast.
Serve with pasta or rice.

title: maria's potato soup
directions: Mix water with chicken bouillon.
Dissolve cornstarch in cold water.

title: south dakota beans
directions: Brown the hamburger meat with the onions.
Drain grease.
Pour in a large bowl. Add the bacon, ketchup and brown sugar. Combine pork and beans, butter beans and red kidney beans
and add to mixture.
Pour into casserole dish. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: tonia's rhubarb cake
directions: Cook rhubarb, sugar and water until rhubarb is tender. Remove from heat and add Jell-O. Mix yellow cake mix as directed. Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Make a layer of mini-marshmallows on the bottom. Pour cake mix over marshmallows. Pour rhubarb mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Heat
juice of pineapple and when hot dissolve jello in it. Add
pineapple and mix.
Let stand in refrigerator for 35 minutes. Remove
and
add cottage cheese.
Mix well, then add Cool Whip. Mix
well
and
add
four
drops of food coloring. Whip by
hand. Replace in refrigerator and leave for 4 hours. Cover while chilling.
This makes a large salad.

title: orange cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Use 1/2 or more of ground oranges in batter.
Save remaining for icing.

title: lo-cal spaghetti
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan; simmer over low or medium heat until vegetables are tender, adding water as necessary to prevent sticking.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish with butter.
Put a layer of chicken and a layer of herb mix.
Add mushroom soup, layer of chicken and herb mix.
Pour on cream of chicken soup.
Add another layer of chicken and herb mix.
Pour broth over top.
Cook at 350° until brown.

title: the "best" chocolate chip cookies!!!
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt in a small bowl; set aside. Mix both sugars, butter and eggs in a bowl; add vanilla.
Add flour mixture, adding more flour as needed.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Cover cookie sheet with parchment paper (this is optional).
Drop dough onto cookie sheet with ice cream scoop sized spoon.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: buttered carrots
directions: Peel carrots and cut into thin slices.
Put into saucepan together with butter, water and salt.
Cover and simmer over very low heat for 20 to 25 minutes.
Liquid should almost be evaporated.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and chopped parsley.
Serves 4.

title: macaroni and salami salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and rinse.
Toss with milk and oil in large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Toss in macaroni. Add salami and mix well.
Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Has about 455 calories per serving.

title: almond cream
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1/4 cup water.
Heat 1/2 cup milk and sugar in a pan until sugar is dissolved.
Mix it with the gelatine.
Then add 1 cup cold milk and almond flavoring.
Stir it well.
Put the mixture into a pie plate and place in refrigerator. When set, cut in diamond shapes.
Pour syrup from the canned fruit over it.
Garnish with canned fruit and mix carefully with a wooden spoon.
Prettiest served from a clear glass bowl in small glass dessert dishes.

title: cake layers
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together thoroughly, then add last 3 ingredients.
Beat well.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° until done. May use your choice of frosting.

title: pepperoni loaf
directions: Roll out dough to approximately 12 x 18-inch on a floured surface.
Spread 1 beaten egg onto dough.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese, garlic powder, parsley, pepper and salt onto dough. Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over Parmesan mixture.
Top with pepperoni.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in large skillet; brown chicken, reserving drippings.
Place uncooked Minute rice in buttered large casserole dish.
Place brown chicken on top.
In drippings in same skillet in which chicken has been browned, add remaining ingredients. Bring to a full boil; pour over chicken and rice.
Bake in 300° oven for 45 minutes or longer.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease pan.
Spread pineapple over bottom of pan.
Dump in cherry pie filling; spread over the pineapple.
Dump in dry cake mix and spread over the filling.
Sprinkle on nuts.
Cut butter in little squares and sprinkle over cake mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.

title: kiflins
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and beat.
Add almonds and mix well.
Add flour and mix well. Roll dough into little balls the size of first finger.
Form into a crescent shape.
Lay on ungreased baking sheet so they do not touch.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
These cookies will be white so do not bake any longer.
While cookies are still warm, roll into powdered sugar.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix together well all ingredients, except pecans.
Shape one teaspoon dough around each pecan and place each ball on cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes at 375°.
They should be cooked just until a light golden color.
Makes 48.

title: angel pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese well.
Stir in the milk until smooth. Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Then fold in whipped topping, pineapple, and pecans.
Divide evenly in pie shells.
Chill.

title: eggs and sausage(great for brunch)
directions: Put cubed bread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with sausage.
Mix together the eggs, milk and salt.
Pour over sausage.
Top with cheese.
Let stand, covered, overnight, in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: summer salad
directions: Mix together. Allow to set for 1 hour before serving.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: You will need pint jars.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Beat butter and cream cheese together in mixing bowl.
Add sugar to mixture and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla.
Sift flour and salt together.
Spoon batter into tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes; dust with powdered sugar.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Microwave at High for 3 1/2 minutes.
Remove; stir and return for 3 1/2 more minutes.
Remove and add margarine and vanilla.
Return for two more minutes. Remove and add soda.
Stir well and put on greased cookie sheet. Break or cut in small pieces when cold.

title: alligator stew
directions: First catch a medium size alligator!
Skin and cut into small bite size pieces.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over a kerosene fire for approximately 3 weeks at 325°.
Salt and pepper to taste.
This will serve about 300 to 350 people.
If more are expected, the rabbits may be added.
But do this only in an emergency, as most people do not like hare in their stew.
Serve with alligator pear (avocado) salad.

title: salad dressing
directions: Put all in blender and blend 30 seconds.
Best if made ahead.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until set.
Use a knife to test if done.

title: easy chocolate cake(also a lenten cake!)
directions: Combine the flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add the vanilla, oil, and vinegar.
Pour the hot water or cold coffee over all.
Stir until well blended and pour in a 9 x 9-inch cake pan. Sprinkle with some chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chipperdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line jelly roll pan with foil.
Line pan with crackers.
Melt butter with sugar and boil 2 minutes.
Pour evenly over crackers.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle chips over top and spread them around as they melt.
Sprinkle with nuts. Refrigerate or freeze until firm.
Break apart as you would with peanut brittle.

title: pecos pasta
directions: Cook noodles to package directions; drain.
Cook hamburger, green pepper and onion; drain.
Add chili, seasoned salt and pepper.
Simmer on low heat 5 minutes.
Stir in cooked noodles, cook 5 minutes more.
Serve with shredded cheese on top.
Serves 6.

title: sam's blueberry buckle
directions: To make batter, blend margarine until soft, gradually add sugar and mix well.
Add baking powder, salt and half of flour. Mix in milk.
Add remaining flour and mix until smooth. Fold in blueberries by hand until covered.
Spread into a 9 x 9
or 7 x 9 pan.
Prepare topping by blending margarine, sugar, flour and cinnamon together with a pastry blender until crumbly in texture. Sprinkle topping over batter and bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: watergate salad
directions: In
a
large
bowl,
combine pineapple and dry pudding. Add food
coloring,
if
preferred.
Mix
in whipped topping, marshmallows and nuts.
Add coconut, if preferred.
Stir until well mixed.
Spread in flat type bowl or pan.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar in large bowl.
In saucepan, mix oleo, cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil and pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 cup buttermilk, 1 cup water and 2 eggs.
Mix well and pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine butter, 2 cups flour and 1/2 cup powdered sugar; blend until smooth.
Pat dough into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, or until light brown.
Combine eggs, sugar and lemon juice; mix well.
Add 1/4 cup flour, salt and baking powder; blend well.
Pour over pastry.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares or bars.

title: hurry up cake
directions: Mix sugar and shortening in large bowl.
Add eggs.
Blend in flour mixture alternately with milk.
Mix all well.
Bake at 350° in greased pan for about 30 minutes.
Spread with icing.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Press hamburger in bottom of pan; salt and pepper.
Spread on soup and top with Tater Tots.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: minnerly's bread pudding
directions: Toast bread and spread with all the butter/margarine while hot.
Arrange toast in buttered baking dish. Sprinkle with raisins. Stir salt and all but 4 tablespoons of sugar into the eggs.
Add milk and stir to mix well.
Pour over toast and let stand 10 minutes.
Press toast lightly down into milk occasionally.
Mix cinnamon and remaining sugar; sprinkle over the top.
Place pan directly on oven rack in a 350° oven about 25 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean and top is golden brown.

title: brasciole (beef roll)
directions: Slice garlic and brown in oil in large pot.
Remove garlic pieces (leave them in for flavor and as vampire protection).
Hit thin steaks with heavy flat thing to soften and make thinner. Spread out steaks; sprinkle with salt and pepper, bread crumbs (cover side), grated cheese and parsley.
Roll up steaks with stuffing inside.
Tie each end and center with string so it doesn't unroll.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Dissolve Knox gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water.
Add the tomato soup. Stir in cream cheese, mayonnaise, chopped shrimp, celery and onions.
Mix well and pour into mold.
Chill 45 minutes.
Unmold in hot water 2 minutes and turn out on serving plate.
Put crackers around the outside of plate.

title: turkey ham bake
directions: Cook onion until tender in 2 tablespoons butter.
Blend in flour and pepper.
Add undrained mushrooms and apple juice. Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Add turkey, ham and water chestnuts.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with cheese.
Melt remaining butter, and mix with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: marinated olives
directions: Combine ingredients in Ziploc bag. Refrigerate 2 hours or up to 1 month. Serve at room temperature. Great appetizer!

title: mint chocolate candy cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: gracie's secret cooler
directions: Combine ingredients; chill.
Garnish with orange slices. Yields 1 1/2 quarts.

title: dinner in a dish
directions: Layer sliced potatoes in a greased casserole dish (size will depend on quantity you wish to make).
Follow with layer of sliced onion, layer of sweet corn and ground beef (already browned).
Top with bacon slices.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Finish with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for about an hour.
This recipe works well in a crock-pot also.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Roll chicken breast in mixture of flour, paprika, salt and pepper.
Place floured chicken in casserole with butter.
Brown chicken on both sides.
Add the chicken soup, mushrooms and cooking sherry.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yogurt dressing(healthful eating)
directions: Combine ingredients with wire whisk.
Chill 3 hours.

title: lisas holiday corn casserole
directions: Combine as much as possible and place in microwavable dish. Occasionally stir while microwaving on high till done. Serve while hot.

title: sourdough starter
directions: First,	make
potato
water by cutting up 2 medium size potatoes
into
cubes
and	boiling
in
3 cups of water until tender.
Remove
the potatoes; measure out 2 cups of remaining liquid.
Mix
the
potato water, flour and sugar into a smooth paste.
Set
in a warm place until starter rises to double its original size.

title: golden corn pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
Mix ingredients thoroughly. Pour into greased 1-quart baking dish, set in pan of hot water 1 inch deep.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes or until silver knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean.
Makes 8 servings.

title: buddig beef cheese spread
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Add Buddig beef.
Add seasoned salt. Add onion.
Mix and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: easy bread pudding
directions: Put sugar in top of double boiler with 1 tablespoon butter. Add the cubed bread (buttered). Combine eggs, milk, salt and vanilla, separately and beat well. Pour over bread in double boiler but do not stir. Cook over hot boiling water for 1 hour. The brown sugar and butter makes a delicious sauce.
No other sweetening is needed. Serve with whipped cream, if you wish. Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: zesty chicken or pork chops
directions: Combine eggs, milk and flour.
Make a thin batter.
Add salt, onion
powder, garlic powder and meat tenderizer.
Beat well. Place
cornflakes
on
large flat bowl or on a pan; dip chicken in
batter,
roll
in
cornflakes
and
place in well greased pan. Spray with squeeze margarine.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey-orange glazed ham
directions: Place carrots in bottom of crock-pot to form rack.
Mix orange juice and honey together and pour over ham and carrots.
Cook on low heat for 6 to 8 hours.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan; place fruit in pan.
Cream 3/4 cup sugar and butter.
Add milk, flour, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Mix and spread over fruit.
Mix 1 cup sugar, cornstarch and dash of salt and spread over batter.
Pour boiling water over batter and bake one hour at 375°.
Can use frozen, canned or fresh fruit.
If you use canned fruit, use juice for water and reduce some sugar.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8-inch round pans. Beat sugar with oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Sift flour with baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Beat into sugar mixture.
Beat in vanilla, carrots, pineapple, walnuts and raisins.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes until cake tests done.
Cool 10 minutes in pans.
Turn out on wire racks.
Spread with favorite frosting when cool.

title: lasagna rolls
directions: Combine Ricotta cheese, eggs, 1/2 of Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses and seasonings.
Mix well.
Place cooked noodles on plate and spoon 1/8 of mixture on each.
Roll up.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix cheese with cracker crumbs.
Add liquid from asparagus to the soup.
Put layer of crumbs and cheese in a buttered casserole. Add a layer of asparagus and sprinkling of nuts.
Cover with soup mixture.
Repeat until all ingredients are used, ending with a layer of crumbs and cheese on top.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
(This can be prepared the day before.)

title: microwave cover dogs
directions: First take a piece of bread. Squirt mustard and ketchup on it. Put 1 tablespoon of relish on next.
Put a hot dog on a paper towel and put it in the microwave for 22 seconds.
Take the hot dog out and put on the bread.
Eat.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Heat sugar and syrup until it bubbles.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter.
Add corn flakes.
Toss until covered.
Shape into cookies or spoon onto foil or wax paper.
Double recipe easily. Freeze, if desired.

title: cheesy rotel crayfish spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti, according to package directions and drain. Saute vegetables in margarine until tender-crisp.
Stir in mushroom soup, tomatoes, skim milk, lemon juice and seasonings.
Mix well. Add Velveeta and simmer until melted, stirring often.
Add crayfish and simmer about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add spaghetti and stir in gently until well blended.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, cornstarch and flour in a saucepan.
Stir in milk.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks.
Add squares of Baker's unsweetened chocolate.
Stir and cook until mixture thickens. Blend in margarine and vanilla.
Cool.
Pour into baked pie shell. Finish with meringue.

title: egg and cheese bake
directions: Place a layer of oysters in a baking dish, then a layer of cracker crumbs, with salt, pepper and butter on this; then another layer of oysters and so on until dish is full, having crumbs and seasonings on top.
When full, add sufficient rich milk to moisten.
Bake one-half hour in hot oven.

title: mom's great nachos
directions: Line pan with chips.
Top with all ingredients (brown sausage first).
Bake at 350° until cheese is completely melted, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Top with favorites, sour cream, Pace salsa.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Spread the preceding in layers in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hawaii banana nut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl with large spoon. Add all other ingredients. Mix well with spoon. Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans for 1 hour and 5 minutes at 350°.

title: green bean pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and spices. Drain. Add beans and sauce.
Mix well. Place biscuits on top of meat mixture. Cover and simmer approximately 5 minutes with the lid on.
Do not peek. Uncover and cook approximately 3 minutes more.
Biscuits are more like dumplings.

title: toll house pan cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Set aside.
Combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour and mix well. Stir in chocolate morsels and pecans.
Spread into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Bake for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 35 squares.

title: lazy man peach cobbler
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk in mixing bowl.
Pour in baking dish.
Pour fruit on top. Bake at 400°
for 25 minutes or until brown on top.
May substitute other fruits.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onions and celery.
Mix soup, water and corn.
Add onions and celery.
Add cream cheese and simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Add shrimp last few minutes.

title: monkey bread deluxe
directions: Combine milk, potatoes, shortening, sugar and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Add yeast, softened in water.
Add eggs.
Beat in 1 1/2 cups flour, then add the balance to make a stiff dough.

Turn out on a board and knead thoroughly. Return to greased bowl and butter top, then let rise 2 hours. Chill in refrigerator, but remove 1 1/2 hours before serving time. Roll dough 1/2 inch thick and cut into 2-inch diamonds.
Dip each diamond in melted butter and arrange alternately in layers around a well-buttered mold.
Let rise until double in bulk, then bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: rum pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat well after each egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt, add alternately with milk and rum extract. Grease sides and bottom of tube pan with soft butter.
Line pan with waxed paper.
Sprinkle 1 cup or more of chopped pecans in bottom, then sprinkle with flour before pouring cake batter in. Bake at 225° for 1 hour, then about 300° until done.

title: potato skins
directions: Bake the potatoes in the oven or microwave until it just reaches the done point.
(Do not overcook.)
Cool potatoes. Slice potatoes about 1/4-inch thick.
Top with bacon bits and then grated cheese.
Bake either in the oven or microwave until the cheese is melted good.
Serve with Ranch dressing.
Makes a great after school snack.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Wash and chop broccoli. Boil in 1 1/2 cups water until tender. When cooled off, pour water and broccoli in blender and blend well. Add flour and blend well. Pour back into saucepan and add half and half. When heated through, stir in mushroom soup, cheese, salt and pepper. Heat until warm but don't boil.

title: old-fashioned apple cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and oil.
Add to sifted dry ingredients. Stir in nuts and apples.
Mix well.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan. Distribute chips over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
For best results, wait 1 day before serving.
(You can use any fruit of your choice.)

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Saute onion and garlic.
Add all other ingredients.
Run tortillas through hot oil and layer with meat mixture.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° until cheese melts. This can be made ahead.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into small pieces.
Fill a large mixing bowl with cold water.
Place potatoes in water until ready to cook. Set aside.

title: rum balls
directions: In saucepan, melt chocolate pieces over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1/2 cup sugar, rum and corn syrup.
Fold in vanilla wafers.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls, using 2 teaspoons of mixture for each.
Roll in additional sugar.
Store in airtight container for several days.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: blue cheese meatballs
directions: Combine first seven ingredients plus 1/2 cup wine.
Shape into bite size balls; brown on all sides.
Drain on paper towels. Place in shallow casserole.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Just heat and serve.
If frozen, heat 1/2 cup wine and pour over top before baking.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Mix all; bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 400°.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Sift flour with baking soda and baking powder. Beat egg and lard together. Add brown and granulated sugars and almond extract. Gradually mix in dry ingredients until well blended. For each cookie, roll 1 tablespoon dough into a ball. Place on ungreased baking sheets and press 1 almond in center of each. Brush with beaten egg yolk and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: millionaire candy
directions: Melt chocolate, paraffin and chips in top of double boiler. Add nuts.
Drop on wax paper.
Chill.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: apricot salad
directions: In small saucepan, heat pineapple to boiling, dissolve Jell-O and let cool.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Stir cream cheese to soften.
When soft, place all ingredients in a bowl with the cream cheese (except for 1 cup of nuts).
Mix together.
Shape into large ball.
Roll cheese ball in the remaining cup of nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If dough is very stiff, add a small amount of milk.
The dough should look dry but should still hold together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Break sausage into small pieces.
Combine sausage, cheese and Bisquick.
Form into bite size balls.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be frozen.

title: marshmallow icing
directions: Beat egg whites stiff; add marshmallows; set aside.
Cook together sugar and water until it spins a thread.
Slowly pour syrup over egg, marshmallows mixture, beating constantly until right consistency to spread.
Add vanilla if desired.

title: cherry blossom
directions: Crush or crumble graham crackers; blend with butter and sugar. Press into bottom and sides of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes, or until golden brown. While crumb mixture is still hot, spread with the following layers in order:
8 ounces cream cheese (room temperature), which has been blended with 2 to 3 tablespoons milk and 1 cup confectioners sugar.
Sprinkle 1 cup chopped nuts over cream cheese mixture and chill.
Whip the whipping cream; spread over nuts.
Spread the cherry pie filling over cream and chill.

title: quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
For a 9-inch pie crust:
Combine egg, milk, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in cheese.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before cutting into wedges.
If using crescent rolls, preheat oven to 325°. Separate dough into triangles.
Place in a pie pan; press together to form crust.
Be creative!
Use cubed ham, luncheon meat, shrimp or crab meat; place 1/2 of a 3 1/2 ounce can of French fried onions on crust before adding filling, then sprinkle remaining over top before baking.

title: popsicles
directions: Mix well.
Fill paper cups and freeze with a stick.

title: crunchy sugar balls
directions: Melt chocolate pieces over hot (not boiling) water.
From heat, add corn syrup and orange juice; combine the vanilla wafers, powdered sugar and nuts.
Add to chocolate mixture and mix well. Let stand about 30 minutes.
Then form into 1 inch balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken marsala with asparagus
directions: Lightly flour chicken strips on both sides.
Melt butter with oil in skillet.
Cook chicken strips about 3 minutes per side. Remove chicken from pan; keep warm.
Add asparagus to pan; cook on a little higher heat until crisp; add a little more butter if necessary.
Return chicken to skillet with asparagus.
Add lemon juice and wine.
Bring to boil; simmer until thickened.
Serve over broad egg noodles or rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef in heavy kettle.
Add onions, brown and drain.
Add whole tomatoes, kidney beans, corn, tomato sauce, taco seasoning, 1 to 2 cups water and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Ladle into bowls and top with grated cheese. Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Good with nacho chips.
(This can be simmered several hours in a crock-pot.)

title: wonderful pickles
directions: *Option:
Don't add all at once, just a part each day.

title: aunt leona's johnny cake
directions: Mix and sift the dry ingredients.
Add the sour cream, buttermilk and egg.
Beat well.
Bake in shallow pan in a hot oven (400°) about 25 minutes.

title: tomato soup for two
directions: Peel and cut up tomatoes.
Cook until tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
In a separate pan, mix soda, butter and milk. Heat, but do not boil.
Add all together and serve hot.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef in butter and add tomato sauce.
Combine remaining ingredients except butter.
Toss noodles with 2 tablespoons butter and place layer in bottom of a greased casserole.
Cover with cheese mixture.
Add remaining noodles and top with beef mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: fudge truffle cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Prepare chocolate crumb crust.
Set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes or until center is set.
Cool, chill.
Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add egg, oil and milk.
Spoon into a greased 12-hole muffin tin.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Check sooner.

title: hurry-up stew
directions: Brown meat in a large pan, leaving it in chunks.
Add ingredients in order of list, using the liquid in the vegetable cans.
Add pasta last.
Stir.
Simmer until pasta is tender.
If stew starts to get too thick, add a little water or tomato juice.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Wash and strain persimmons.
Mix 2 cups persimmon pulp with sugar, flour, eggs, salt, margarine, milk and flavoring.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° until set, about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage ryes
directions: Brown the meats and drain.
Add the Velveeta cheese.
Melt the cheese, adding a little milk, if needed.
Mix in the Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt and oregano.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Spread onto rye bread.
Broil until heated.
These are great for freezing for a later date.

title: turkey parmigiana
directions: Dip turkey in egg and bread crumbs.
Fry slowly in oil. Arrange in baking dish.
Sprinkle onion and cover with tomato sauce.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake additional 10 minutes.

title: sister's caramel corn(yields 7 quarts)
directions: Pop the popcorn.
Place popped popcorn in a 17 1/4 x 11 3/8 x 2 1/4-inch pan.
Sprinkle all the nuts over the popcorn and set aside.
Place butter in 6-quart saucepan and melt on medium heat. Add brown sugar and Karo.
Stir constantly until sugar is dissolved and mixture comes to a boil.
Remove mixture from heat and add baking soda and cream of tartar.
Then stir well.
Pour hot mixture over nuts and popcorn.
Mix well.
This will be sticky.
Then place sticky mixture in 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Remove from oven and stir one more time.
Let cool.
Then place in airtight container.
Preheat oven to 200°.
Yields 7 quarts.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes.
Mash.
Add mayo, mustard and sweet relish. Garnish with paprika.

title: make-ahead delicious noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain and stir in butter.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and season to taste.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, cream cheese, onion and green pepper.

title: baked haddock or halibut
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Cover fish with white wine and allow to marinate.
Time not important.
Place marinated fish in bottom of casserole.
Toss bread cubes and onions together with salt and pepper to taste.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix well and store in a covered container in the refrigerator. Keeps at least 2 weeks.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Parboil 1 eggplant; cool.
Butter a shallow baking dish; add a layer of eggplant.
Dot with pieces of butter, a layer of Cheddar cheese, salt and pepper and a layer of Ritz crackers.
Repeat layers.
Beat 1 egg and enough milk to partially cover the eggplant.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: carrot cake(very delicious!)
directions: Grease and flour three 8 or 9-inch cake pans.
Combine oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat well.
Combine flour, cinnamon and soda.
Sift together and add to bowl.
Beat well.
Fold in the grated carrots.
Divide into the three cake pans and bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until cake springs back when touched in center.
Cool.

title: wedding punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice, sherbet and 1/2 the ice cream.
Beat until smooth.
Add ginger ale or 7-Up.
Spoon remaining ice cream into punch.
Serve immediately.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies.
Combine pudding and milk.
Beat 2 minutes. Mix cream cheese, sugar and butter until smooth.
Then combine both mixtures and beat real good.
Blend in an 8 ounce tub Cool Whip.
Layer in a large bowl:
line bowl with cookies, 1/3 of pudding, layer of cookies, 1/3 of pudding, layer of cookies, 1/3 pudding, cookies and remainder of pudding.
Top with cookies. Refrigerate.

title: whole grain bread
directions: Dissolve sugar, molasses and yeast in warm water.
Add salt and oil.
Beat in whole grain flours, using electric mixer.
Cover large area with 3 cups white flour.
Place beaten mixture in center and knead white flour until proper elasticity of dough is achieved.
Additional flour may be needed.
Divide the dough into 4ths.
Form into loaves.
Place in loaf pans.
Cover with damp towel.
Place in warm place and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool.

title: eastbrook cherry or apple crunch
directions: Put pie filling into an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Spread cake mix over it and sprinkle with melted butter.
Bake at 400°, uncovered, until very brown and dusky, for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: raw broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli and cut into bite size pieces.
Drain thoroughly.
Place in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Chill before serving.
Add a handful of dry roasted peanuts over top just before serving.

title: mock raspberry jam
directions: Bring 1st two
ingredients
to a boil; cook and stir 10 minutes.
Remove
from heat.
Add jello; stir until dissolved. Pour in small jars.
Pour wax on top or freeze.

title: classic green bean bake
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in 1/2 can onions and green beans.

title: marilyn's brown eyed susans
directions: Cream the margarine.
Add the sugar, almond extract, flour and salt.
Roll level tablespoons of this mixture into balls.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and flatten lightly.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes, after 5 to 10 minutes turn over and finish baking.
When cool, frost with chocolate icing.

title: perfect potluck dinner
directions: Grease casserole dish. Brown the beef. Cook the noodles while frying the onion, pepper and mushrooms. Add salt and pepper.

Pour tomato sauce, mustard and beans into the beef. Stir all together. Pour everything into the greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and top with the shredded Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kool-aid play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients in medium saucepan.
Add water and oil. Stir constantly over medium heat until ball forms (3 minutes). Knead 1 minute on floured surface.
Keep in airtight container in the refrigerator.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Cook all ingredients, except pecans, to hard boil stage.
Pour over nuts and put on wax paper and separate.
Freezes well.

title: grandma jackson's christmas cinnamon rolls
directions: On lightly floured board, roll dough into a 1/4-inch thick, oblong shape.
Melt Crisco and spread on dough.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
May sprinkle with raisins, if desired.
Roll up as a jelly roll, starting with long side.
Seal the seam by pinching the dough together.
Cut roll in 1-inch slices (may use thread to cut dough).
Place on lightly greased cookie sheets, approximately 8 rolls per sheet.
Let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes. Let cool.
Ice with powdered sugar icing.
Garnish center with a cherry.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put together in 13 x 9 inch dish and let set overnight.
Bake one hour at 300°.

title: baked pineapple(good served with baked ham)
directions: Combine ingredients in greased baking dish, except bread and oleo.
Cut bread into strips and place on top.
Pour melted oleo over all.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal coconut cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Mix rest of ingredients in and drop cookies on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix well.
Use Thousand Island dressing or other, if preferred.

title: different fried taters
directions: Cook in covered skillet until tender.
Add 3 ounces roast beef hash.
Brown slightly.
If using 15 ounce can of hash, divide into three 5-ounce sections.
Freeze the two unused sections for later.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Cook all veggies with seasonings in oil or butter until just tender.
Sprinkle 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese over cooked mixture and let stand a few minutes before serving.
Delicious and healthful!

title: carrot-whole wheat pretzels
directions: Combine whole wheat flour and yeast.
Heat and stir butter or margarine, honey and 2 cups water until warm (115° to 120°).
Add to flour mixture.
Add the 1 egg and carrot.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes.
Stir in as much of the all-purpose flour as you can.

title: baked custard
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, salt and vanilla. Add scalded milk gradually, stirring constantly. Pour into a lightly buttered 1-quart baking dish. Fill a 9 x 13 baking pan 1/3 full with warm water. Sprinkle nutmeg on the custard. Set custard in the pan. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes. Makes 5 servings.

title: banana and orange trifle
directions: Break up the trifle sponges and put in bottom of serving dish. Mix undiluted orange squash and sherry (about a teacupful altogether) and pour over sponge, making sure it is all moistened. Leave to stand, preferably overnight.

title: applesauce dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water in medium bowl. Stir in applesauce.
Pour into dessert dishes.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.
Diabetic Exchange Per Serving:
1/2 fruit.

title: b b q cups
directions: Saute beef and onions till done.
Drain, (I wash mine) Put beef back in pan.
Mix in BBQ sauce.
Simmer on low heat at least 15 minutes.
Set aside.

title: stir-fry crawfish
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add celery, onion and green pepper. Cook until tender.
Blend soup and broth and add to skillet.
Stir in soy sauce, pepper, crawfish and Chinese vegetables (be sure they're rinsed and drained).
Cook until heated throroughly and then serve on bed of rice.
Top with noodles.
Serves 6.

title: freezer lemon squares
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill.

title: chicken tostadas
directions: Cook chicken, cut into strips.
Fry tortillas crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Spread each tortilla generously with beans, chicken, lettuce and cheese, olives, tomato and avocado.
Top tostada with hot sauce.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in well-greased 8 x 8-inch pans at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: rockefeller dip
directions: Drain oysters, reserving liquor.
Grind all greens in the blender, using 1/2 cup oyster liquor and melted butter for liquid. Place in an enameled or stainless steel pan; add Worcestershire, lemon juice and seasonings.
Bring to simmer.
Blend or cut oysters into small pieces.
Add to spinach mixture along with breadcrumbs and continue to simmer about 1 hour or until raw taste is gone.
Check for seasonings.
May be frozen.
Yield:
1 1/2 quarts.

title: frozen salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Stir in fruit and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into 2 (1-quart) refrigerator trays; freeze overnight.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Heat 1/2 of the chocolate chips and margarine over low heat until melted.
Cool.
Heat oven to 375°.

title: turtle cake
directions: First, melt your butter, then put in the caramels (whole 16 ounce package) and the evaporated milk.
I melt the caramels, butter and milk in the microwave on High setting in 5 to 8 minutes, stirring often.
Add pecans.

title: cheese potato soup casserole
directions: In a large
bowl,
combine
potatoes, soup, sour cream, salt and pepper and half of the shredded cheese.
Butter one 9 x 13-inch pan well.
Pour
in the mixture.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1
hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10. Great leftover.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 layers according to directions on box.
Cool. Split into 4 layers.
Mix sugar, sour cream and coconut together. Chill.
Spread all but 1 cup with whipped cream.
Frost top and sides.
Seal in airtight container for 3 days before serving.

title: grandma ma's mac
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package and put to side in colander to drain.
Put cheese in medium casserole dish and add half stick of butter (cut up).
Pour drained, hot macaroni over cheese and butter, then stir until melted.
Season to taste with salt and Accent.
Add milk and stir; add eggs and stir.
Bake in oven at 375° for approximately 30 minutes.
Then bake at 400° until lightly browned on top.
Be sure to watch because of varying ovens.

title: play doh
directions: Put water and salt in a kettle.
Bring to 180° or until bubbles form on bottom of pan.
Remove from heat.
Add alum, oil, coloring and a couple drops of peppermint.
Add flour slowly so as not to get lumps.
Knead.
Refrigerate in an airtight container.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in large pot.
Take wrapper to grease the baking pan.
Pour in cherries, lemon juice and cinnamon into bowl.
Put in cake mix and mix all well.
Place in oven at 350° for 1 hour. Cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: chocolate fondue dipping sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients. Warm in a medium saucepan over low to medium heat.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Lightly brown hamburger and onion in heavy skillet or kettle. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer at least 1 hour.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice according to box directions.
Scramble eggs in 2 tablespoons of peanut oil and set aside.
On medium heat, heat 3 tablespoons of peanut oil; add rice.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add chicken broth, onions, soy sauce, pepper, eggs and sesame oil.
Continue stirring for 5 minutes.
You may add chicken or pork.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add condensed milk and lime juice until blended.
Mixture will thicken as it stands.
Very good.

title: david's favorite christmas italian fudge
directions: Put all ingredients together and put over low to medium heat. Cook mixture until it forms a ball in cold water.
Stir the entire time it cooks.
Once it forms a ball, remove from heat and beat until cool enough to pour into a pan.
Will only harden if it has been cooked long enough, otherwise get a spoon and eat caramels!

title: sandbakkelse
directions: Beat butter, margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, salt and flavoring.
Blend in flour.
Form into balls the size of a walnut.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press flat with fork dipped in cold water. Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes until light golden brown around edges.
Cool on rack. Store in airtight container in freezer.

title: lemon champagne punch
directions: Mix concentrated lemonade, pineapple juice and water; chill, covered, in refrigerator.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and sparkling water and pour over ice cubes or ice ring in large punch bowl.
Pour well-chilled champagne as evenly as possible over punch and stir gently.
Yields 50 servings.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Dissolve gelatin in just enough boiling water to make a paste (1 to 2 tablespoons).
Mix all other ingredients, except the sugar, into the paste.
Measure the resulting mixture and add 1 cup sugar for every 1 1/2 cups of mixture.
Top with garnish (pecans).

title: burger beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef or chuck in margarine in soup pot, stirring until crumbly.
Add onion and cook until lightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Combine tomato juice and soup with 1 can of water in bowl, mixing well.
Add to ground chuck or beef mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: alex's meatballs
directions: Mix these ingredients together in a large bowl; form meatballs and add to sauce raw.
The meatballs will cook in the sauce.
If you make the sauce without the meatballs, you may need to add a little water or wine to make the sauce a little thinner.
The sauce starts out very thick, but the meatballs thin it out.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Simmer chicken breasts in butter and lemon juice until all liquid is gone.
In same skillet, pour both cans of soup over chicken with about 1/2 cup water.
Let simmer on low heat about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Put over rice or noodles.
Tastes great and fast and easy to cook.
If you want more twang to it just add more lemon juice.

title: maryann's chicken stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry chicken in hot oil over high heat.
Add onion, celery and carrots.
Stir-fry just until crisp-tender.
Quickly blend cornstarch with soy sauce in small bowl.
Stir in sugar and ginger. Add at once to skillet with green pepper, mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Stir-fry about 3 to 4 minutes longer until sauce thickens slightly and becomes shiny.
Serve on hot cooked rice.

title: reese's cup fudge
directions: Melt margarine.
Combine all ingredients and press into 9-inch square pan.
Cut into squares.

title: new orleans pecan pie
directions: Mix well first 6 ingredients.
Cook in double boiler or microwave until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Mix butter and flour and pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar, vanilla and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Mix chocolate pudding and 1 1/4 cups milk.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Let stand.
Mix butterscotch pudding and 1 1/4 cups milk.
Pour over chocolate layer.
Spread top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped Skor candy bars.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Prepare yellow cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour into a greased and floured cookie sheet with sides or a jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix 2 boxes of instant vanilla pudding with half the milk called for on box, then add Philly cream cheese and mix well.
Spread on cooled cake. Sprinkle pineapple over pudding.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions and spread on top of pineapple.
Top with coconut. Keep refrigerated.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
