Place in 8-inch round shallow casserole (1 to 1 1/2-inch deep).
Toast almonds in butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: baked pork chops and rice
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper.
Brown in skillet.
Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with rice.
Mix soup, milk and salt.
Heat and pour over the chops and rice.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle chopped pecans in bottom of Bundt pan.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits into quarters and roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Arrange pieces in Bundt pan.
Melt butter and add brown sugar.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: sweet milk biscuits
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder; add shortening and milk. Mix with spoon or by hand.
Roll dough on floured board to about 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut and bake in hot oven.
This recipe will make about 16 small biscuits.

title: kentucky kernals
directions: Soak the pecans in the bourbon overnight.
Grate the butter into the powdered sugar.
Use fork to blend, not hands.
Add nuts and mix well.
Make into small balls using powdered sugar to keep hands from sticking (the mixture is very soft so I keep it in the refrigerator and do a small amount at a time).
Freeze balls.
Dip into melted semi-sweet chocolate and paraffin.
(I use about 1/4 of a bar of paraffin to one large bag of chips; use only real chocolate chips.)
Let cool and set.
Store in a tin in a cool place.
These are definitely an "adult only" confection.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and add topping.

title: green rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: milk punch
directions: Dip sherbet and ice cream into punch bowl. Add milk.
Pour chilled 7-Up over the mixture.

title: fried okra
directions: Wash and thinly slice okra, onion and pepper.
Add vegetable flakes.
Prepare wok or frying pan, using a very low-fat oil. Slide vegetables in and stir until tender, about 20 minutes.

title: beanless chili
directions: Cook meat, garlic, onion and green pepper in a heavy skillet over medium-high heat, stirring frequently to break up meat.
Cook until onion is soft and meat has lost its pink color.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat. Simmer for 45 minutes, stirring frequently.
Let simmer longer for even better flavor.

title: corn and mac bake
directions: In 8 x 8 greased baking dish, place both corns, melted butter, cheese and macaroni. Mix and bake at 350° until bubbly and set.

title: no-knead rolls
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and boiling water.
Cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine all ingredients and mix with a spoon.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Make into
rolls.
Let rise.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: vlasta's czech potato soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until translucent.
Add the flour.
Make a roux over low flame.
Add vegetables and stir, then add 3 1/2 to 4 quarts of cold water.
Cook for 45 minutes over low to medium heat.
And the Maggi brand seasoning, if desired. Serve, garnished with chopped parsley.

title: corn pone
directions: Add butter last. Bake in 9 x 9 pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl, then place in a buttered casserole dish.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender; drain.
Drain peas; reserve some juice to mix in later.
Mix tuna, noodles, soup and peas together. Put in a casserole dish.
Spread cracker crumbs or chip crumbs on top of mixture.
May add cheese slices to top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted or until casserole starts to brown around edges.

title: easy tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Drop on cookie sheet 1 teaspoon at a time.
Press with fingers real thin.
Bake at 325° until golden brown around edge.
Remove from oven and let cool about 2 minutes.
Lift from cookie sheet.

title: cabbage in cheese sauce
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water for 8 minutes or just until tender.
Melt butter in saucepan and saut onion for 5 minutes. Blend in flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Add milk and stir until boiling; cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Stir in 3/4 c. cheese until melted.
Add cabbage and turn into greased baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs mixed with cheese.
Bake at 375 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: rye bread
directions: Combine in a mixing bowl the scalded milk, salt, shortening and molasses.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in rye flour.
(One tablespoon crushed caraway seed may be added, if desired.)
Add yeast to warm water.
Let stand a few minutes, then stir to dissolve.
Add milk mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Mix in remaining flour, a little at a time, stirring by hand, until dough is quite stiff and the sides and bottom of bowl are clean.

title: salmon quiche
directions: Drain liquid from salmon and add enough water or milk to make 1/4 cup.
Bake empty crust 10 minutes at 400°.
Combine ingredients and put in crust, reduce temperature to 325° and bake 30 minutes.

title: reese's peanut butter cup treats
directions: Mix together and shape into balls the size of small walnut. Spray small muffin pans with Pam and put the balls into muffin pan.
Bake for 9 minutes at 350°, no more.
Do not overbake. Press Reese's peanut butter cups into each and let cool.
Makes approximately 48.

title: green chile stew
directions: Brown meat.
Add all ingredients to crock-pot.
Simmer all day.
Serve in soup bowls with flour tortillas.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix in bowl the vegetables and salsa.
Layer hamburger in bottom of dish, then add layer of vegetables, then hamburger and so on.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 300° until cheese melts.

title: nacho chip dip
directions: Heat on low the milk, cheese and salt. Stir occasionally. Brown the sausage, cooking thoroughly. Drain grease from sausage and add to cheese sauce. Add jalapenos. Dip nacho chips in cheese dip or use cheese dip as topping to a taco salad.

title: tea cakes
directions: Beat eggs, soft butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour gradually.
Roll on lightly floured board and cut out.
Bake at 350° until done.
Don't overbake.

title: hot tomato kraut(for canning)
directions: Chop cabbage, then dice up tomatoes and peppers; mix well. Put in quart jars.
Add 1 tablespoon pickling salt to each quart, then fill with water.
Let stay in a warm place for about 4 days and then tighten your lids tighter.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put in crock pot.
Cook on low for 3 hours.
Save 1/2 cup cheese to sprinkle on top.

title: lite pumpkin pie
directions: Bake one pie crust according to package directions.
Set aside.
In a large saucepan, combine gelatin, cornstarch, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger and salt.
Stir in pumpkin and evaporated skim milk.
Let stand 5 minutes to soften gelatin.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture bubbles; cook and stir for 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir 1 cup hot mixture into eggs; return all egg mixture to the saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat for 2 minutes.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat. Stir in Equal.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Cover and chill 6 hours or overnight.
Contains 237 calories per serving.

title: bacon-bit spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: crab quiche
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in olive oil and butter until onions are clear and mushrooms are soft.
Add wine and crab meat; season with salt, pepper and Tabasco and simmer for 2 minutes.
Spread evenly over bottom of quiche dish which has been sprayed with Pam. (I use a 10-inch Corning Ware dish.)
Pour beaten eggs, mixed with cream evenly over crab mixture.
Top with Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until mixture is firm and cheese browns.

title: red rock candy
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a heavy 3-quart saucepan. Cook, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often, about 10 minutes or until mixture reaches soft ball stage (234°).
Add cinnamon candies, cook stirring constantly, to hard crack stage (300°).
Remove from heat, stir in butter.
Quickly pour into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Break into small pieces to serve.
Yields 1 1/2 pounds.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with bacon.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: mae zimmerman's stuffed peppers
directions: Cut centers out of door knob peppers.
Remove all seeds. Grate cabbage.
To 3 heads of cabbage, add 1/2 cup canning salt and bruise with hands.
Put cabbage into the peppers and place in jars.
Bring water, vinegar and sugar to a boil.
Pour over peppers.
Place lids on jars.
Put in a hot water bath for 15 minutes until lids seal.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar well.
Add eggs, beating well after each addition.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with the milk.
Add flavoring and fold in coconut.
Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain and mix all the beans; add celery, pimento, sliced onion and salt.
Cover beans with mixture of salad oil, sugar and vinegar.
Marinate for 24 hours.
Stir several times.
Add salt and sugar as needed.
Drain before serving.
(Sometimes I just use green, yellow and kidney beans.)

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar, then refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight.
Add other ingredients and chill.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cube bell peppers, onions and pineapple.
Saute the cubed mixture.
Mix tomato sauce, sugar, soy sauce and garlic.
Stir in chicken.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 8 hours.
Broil chicken 7 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Turn and broil for 7 to 10 minutes more or until done.
Serve with sauteed vegetables.

title: sweet carrot sticks
directions: Cut carrots into sticks.
Let soak in pineapple juice for 1 hour or longer.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes a great quick sweet snack.

title: squash pickles
directions: Place squash in layers.
Sprinkle each layer with salt.
Let stand overnight.
(Use non-tarnish bowl.)
Drain squash.
Heat all other ingredients in vinegar.
When strikes a boil, add squash. Boil 4 minutes.
Can in sterilized jars.
Process 5 minutes.

title: fruit slush
directions: Mix all together and freeze.
Stir often while it is freezing.
Thaw slightly before serving.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: In a medium saucepan lightly beat egg. Stir in milk, sugar, and butter. Cook and stir over medium heat about 12 minutes or until thickened and bubbly. Remove from heat. Stir in coconut and pecans. Cover and cool thoroughly.

title: fried chicken croquettes
directions: Mix together the chicken, carrot, mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice, soy sauce and pepper.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Shape into 12 balls.
Roll in flour.
Pour oil into fryer, filling 1/3 full. Heat.
Fry croquettes, 4 at a time, about 2 minutes.
Turn; repeat until golden brown.

title: chicken delight
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil; pour over chicken. Add stuffing and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: patchwork cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar until blended.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour.
Spread evenly in well-buttered 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 18 minutes until lightly browned.
Remove from oven; quickly spread chocolate pieces over baked cookie base.
Return to oven 2 to 3 minutes to soften chocolate.
Remove from oven; immediately spread chocolate evenly over base.
Make off in squares and top with the following:
rainbow sprinkles, chopped nuts, coconut, crushed peppermint candy, etc.
Chill just until frosting is set.
Cut into squares.
Arranged patchwork style on serving tray.

title: granola goody bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at low speed, scraping sides often until well mixed, 1 to 2 minutes.
Press firmly into a 9-inch square baking pan. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are browned.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Makes about 2 dozen bars.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix everything together, except sour cream, and pour half into 9 x 13-inch container.
Refrigerate until jello is firm.
Spread all of sour cream on top of this and add remaining jello mixture.

title: country dinner
directions: Cook and drain noodles add 1 can soup, milk and rest of ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat in a greased long pan.
Then mix the remaining ingredients and pour over first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: soused apple cake
directions: Soak apples in brandy. Beat together the sugar, oil and eggs. Sift dry ingredients and combine with egg mixture.
Add apples, walnuts and raisins. Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour. Cool and serve with whipped cream or plain.
Use a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in syrup, sugar, melted butter and pecans.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in center of oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: ham and bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight and then drain.
In a large pan combine the beans, 6 cups of water, ham, salt and garlic.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 hours.
Then add 2 cups water and vegetables to beans.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Bring water and butter to boil and remove from heat.
Add flour and eggs (one at a time).
Beat with large wooden spoon, do not use mixer.
Pour into ungreased pan and bake at 400 degrees for 25 minutes.
Crust will bubble with air pockets.
Press down with heavy glass until flat and allow to cool.
Beat pudding, cream cheese and milk until smooth (some lumps are okay).
Pour into prepared crust.
Spread with cool whip and drizzle with syrup of choice.
Chill and serve.

title: monte's roman bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Add yeast and sugar to tepid water. Stir well to dissolve both.
Add flour, salt and onion.
Knead until smooth.
Place in oiled bowl.
Let rise until double.
Punch down.
Flatten to thickness of 1 inch on an oiled cookie sheet. Oil top and let rise to double again.
Sprinkle with additional salt, rosemary and basil to taste.
Bake in preheated oven for about 20 minutes until golden.
Cut in squares to serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine all and
pour
into
buttered
pan (cake pan is good). Bake at 350° for 2 hours, stirring occasionally in the first hour.

title: punch
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and add the rest.
Mix together and when ready to serve, add 1 quart of ginger ale.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cut meat into cubes and brown in large skillet.
Drain juice and transfer to large pot.
After meat is brown, cover completely with water (keep water level high) and boil slowly in skillet for 30 minutes.
Cut up tomatoes and add with their juice to the large pot.
Add 1 (11.5 ounce) can water, both vegetable juices and the next 8 ingredients.
Salt and pepper carefully to taste.
Bring to a boil and cook slowly.
Add meat and juice.
Cook 3 hours, stirring frequently.
Drain corn and peas and add about 30 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and milk together and cook over medium heat until comes to a rapid boil, then cook a full 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and the peanut butter. Stir in the oatmeal.
Sometimes it may take a little more oatmeal to be thick enough to drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Grease and flour 1 large pan or 2 smaller ones.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and sugar.
Blend in margarine. Add raisins and caraway seed.
Mix with buttermilk combined with the beaten egg.
Spoon batter into pan or pans and brush top with milk.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel apples and chop; set aside.
Pour Mazola oil into large mixing bowl; add sugar.
Mix.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Sift flour with salt, soda and baking powder.
Save back enough flour mixture to coat apples and pecans.
Gradually add flour to creamed mixture.
Gently fold in chopped apples and pecans.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Clean strawberries; add desired amount of sugar and let set. Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add water and Karo syrup.
Cook over medium heat until clear and thickened.
Add jello and cool slightly.
Pour mixture over strawberries in pie shell. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
May top with whipped cream if desired.

title: mexican veal steak with noodles
directions: Cut steak into small slices.
Dredge with flour.
Heave butter or olive oil.
Saute the meat quickly on both sides until brown.
Reduce the heat.
Cover the meat with onions, chili sauce and stock.
Simmer closely covered about 1/2 hour.

title: chicken-noodle casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Debone and dice.
Cook noodles, pepper, onion and celery in chicken broth.
Mix noodles with 3 cans of soup in a large casserole dish and add cheese.
Bake in oven until cheese melts.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix 1st 4 ingredients and bake in 350° oven about 20 minutes. Mix next 4 ingredients and spread over cake layers.
Add a little sugar and cornstarch to pie filling (if needed).
Put pie filling between the layers and on top.

title: peach custard dessert
directions: Put 2 slices bread in bottom of glass loaf baking dish.
Slice peaches and put on top of bread.
Sprinkle with 3 tablespoons sugar.
Put remaining 2 slices of bread on top of peaches.
Beat eggs well.
Add milk, sugar and vanilla and pour over bread-peach layers.
Put baking dish in shallow pan of water and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: batter for deep fry oysters
directions: Mix and let set for 4 or 5 hours.
Deep fry oysters.
Goes good with green salad.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Brown beef. Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add sauce, corn and chili mix to the cooked mixture. Pour in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix corn bread as directed on package. Spread over top of mixture. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Grate or sprinkle your favorite cheese over top.
Put back in oven to melt cheese.

title: crawfish dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Saute meat and seasonings until tender.
Add both soups. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: cheesy crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 375°, or according to package directions. Separate dough into sixteen triangles. Sprinkle each with about 2 tablespoons of the cheese. Roll up tightly, starting at the shortest side of the triangle. Place pointed end down on an ungreased baking sheet, curve slightly to form a crescent. In a small bowl, beat egg and water. Brush over top of crescents. Sprinkle with seeds. Bake 12 to 14 minutes or until puffed and golden brown. Serve warm.

title: crawfish salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Eat and enjoy.
Serves 8.

title: brenda's best-ever lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly, spooning off excess fat.
Add next 5 ingredients and simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Cook noodles in large amount of salted, boiling water.
Drain and rinse.
Combine remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella.

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350°; bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Shell and cut eggs in half, lengthwise.
Remove the yolks. Sieve them and add mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper and optional items.
Stir in enough mayonnaise to bind together.
Pile into the hollows of the reserved egg whites.

title: chili stuffed peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut bell peppers lengthwise in half. Remove seeds and membranes.
Place peppers, cut side up, in rectangular 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook ground beef or turkey and onion in 10-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until meat is brown.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Divide meat mixture evenly among peppers.
Cover and bake 40 to 45 minutes or until peppers are tender.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix together and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate heath bar cake
directions: Combine above ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: poor man's crab rangoon
directions: Rinse tuna and flake.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Cream the cream cheese and add the onions, sauce and garlic powder.
Mix in tuna.
Spread 1 teaspoon of filling in each won ton skin.
Fold over and fry in hot oil until lightly browned.

title: country chicken
directions: In a large kettle, combine chicken, salt, bay leaf and water. (Lower calorie:
skin chicken; tastes just as good for less fat.) Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 1 hour.
Let chicken cool to touch.
Remove all bones and skin.
Discard bones and skin.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces or to your desired size.
Return the chicken to the pot.
Add onion, carrots, celery, peas and potatoes. Simmer for about 15 minutes.
In a bowl, combine biscuit mix, milk and thyme; mix lightly.
Bring chicken, broth and vegetables to a boil; drop dough from teaspoon into soup.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Serves approximately 4.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crust:
Melt 1 stick oleo; add graham cracker crumbs and press on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: janet's pudding cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and pudding until lumps are gone.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Shake until level.
Scatter brown sugar, chocolate bits and nuts on top and press into batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; test.

title: chicken with honey and orange juice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rub the skin and inside the chicken with salt.
Place the onions in a roasting pot and place the chicken on top.
Heat the honey, oil and orange juice until the honey dissolves.
Add the pepper.
Spoon some of the sauce inside the chicken and the rest over the top.
Bake for about 1 1/2 hours, basting occasionally with the juice.
Slice the orange and use them to garnish the chicken.
Serve with rice or potatoes.
Serves 4.

title: baked cavatelli
directions: Prepare pasta, drain and set aside.
Cook sausage in a large skillet; drain fat except for 1 tablespoon.
Cook green onions and garlic until tender.
Use 2-quart casserole. Combine pasta, sausage, onion mixture, tomato sauce, spaghetti sauce, 1/2 Mozzarella, Italian seasoning and pepper.
Mix thoroughly. Bake, covered, in a
375° oven for 25 minutes.
Uncover and put remaining Mozzarella on top.
Continue to bake 5 or 10 minutes more.

title: christmas salad
directions: Wash vegetables.
Break broccoli and cauliflower into small pieces.
Slice radishes into thin pieces.
Sprinkle dry Ranch-style dressing.
Moisten with mayonnaise.

title: turnip casserole
directions: Cook turnips according to directions on package.
Fold in sugar, egg, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix Ritz cracker crumbs with melted butter.
Put turnip mixture in oven-proof casserole.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Cook 1 hour at 325°.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Place candy in refrigerator until cold, leave in the wrapper to crush bars.
Beat eggs, add sugar, peanut butter, crushed candy bars, vanilla and milk.
Pour in gallon ice cream freezer and finish filling with whole milk (approximately 2 quarts and 1 cup of milk).

title: cheezy cornbread
directions: Stir together and pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 375° until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: incredibly good toasted cheese surprise
directions: Toast a piece of bread.
Then place a slice of cheese on each piece of bread and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Place the sandwich in the microwave and heat on High for 20 seconds or until the chocolate chips begin to get soft.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients
together and let set overnight for best results.
Serve with Wheat Thins or other crackers.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Grease 9 inch pie plate.
Cook beef--drain.
Pour beef into pie pan.
Spread flat.
Sprinkle with salt and cheese.
Stir remaining ingredients until blended.
Pour into pie plate.

title: easy nacho dip
directions: Melt cheese over low heat.
Add meat and chili.
Great in a crock-pot.
Serve with corn chips.

title: easy barbecue chicken
directions: Put ingredients into a kettle on top of stove, including chicken.
Bring to a boil.
Do not cover.
Simmer until chicken is done.
Sauce will boil down and cover chicken.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Melt butter and mix with flour and pecans.
Put into pan and cook at 350° for 13-15 minutes.
Let this cool completely before adding the next step.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Butter bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Season meat with chili powder, salt and garlic.
Place half of Doritos in 3-quart casserole dish.
Add seasoned meat, beans, onion and cubed cheese. Top with remaining Doritos.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Soften margarine and cream cheese.
Beat until well blended. Add sugar 1 cup at a time.
Blend well after each cup.
Add flour 1 cup at a time.
Blend well, adding 2 eggs at a time.
Then add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Bake in tube or 13 x 9 x 2-inch well-greased and floured pan.

title: butter cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks and beat thoroughly.
Sift flour, measure and sift with baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk to sugar and butter.
Beat thoroughly.
Add flavoring.
Fold in eggs.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine butter and flour over low-medium heat.
Add milk and water slowly (like gravy).
Add all the rest of the ingredients. Simmer until almost at a boil.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until fluffy.
Add peanut butter and whip. Add sugar and continue beating; when blended gradually add milk. When blended, fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) graham cracker crusts and freeze.

title: 1 meal salad
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator for 1 1/2 hours for flavors to mix together and set; no salad dressing is needed.

title: scripture cake
directions: Bake in moderate oven (360° to 375°).
Follow Solomon's advice for making good boys and you will have a good cake.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of a 9 x 14-inch pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine dry cake mix and margarine.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Spread over pie filling and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream oleo and butter.
Add egg and beat until creamy.
Add dry ingredients sifted together.
Stir thoroughly.
Add chopped nuts and apples.
Bake in a 7 x 11-inch pan at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut in squares.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, salt and lemon juice.
Add 1/2 cup grapes (may be cut in half) and half of oranges to chicken mixture.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed of mixer until smooth. Gradually add the sugar, beating until blended. Gently fold in whipped topping. Place half of cake cubes in a large glass bowl. Top with half of cheese mixture. Spread half of cherry filling over cheese mixture. Repeat layers with remaining cake cubes, cheese mixture and cherry filling. Cover and chill. Yield: 12 servings (serving size: 1 cup).

title: apple pudding - for the birds
directions: In a skillet or saucepan, warm the fat until pourable. Meanwhile, stir together the remaining ingredients.
Gradually add the fat to the fruit mixture until a sample just holds its shape when squeezed.
Press into muffin cups fitted with paper liners, or pack into a loaf pan or square baking pan lined with plastic or foil.
Clean tuna or cat food cans can also be used (no need for liners).
Chill until firm.

title: goulash
directions: Cook hamburger meat about half done.
Add celery, onion and other spices.
(If you like, add garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce to taste.)
Finish cooking or brown good.
Boil macaroni until done.
Use very little water (don't have to drain).
When macaroni is done, add hamburger, tomatoes and sauce and let simmer about 15 or 20 minutes.

title: reduced fat peanut butter cocoa macaroons
directions: In a small saucepan melt peanut butter over low heat, stirring constantly; set aside to cool.
In a small bowl mix together 1/4 cup sugar and cocoa powder; set aside.
In large mixer bowl beat egg whites and vanilla until soft peaks form.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating until soft peaks form.
Fold in the peanut butter, cocoa mixture, coconut and raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until set.
Remove and cool completely on wire racks.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Blend sugar and cinnamon.
Grease a 10-inch Bundt pan and dust with 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon mix.
Blend cake mix, applesauce and eggs until moistened.
Beat as directed on box. Reserve 1 1/2 cups batter.
Pour rest into pan.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mix on top, then pour reserved batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool cake in pan for 15 minutes.
Invert on plate.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water with salt.
Drain and add cheese.
Mix until cheese melts.
One serving equals 1 bread and 2 meat exchanges.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except stuffing.
Pour into lightly greased casserole.
Sprinkle stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening. Pour in raisins and nuts. Mix well together and pour out on waxed paper. Refrigerate until hard. Break into pieces and serve.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Make pudding as directed on package using 2 1/2 cups milk.
Let set for 5 minutes.
Add Cool Whip.
Layer graham crackers in a cake pan and add 1/2 pudding, another layer of crackers and rest of pudding, another layer of crackers, then top with pie filling. Chill 4 hours or overnight.

title: homemade hot fudge
directions: Mix 3/4 cup milk with sugar; set aside.
Mix cocoa, 1/4 cup milk and flour; mix well.
Add this to the milk and sugar in a saucepan.
Heat over medium heat.
After it thickens, remove from heat and add butter, vanilla and pinch of salt.
Serve over your favorite ice cream.

title: sour cream pancakes with strawberries
directions: Combine egg yolks, milk and sour cream; stir well and set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Gradually add to the sour cream mixture; stir until smooth.
Add melted butter.
Beat room temperature egg whites until stiff peaks form. Fold into batter mixture.
Pour 1/2 cup of batter for each pancake onto hot, lightly greased griddle.
Turn when top is covered with bubbles and edges appear cooked.
Serve with warm strawberry topping.

title: chicken a-la-can-can
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook for 7 minutes. Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Top with French fried onion rings.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Slice peaches into greased 9

X 13 pan. Make a batter of sugar, flour, milk, baking powder and salt. Batter is thick. Spoon batter over peaches. Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon together & sprinkle over batter. Top with boiling water. Bake at 375 degrees for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased bread pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: linguine with tomato and basil
directions: Combine tomatoes, Brie, garlic, basil, 1 cup oil, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Prepare at least 2 hours ahead.
Cover and store at room temperature.
Bring 6 quarts water to boil and add 1 tablespoon oil and salt.
Add linguine and boil for 10 minutes. Drain pasta and toss with tomato mixture.
Not recommended for freezing.
Very good and very fattening!
Serves 5 to 6.

title: apple chunkies
directions: Sift dry ingredients and put in large mixing bowl.
Add apples and nuts.
Mix butter, eggs and vanilla.
Combine with other ingredients until well blended and flour is moistened.
Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal date cookie
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and soda water.
Blend. Add oatmeal and flour.
Roll and cut 2 circles for each cookie. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: buried cherry cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, beat butter on medium speed until softened.
Add sugar and beat until mix is fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat.
In a medium mixing bowl, stir together the flour, cocoa, baking soda and powder and salt.
With mixer on low speed, gradually add to butter mixture, beating until well mixed.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down center of each ball with your thumb.
Drain cherries, reserving juice.
Place a cherry in the center of each cookie.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Stir milk, soup and parsley together.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan put a layer of potatoes, onion and sliced corned beef alternately until gone.
Then pour soup mixture over this.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: reese's cups
directions: Melt butter.
Mix remaining ingredients together with butter. Spread in 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan or dish.
Melt chocolate chips quickly and spread over the other ingredients.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: pizza burger
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Mozzarella cheese; form patties (very thin).
Place a slice of Mozzarella cheese between 2 and seal edges.
Fry as usual.
Serve on buns.
Makes 4 burgers.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 550° for 20 minutes or microwave 4 to 6 minutes to serve warm.
(May also serve cold.)

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Mix together with a wire whisk or mixer. Store in refrigerator.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: papa's mama's banana bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and shortening.
Add bananas and well beaten eggs.
Mix quickly.
Do not overmix.
Bake in small loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until done in the middle.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix starter, oil, salt, sugar, water and wheat flour (can use white flour).
Stir and add bread flour.
Stir well.
it will form a ball.
Oil a large bowl, put dough in it and cover it.
Place in warm place and let rise for 8 hours or overnight.
Make into 2 or 3 loaves and put in well-oiled pans.
Let it double in size for 8 hours.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 30 minutes.
Butter the tops of the bread and drop from pans after cooling for a few minutes.

title: cherry wink cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside. Cream sugar and Crisco.
Blend in eggs; add buttermilk and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts, dates and cherries.
Shape into balls.
Crush corn flakes and roll each ball in crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: junk salad
directions: Mix and let set in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.

title: microwave cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and margarine (which has been broken into small chunks).
Stir until margarine melts.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add oats and margarine. Mix well.
Add white sugar and eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into utility dish.
Bake 12 minutes, turning dish often.

title: spinach spoon bread
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Cook onions and spinach according to box directions and strain spinach well.
Mix together eggs, sour cream, butter and salt.
Stir in muffin mix.
Blend in spinach and onions and cream sauce.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until brown.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Put back in oven until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: granny white's lemon cheesecake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to box, making 4 layers.

title: chicken ala king for 100
directions: In a large kettle, melt butter.
Add flour and stir to make paste.
Add broth gradually while stirring.
Cook until thickened. In second kettle, parboil vegetables.
Stir into gravy.
Blend in chicken and heat through, stirring occasionally. Serve over baking powder biscuits.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw frozen spinach; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Enjoy!

title: fig preserves
directions: Wash figs and slice lemon.
Combine sugar and water; cook 5 minutes.
Add figs and lemon.
Cook rapidly until clear.
Seal in clean hot jars.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Thaw strawberries completely.
Sift dry ingredients and mix gently until just well mixed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer if necessary.

title: perfect peppermint patties
directions: In a bowl, combine first four ingredients.
Add milk and mix well.
(It will be sticky.)
Dust hands with confectioners sugar and roll into 1-inch balls and place on wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Chill 30 minutes.
Flatten with a glass to 1/4-inch. Freeze 1 hour.
In double boiler or microwave-safe bowl, melt chocolate chips and shortening.
Dip patties; place on wax paper to harden.
Store in airtight container.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Stir flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine milk, egg and zucchini.
Drop from tablespoon into deep fat.
Fry 3 to 4 minutes; drain.
Makes 24 fritters.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Mix together sugar, soy sauce and wine.
Marinate strips in mixture for 20 minutes.
Stir-fry green pepper strips and onions in oil.
(Salt oil first.)
Remove from pan but reserve oil.
Stir-fry garlic, ginger and scallions in reserved oil.
Add salt to taste and 1 additional tablespoon oil, if needed.
Add meat and stir-fry a few minutes.
Return onions and peppers to skillet.
Add tomato wedges.

title: jerome bars
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Over low heat melt margarine.
Add sugar.
Beat egg into evaporated milk and add to margarine and sugar mixture.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add coconut, pecans and graham cracker crumbs.
Stir and spread on crackers in pan.
Add another layer of graham crackers and press lightly into filling.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Pour the melted stick of butter over the dry cake mix in a mixing bowl.
Stir with a fork until well combined.
(Mixture should form a crumbly dough-like ball.)
Stir in nuts at this point if desired; or if slightly crunchier nuts are desired, sprinkle them on top just before baking.

title: red velvet cake, cooked frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk to pudding stage stirring constantly until thick. Cool. Cream butter and crisco. Add sugar and beat until creamy. Add cooked pudding slowly and beat until fluffy.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with the milk to creamed mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in nuts and egg whites.
Pour into 2 greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool.
Before serving, put layers together and frost with sweetened whipped cream.
Sprinkle with chopped hickory nuts.

title: oysters rockefeller
directions: Remove stems from spinach; process spinach in food processor until fine.
Process onion, garlic and parsley.
Put in a large bowl and add melted butter, crushed crackers and cheeses.
Mix well until nice and thick.
Put in refrigerator to set up.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs 5 minutes and gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir together flour, baking powder, spices and salt.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.

title: carrot and potato soup
directions: Peel and cut carrots and potatoes into 1-inch chunks.
In a 5 to 6-quart pan over medium-high heat, melt butter and add onions. Cook until golden.
Stir in potatoes and carrots.
Add chicken broth and bring to a boil; reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender when pierced.
Whirl in blender until smoothly pureed.
Return to pan.
Stir in milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir on medium-high heat until hot.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Bake cake and cool.
Mix pudding and spread over cake.
Slice bananas on pudding.
Spread Cool Whip on bananas.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Chill in refrigerator for two (2) hours.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until slightly brown.
(When I make these, I make half a recipe.)
They also freeze very well.

title: graham ghosts
directions: Spread marshmallow cream on graham squares.
Make features with chocolate morsels.

title: basic white cake
directions: Sift into bowl first 4 ingredients.
Add Crisco and half of milk.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add eggs, vanilla and rest of milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan for strip cake or 2 layer cake pans.

title: layered breakfast cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix cake mix, pudding mix, sour cream, eggs and vegetable oil in a mixing bowl. In a separate bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon and walnuts. Layer bottom of bundt pan with walnut mixture. Pour 1/2 cake mixture over walnut layer. Repeat with walnuts mix, then cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: baked chocolate pudding
directions: Stir sugar, cocoa, cinnamon and nuts into mix; add milk.
Beat 3 minutes at low speed.
Spread in pan.
For topping, combine brown sugar and cocoa and sprinkle over batter in greased pan. Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with sauce that forms beneath it.
Top with whipped cream if desired, or serve cold with ice cream.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Wet hands in cold water and make 2 balls.
Mix pecans, paprika and parsley flakes in pan and roll balls in mixture.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Cook
brown sugar, butter and cream until golden brown. Remove from
heat
and
add
flour,
beating until mixture is smooth. Then add milk and eggs which have been beaten together.
Return to	medium	heat and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
When
cool,
pour into baked pie shell. Spread meringue on top and brown in oven at 350°.

title: easy cake
directions: Mix all.
Pour into a long greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: lemon raspberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; mix well.
In small bowl, combine oil, half and half, lemon extract and eggs; mix well.
Add to dry ingredients and stir. Fold in raspberries and fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 425° for 18 to 23 minutes (21 minutes works best for me).
Makes 14 to 17 muffins.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt the first 4 ingredients in a double boiler. Add the popped corn, M&M's and salted peanuts.
Mix well and press into well-greased Bundt pan. Turn out after 10 to 15 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fry in oil until brown.

title: microwave chocolate pie
directions: Mix 1 1/2 c. sugar, cocoa, flour and cornstarch in a 2-qt mixing bowl (microwavable) to get out all lumps and set aside. Mix together and set aside:
1/4 c. milk and 3 egg yolks, slightly beaten.
Put 2 c. milk in microwave and bring to a simmer - about 2-3 minutes.
Blend the sugar/cocoa mixture with the milk/egg yolks and slowly add the 2 c. simmered milk.
Once all of the above is blended, cook on high in microwave in 3-minute increments.
Whisk and put back in microwave.
Cook for about 3 or 4 3-minute increments until mixture is thick enough to "ripple" when dropped from a spoon.
Add 1 stick butter (or margarine) and 1 tsp. of vanilla.
Stir until smooth and pour into a baked 9-inch deep-dish crust.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In large saucepan cook potatoes in 1/2 to 3/4 cup water until soft.
Mash potatoes
in
cooking water.
Add 1/2 to 3/4 cup water, broccoli and bouillon cube.
Cook until broccoli is tender. Add milk; heat
through.
Mix
sour
cream and flour. Slowly stir into soup mixture.
Add salt, pepper and butter to taste.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine all shredded items in large bowl and set aside. In smaller bowl mix all other ingredients. Pour mixture over cabbage and stir. Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix dressing as indicated on envelope with vinegar, water and oil. Cook spaghetti according to package directions to "al dente". Do not overcook. Chop vegetables; mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Cover bowl securely and refrigerate.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit; set aside.
In a separate bowl, mix pineapple juice with a large box of vanilla instant pudding.
Pour fruit and mix well.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix in small bowl; set aside.
Layer, putting beans, hamburger, then sour cream mixture, picante sauce, tomatoes, avocado dip, olives, Cheddar cheese and green onions.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: fried shrimp
directions: Peel shrimp and devein.
Mix milk, vinegar, baking powder and eggs.
Put shrimp in mixture and soak for at least 1 hour.
Remove shrimp.
Sprinkle shrimp with Tony's Creole seasoning.
Roll in flour and fry.

title: ginger-garlic "chicken"
directions: Combine soy sauce and next 6 ingredients into an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Add chix, turning to coat; cover and refrigerate 2 hours (turning occasionally).
Remove chix from marinade.
Place marinated chix on lightly greased cookie sheet or pan.
Broil 7 minutes on each side or until done.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: chili rellenos(appetizer)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish by brushing lightly with vegetable oil or spray with Pam.

title: sweetheart cake
directions: Prepare cake mix per package directions for 2 round layers. Add cherries and walnuts to mix and bake according to package directions.
Cool and frost with cherry frosting.
This is a beautiful dessert for Valentine's Day, or anytime you want to please your sweetheart.

title: best breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer as follows:
All bread, all sausage, all cheeses and all mushrooms.
Mix milk, Worcestershire, mustard, eggs, salt and pepper together and pour over four layers. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Very good served with blueberry muffins and fresh fruit salad.

title: maryland style crab soup
directions: In a big soup pot, put beef bone, V-8 juice, water and 1 pound crab meat.
Add seasonings, green pepper, onion and celery. Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add potatoes and frozen mixed vegetables.
Cook until potatoes are tender, 20 to 30 minutes. Wait until a half hour before serving time to add the last pound of crab meat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: First boil your chicken slowly until done.
Cool and debone. Then mix your soup, chicken and sour cream together.
In a baking pan, lay a layer of crackers, then a layer of mixture.
Repeat until mixture is gone.
Top with crackers then pour cup of chicken broth on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: moist chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs and soup mix in a large plastic bag. Brush chicken on all sides with real mayonnaise.
Place chicken, 1 piece at a time, in bag; shake to coat well.
Arrange on rack in broiler pan.
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 minutes or until tender and brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix in blender and store in refrigerator.

title: macaroni saute
directions: Saute macaroni, onion, green pepper and garlic in hot oil until macaroni turns slightly yellow.
Add tomato juice and seasonings; bring to boiling.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: easy chicken and rice casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in casserole dish, approximately 10 x 10-inch.
Sprinkle rice evenly in bottom of dish.
(Rice can be boiled for a few minutes before putting in casserole dish to assure tenderness.)
Salt and pepper chicken pieces to taste and place over rice.
Mix water with soups; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350°, covered.
Remove cover and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: butter syrup(for pancakes or waffles)
directions: Cook just until mixture thickens, then add 1/2 teaspoon maple flavoring.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Toss chicken with 1 1/2 teaspoons soy sauce; set aside. Combine bouillon with cornstarch and remaining soy sauce; mix well.
Prepare vegetables.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix flour, meal, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Mix egg, milk, onion, oil and squash.
Stir squash mixture into dry mixture.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into deep, hot fat heated to 360°.
Fry 5 to 6 fritters each time.
Drain on paper towel. Serve hot.

title: hot chocolate with a kick
directions: Heat milk in saucepan over low heat.
Add chocolate syrup. Mix well.
Add Kahlua to taste.
Serve warm.

title: sugar-free jello pie
directions: Mix milk in bowl with Jell-O and pudding.
Add Cool Whip. Beat 1 or 2 minutes.
Spoon over crust.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: bran bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and let stand for a few minutes. Dissolve yeast in 1/4 or 1/3 cup warm water with 1 teaspoon sugar. Beat eggs and add to first mixture with cold water.
Add flour to make stiff bread dough.
Let rise.
Punch down.
Let rise again. Punch down and make into loaves.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Can turn back to 375°.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Boil in salted water until tender; drain.
Place potatoes in long casserole dish and pour 1/2 bottle of Italian dressing to coat all of potatoes.
Sprinkle onion over top of potatoes.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or until ready to serve.
When ready, add Miracle Whip salad dressing to coat all potatoes well (stir gently).
Finish by slicing eggs over top.
Serve.

title: buckeyes(childrens recipe)
directions: Melt oleo in 2 qt. heavy saucepan.
Add peanut butter and stir until blended.
Remove from heat, pour in powdered sugar and shape into balls.
Refrigerate for one hour.
Melt chocolate over low heat.
Dip chilled balls 3/4 way into chocolate, leaving small circle of ball showing at top.
Place on waxed paper.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken creole
directions: Combine chicken and rice.
Mix into this the stewed tomatoes. Cook over low heat for 10 to 12 minutes.
Toss in the cut celery, onions and green pepper.
Cook over low heat another 10 minutes. Add salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Grease a baking dish and pour mixture into it; liberally cover the top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
If top gets brown, cover with foil.
Serves 6.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar for 2 minutes.
Add other ingredients. Sift flour 4 times.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Bake in Bundt pan or loaf pan.

title: johnny masetti
directions: Saute onion and celery with a little oil.
Add ground beef and cook; drain.
Place layers of beef, noodles and soup (mixed with water) in a 2-quart baking dish.
Season and cover with cheese. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onions and green peppers slowly in Spry until onions are yellow.
Add hamburger and saute until the mixture falls apart. Add tomatoes, rice and seasoning.
Arrange in large casserole; cover and bake in oven at 375° for 45 minutes or until done. Serves 8.

title: meatball dinner
directions: Soften bread in the milk.
Beat the egg and add it.
Mix the ground beef, onion, parsley, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper together. Combine the bread and meat mixture and form into 18 balls.
Brown balls in skillet in 2 tablespoons hot oil.
Drain off excess fat. Add tomato juice, water, carrots, celery and salt.
Cover; simmer 45 minutes.
Serve over rice, if desired.

title: artichoke appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in lightly greased casserole dish. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes. Serve with crackers or thinly sliced French bread.

title: tuna pate
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Can double recipe.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic salt in large skillet. Drain and add tomatoes, beef broth, corn, rice and chili powder. Be sure to dissolve beef cube in 1 1/4 cups water.
Heat until boiling.
Remove from heat; stir and cover.
Ready in 10 minutes. Makes 5 servings.

title: broccoli cauliflower casserole
directions: Put vegetables in a large casserole.
Dot with cheese.
Pour soup over all.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Dot with butter, if desired.
Bake covered at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until butter and cheese start to melt.
Mix well and bake another 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tender ribs
directions: Wash ribs well.
Sprinkle black pepper and meat tenderizer on ribs.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Place in refrigerator for 1 or 2 hours.
When ready, place on grill and sprinkle seasoned salt on them.
Good for in or outdoor cooking.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In large bowl, mix cheese until fluffy.
Gradually mix in milk.
Stir in mashed strawberries and lemon juice.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into crust and freeze 4 hours.
After frozen, top with strawberries.
Serve cold.
Keep refrigerated.

title: broccoli corn casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain and mix in casserole with remaining ingredients, except for cheese. Sprinkle cheese over top of vegetables.
Bake about 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cinnamon pears
directions: Combine water, candies and sugar in pan.
Heat until candy is dissolved.
Add pears.
Remove from fire.
Baste often with syrup until cold.
Put in a jar in refrigerator.

title: cheerio squares
directions: Combine syrup and sugar.
Heat until dissolved.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Fold in Cheerios and mix well.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips and spread over top.
Cool for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal brownies
directions: Heat
oven to 375°. Lightly grease 8-inch square baking pan. Mix oats, flour, sugars, espresso powder, baking soda and salt
in a	bowl.
Stir
in
semi-sweet
chocolate and butter mixture, eggs,
vanilla
and walnuts until well blended. Pour into prepared baking
pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan
on
wire rack
at
least 4 hours. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into squares.

title: cheese strata with ham and broccoli(great for brunch)
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Remove crusts from day old bread.
Cut 12 doughnuts and holes from center of each slice. Tear scraps and place in a greased pan.
Arrange cheese on bread scraps.
Top with a layer of broccoli and then a layer of ham. Arrange bread doughnuts and holes on ham.
In a mixing bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over ingredients in pan; cover and refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
When ready to cook, preheat oven to 325°.
Place pan, uncovered, in a preheated oven. Bake 55 minutes or until custard is set.
Remove from oven.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes to firm before serving.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender or use mixer; blend well. Pour into 2 pie shells and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: peter-paul mound cake
directions: Put all ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Blend for 2 minutes. Then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread batter in pan.
Smooth out.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Remove to rack.
Cool.

title: the best ever cheesecake
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Press into a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg; add pineapple and juice, mix well.
Add flour, soda and nutmeg.
Mix in nuts.
Chill.
Drop by spoonfuls onto lightly greased pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 400° oven.

title: hand soap
directions: Heat oil in large, heavy pot.
Add each ingredient, one at a time, stirring well as each is added to grease.
Stir with a wooden spoon.
While it is cooling, add sugar and scent.
Place in a cardboard box and cut into squares before it becomes too cold.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together
and
bake at 450° for 1 hour or until done.
Makes a 9 x 13-inch pan full.

title: orange punch
directions: Put ice in container first.
Pour softened orange juice and 7-Up over ice.
Add sugar to taste.
Makes 5 gallons.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix beef, rice, onion, basil, salt and pepper.
Shape into small balls.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine apples, sugar, cinnamon and flour and pour into baking dish.
Combine brown sugar, rolled oats, flour and butter and spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat egg yolks and egg white.
Add mixed sugar and flour alternately with milk; add vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie crust and bake.
Meringue may be added if desired.

title: skyline party dip
directions: Spread cream cheese evenly on bottom of 8 x 8 microwavable casserole dish. Sprinkle on diced onions; pour heated chili over onions and cream cheese. Cover with shredded cheese. In conventional oven, heat at 350° for 10 minutes. In microwave oven, heat on High 2 minutes or until cheese is melted. Let stand 5 or 10 minutes. Serve with nacho chips or corn chips.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Gradually stir lemon juice into sweetened condensed milk.
Add egg yolks and stir until well blended.
Pour into chilled crumb crust.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites; beat until almost stiff enough to hold a peak.
Add sugar gradually, beating until stiff. Pile lightly on pie filling.
Bake in slow oven (325°) until lightly browned, about 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Mix together.
Roll out on wax paper sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll up.
Chill in refrigerator, then cut into slices.

title: curried rice
directions: Cook and stir onions in oleo until tender.
Stir in curry powder, salt and pepper.
Stir in hot rice.
Sprinkle with almonds and olives.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour butter into rest of ingredients. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: holiday punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water.
Add orange juice, mixed with 3 cans of water.
Add juice of squeezed lemons and add the pineapple juice.
Add mashed bananas.
Stir well.
Freeze in Cool Whip size containers.
When ready to serve, thaw 30 minutes and mix with 2 liters of ginger ale.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and slice peaches and put in bottom of 8 x 8-inch baking pan that has been coated with nonstick spray.
In medium mixing bowl, lightly beat flour, sugar and milk until just mixed.
Pour over peaches.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes until top is golden brown.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Mix together Cool Whip, sour cream, evaporated milk and powdered sugar.
Then mix together strawberries and strawberry glaze.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Combine cake mix as directed.
Add pecans and coconut.
Pour cake mixture into an oblong cake pan.
Then mix butter, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Drop on top of cake mixture in spoonfuls.
Cook at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: garlic chicken with pasta shells
directions: Warm oil in a large skillet.
Press garlic cloves through garlic press into warm oil.
Add chicken and stir over medium heat to coat with garlic and oil.
Stir in water, tomato paste, soy sauce and lemon juice. Simmer, covered, over low heat about 5 minutes.
Stir once or twice until chicken is cooked through.
Add parsley. Toss with hot shells. Serves 4.
Contains 471 calories and 6.1 grams fat.

title: camp stew
directions: Boil fryer and butt until tender.
Remove all bones; season with salt and pepper.
Combine all ingredients, including broth from meats.
Cook for 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Heat all ingredients in a large saucepan until heated through. Or, place all ingredients in a slow cooker and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water; set aside.
Mix 2 cups water, egg, oil and sugar; add to yeast mixture.
Stir in flour, mixing thoroughly.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: drop dumplings
directions: Stir until smooth and drop in spoonful at a time in boiling broth.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Grease small cake pan.
Put cherries on bottom.
Sprinkle cake mix over.
Pick like a pie crust; drizzle butter over and add nuts.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Garnish with wedges of tomatoes or slices of boiled eggs.

title: party punch
directions: Mix and chill.
Makes 35 to 50 cups.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows, butter and cherries (including juice) in boiler.
Crumble graham crackers.
Add pecans, raisins and nutmeg to cracker crumbs.
Pour liquid ingredients over dry ingredients; mix well.
Press into pan.
Cover with wax paper; put into refrigerator for 24 hours.
Remove from pan and rewrap.
Place back in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar. Add crushed pretzel sticks and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes and cool.

title: velveeta broccoli bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Mix broccoli, cheese and if using meat, already fried together.
Spoon into greased 10 x 6-inch baking dish. Sprinkle crushed crackers on top and dot with margarine. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add salt and milk.
Flavor with vanilla or rum.
Dip bread slices into egg mixture.
Bread may be cut in round shapes with a doughnut cutter.
Brown the bread on each side on a hot, well buttered griddle.
Serve hot, sprinkled with sugar and cinnamon.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a shallow casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Before removing from oven, top with grated Cheddar cheese and allow to melt.

title: pepperoni appetizer
directions: Open package of biscuits and cut the 10 biscuits in halves, making 20 pieces. Stretch the pieces upward and sideways but try not to tear. Place piece of pepperoni in center and sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top of pepperoni. Close by pinching dough together on top and sides. Place in aluminum foil on a cookie sheet. Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes. Should be golden brown.

title: old-fashioned chocolate pudding
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Add milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Add beaten egg yolks, butter and vanilla.
Mix well.

title: beer cheese spread
directions: Grate cheese.
Let soften, then add all ingredients except beer.
Use mixer or blender to mix.
Add beer slowly while mixing, using as much as needed to make spread consistency desired.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs, sugar, margarine and nuts. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and set aside.

title: cheese crescents
directions: Combine cheese, bread crumbs and bacon bits (as desired) over low heat until cheese is melted.
Spoon onto halved triangles of crescent rolls and roll up as directed.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes.

title: norwegian kristen kringles
directions: Cut together flour, butter and water (first 3 ingredients). Make 2 equal strips on cookie sheet 3-inches wide by length of cookie sheet.
Heat 1/2 cup butter with 1 cup water.
Take off heat. Add 1 cup flour.
Beat until clear. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg. Add salt and flavoring.
Spread on pastry crust evenly. Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Frost.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats, cover and let set 20 minutes.
Beat butter until creamy.
Gradually add sugar and beat until fluffy. Blend in vanilla and eggs.
Add oats; mix well.
Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Add creamed mixture; mix well.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Work together and mix thoroughly.
Roll into 1-inch size balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: reese's cups
directions: Put peanut butter in bowl.
Cover with powdered sugar; mix. Cover with graham cracker crumbs; mix.
Keep adding powdered sugar and graham cracker crumbs until tasty.
Add melted butter.
Spread out in pan.
Cover with chocolate (melted Hershey bars).
Put in freezer until chocolate hardens.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: curried pork chops
directions: On waxed paper, combine flour, curry powder, salt and pepper. Coat both sides of pork chops.
In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot oil, cook pork chops 7 to 8 minutes until tender and golden brown on both sides.

title: dad's most excellent barbecue sauce
directions: Melt margarine.
Add the remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Baste meat -- best for chicken -- good on burgers, too.

title: dark banana bread
directions: Beat together egg and sugar.
Add shortening, bananas, flour, baking soda and salt (walnuts).
Bake at 300° for 1 hour in loaf pan (greased).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken and 1/2 cup celery soup together.
Spread over chicken.
Cover with sage and onion croutons.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: trulie's brownie cupcakes
directions: Combine sugar, flour and eggs. Blend, do not beat.
Melt butter and chocolate in a saucepan.
Add nuts and stir.
Combine the two mixtures.
Add vanilla.
Blend only to mix well. Pour into 24 paper-lined muffin tins.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Yields 24 cupcakes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off grease.
Mix in a baking dish with Spanish rice, tomato sauce and 1 can water.
Mix well.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven about 45 minutes or until thickened.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Let first 3 ingredients above stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Then whip the cream cheese until smooth and fluffy.
Then blend together with all the ingredients, except eggs.
With electric mixer, beat each egg individually into batter.

title: diet salad
directions: *If oranges are sweetened, drain and rinse off in water and then cut in small pieces.

title: strawberry satin
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill, then serve.

title: cracklin' bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and sugar into corn meal in large bowl.
Mix well.
Mix eggs, corn, milk and cracklins.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan that has been greased.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 9 x 12-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Put coconut and pecans on bottom of pan.
Make cake according to directions. Pour over coconut and pecans.
In separate bowl, mix margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Drop by spoonfuls over cake. This sinks into cake.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and flour.
Add melted butter, buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 425° for 10 minutes and at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: chinese hamburger
directions: Brown meat in 2 tablespoons oil oil until crumbly.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Put in a greased casserole and bake, covered, for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 30 minutes more. Spread one can of Chinese noodles over top.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: extra moist coconut cake
directions: Mix sugar, sour cream and coconut and let set in refrigerator until sugar is dissolved (2 or 3 hours), stirring occasionally. Bake cake as directed on box in 2 round cake pans.
Cool.

title: baked apples
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and coat by mixing in Tupperware with lid.
Melt the butter and apple juice in microwave.
Pour on top and cover loosely with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook noodles until slightly crunchy.
Rinse cold water.
Melt butter and put 1/2 aside.
Heat 1/2 cream and 1/2 butter until bubbly.
Add noodles and parsley.
Toss until cream starts to cook off.
Add rest of butter and cream, then as you toss add as much cheese as desired.
Add salt and pepper if desired.

title: pumpkin trifle
directions: Set aside 1/4 to 1/2 cup cake crumbs for garnish.
Divide remaining crumbs into 4 portions.
Sprinkle 1 portion into bottom of trifle bowl or 3-quart serving bowl.
In mixing bowl, combine pumpkin, spices, milk and pudding; mix until smooth.
Spoon half into trifle bowl over cake crumbs.
Layer with second portion of cake crumbs.
Whip cream until stiff.
Spoon half over cake crumbs.
Sprinkle third portion of crumbs.
Top with remaining pumpkin mixture; then last portion of crumbs and remaining whipped cream.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top.
Garnish with cherries. Cover and chill.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, corn syrup and salt in a microwavable bowl.
Cook on High in the microwave until it boils or about 4 minutes.
Stir three times and add baking soda and vanilla.
Place popcorn in a grocery sack and pour ingredients of bowl into the sack.
Stir with a wooden spoon.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes on High in the microwave.
Add peanuts (optional).
Cook for last time for 15 seconds.

title: peppermint patties
directions: Follow directions for Orange Blossoms, substituting extract for orange juice.
Instead of making the spoonfuls of fluff peak, using back of spoon, flatten into patties.
This recipe makes 40 patties.
May be had anytime, equals all the milk for the day and all the extract freebie.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix in bowl, sugar and flour.
Set aside. Bring to a rapid boil, 1 stick of butter, vegetable oil, water and 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture; blend well.
Stir in eggs, 1 teaspoon vanilla, cinnamon, soda and buttermilk.
Pour batter on cookie sheet (I use a 13 x 9-inch cake pan).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Take 1 stick butter, milk and 4 tablespoons cocoa and bring to a rapid boil.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla, powdered sugar and nuts.
Pour over cake as soon as removed from oven and spread to cover entire cake.

title: sweet surprise
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick melted butter.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 3-inch dish.
Chill.
In a large bowl, mix 2 sticks butter, confectioners sugar and eggs.
Beat for 15 minutes. Spread on top of graham cracker crumbs.
Drain pineapple and sprinkle on top.
Place sliced bananas over pineapple.
Spoon Cool Whip over bananas.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Arrange cherries as garnish.

title: apple rolls
directions: Mix flour, shortening and milk to make stiff.
Chill 5 to 6 hours.
In saucepan let water, margarine, sugar and vanilla get hot.
Roll chilled pastry thin and add apples, brown sugar, cinnamon.
Roll up into long roll.
Slice 1 1/2 inches thick.
Add this to the top mixture.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs and place in baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes. Cook onion in fat until done.
Add lemon juice, brown sugar, chili sauce, water, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over ribs.
Bake one hour longer in moderate oven.

title: savory tomato soup
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, melt butter and cook onion and carrot until soft.
Stir in flour and cook for 1 minute.
Slowly stir in the bouillon.
Add tomatoes, juice and salt.
Bring to the boil and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.
Puree the soup in a processor or with a stick blender for a smooth texture.
Stir in the vanilla.
Serve hot with dill weed or basil, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: potage pea soup
directions: Defrost peas to room temperature.
Reserve 1/2 cup of peas for garnish.
In small saucepan, combine remaining peas with water, salt, sugar and pepper.
Bring to vigorous boil over high heat. Cover, lower heat to medium and cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Strain liquid and reserve.
Cool peas and place in blender with chicken broth.
Cover and blend on high speed for 1 minute.
Add to saucepan with cooking liquid and bring to a boil.
Stir in butter with wire whisk.
Taste and correct seasonings.
Before serving, add 2 or 3 tablespoons of soup to cream.
Garnish with uncooked peas.

title: pickled squash
directions: Mix squash, onions, bell pepper and salt.
Let set 3 hours. Mix remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Drain squash and add to vinegar mixture.
Bring to a hard boil, then put in hot jars and seal.

title: chleb wiejski (country-style bread)(origin: polish)
directions: Measure flour.
In bowl, mix 1/3 of that amount with 1 cup lukewarm water and set aside in warm place to ferment 24 hours.

title: broccoli salad(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Chop cauliflower and broccoli.
Add grated cheese.
When ready to serve, toss with dressing.

title: 7-up sunshine pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix and 1/4 cup 7-Up in saucepan.
Blend in 2 egg yolks; add rest of 7-Up, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice, lemon rind and cream cheese, beating until smooth.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold into lemon mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill until set.
Garnish with lemon slices and mint leaves, if desired.

title: creamy salad
directions: Dissolve marshmallows in Jell-O and water.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Let harden in refrigerator.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Beat eggs until foamy and add next 4 ingredients.
Mix together.
Add flour mixture (flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon).
Blend with mix and stir in nuts and raisins (optional).
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: pancake syrup
directions: In a small pan, dissolve sugar in water.
Add salt and cinnamon; boil 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve warm or cold.

title: famous austrian chicken soup
directions: Put the first five ingredients in a soup pot; add enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil; lower heat and cook for 1 to 2 hours. Remove chicken from pot and place in a bowl to cool; set aside. Puree in a blender the remaining broth and cooked vegetables.
Add to taste Parmesan cheese, garlic, salt and pepper.
Remove chicken from bones and cut into bite-size pieces; add to pureed broth.
In separate saucepans, cook the pasta, corn and potatoes.

title: peachy cream cheese
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Add sweetened condensed milk; blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and extract.
Spread about 1/3 of the filling on bottom of crust.
Reserving several slices for garnish, arrange peaches on filling and around edge of crust.
Top with remaining filling and garnish with reserved peaches. Chill 2 hours.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: chili dip
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave.
Add chili and chilies.
Mix well.
Return to microwave.
Microwave for 2 minutes.
Add cheese and microwave for 1 minute.
Serve warm.

title: praline squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lay out crackers, side by side, in ungreased 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Put butter and brown sugar in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat and cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.
Stir in nuts; mix well.

title: hershey's doubly chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; add to butter mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by round teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: orange pop salad
directions: Boil 1 cup orange pop.
Mix with jello.
Stir until dissolved. Add rest of pop.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
With mixer on low speed, mix with Cool Whip.
Add oranges.
Pour in serving dish or mold.
Chill until set.
(Can use diet jello and pop.)

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown meat,
onion and salt in nonstick pan or use Pam. When brown,
add
potatoes
and carrots.
Cover with water and simmer until
vegetables
are
done.
Add	tomato	soup, more water, barley,
can
of
vegetables,
corn and picante sauce. Heat until hot and barley is done.
Serve with cornbread.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order by hand.
The mixture will be thick. Pour into a greased tube or Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 hour and 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Remove from pan.
No icing is needed.
Freezes good.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spread coconut and nuts on top of butter.
Pour in cake mixture.

title: terri's pure dee pumpkin pie
directions: Combine
eggs,	sugars,
salt and spices in mixing bowl with mixer
on
medium speed.
Add milk, vanilla and pumpkin. Pour into pie
shell
and
bake
in 450° oven for 10 minutes. Turn down to 350° and bake for 40 additional minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: In a paper bag, shake tomatoes in corn meal until coated. Heat oil in a skillet.
Fry tomatoes quickly until meal is golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.

title: no fat poppy seed dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a jar.
Cover and shake until blended. Dressing keeps several days in refrigerator.

title: skillet au vin
directions: Mix flour, salt, and pepper.
Coat chicken.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon.
Add chicken to bacon fat.
Brown on each side.
Drain fat.
Add thyme, bay leaves, vegetables, chicken broth, and wine.
Cover.
Simmer until all is tender.
Do not over cook.
To serve, crumble reserved bacon over top.
Serve in shallow bowls with hot French bread.

title: peachy salad dressing
directions: Combine peach and 1/4 cup buttermilk in blender, whirl until pureed.
Add remaining buttermilk, vinegar, honey, salt and sugar. Whirl to blend.
Scrape the dressing from the blender.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Use it for green salad or fruit salad.

title: boneless chicken breasts(italian style)
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Spread with crushed garlic and flour.
Saute in oil and butter until light brown. Place in shallow casserole and sprinkle with tarragon.
