Add broth to skillet and heat while scraping brown particles from bottom of pan. Add wine and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake 20 minutes; add cheese 5 minutes before serving and bake, uncovered, until cheese melts.

title: virginia chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together.
Add other ingredients, one at a time, except alternate additions of flour and syrup (beat after each addition).
Bake in greased and floured rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: beef and vegetable stew
directions: Place the potatoes, carrots and onions in a large slow cooker. In a large skillet, brown beef in oil, a single layer at a time. Place over the vegetables.
Sprinkle with flour.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Stir in vinegar, ketchup, mustard and sugar; pour over meat and vegetables.
Cover and cook on high for 5 hours.
Add peas, corn and mushrooms.
Cover and cook on high for 45 minutes longer.
This is great to put on in the morning and have ready for dinner.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Put all ingredients together; bring to a boil on top of the stove.
Reduce to simmer for 20 minutes, or until rice is soft. Serves 8.

title: easy vegetable stew
directions: Saute onion in water until transparent.
Add potatoes and carrots and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add chopped tomatoes and seasoning.
Cover and simmer for about 1 hour. Add string beans and cook for 25 minutes more.

title: cheese-cornmeal biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Briskly mix cornmeal into hot milk. Cover and set aside.

title: low-fat devil's food cookies
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar and beat at medium speed of electric mixer until blended.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and egg whites; beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart onto cookie sheets coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: quickie pie
directions: Put butter in pan and melt. Mix other ingredients together and pour in pan, then put fruit and bake at 300° until crust rises and is brown.

title: plain pound cake
directions: With electric mixer, cream Crisco.
Add sugar until well mixed.
Add one egg at a time, beating after each one.
By hand, fold in flour.
Add vanilla.
Pour in well-greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Allow cake to cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Form into ball and chill.
Cover with chopped nuts.

title: orange fruit jello
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water and lemon juice. Chill until partially thickened.
Fold in chopped bananas, marshmallows and pineapple.
Chill until firm.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Add peanut butter and vanilla and mix well.
Roll batter into small balls and refrigerate several hours.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in top of double boiler.
Using toothpick, dip each ball into melted chocolate and allow to cool on baking sheet.
Store in covered container.
Can be frozen.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs; add ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour into electric freezer container.
Freeze.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place the pie filling on the bottom of an 8 or 9-inch baking dish.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast in warm water.
In medium size bowl, break the egg and beat well.
Add buttermilk, sugar, soda and oil; add yeast and mix well.
Add this mixture to the flour and blend thoroughly.
If not stiff enough (like biscuit dough) add flour sparingly.
If too stiff, add small amount of buttermilk.
Let stand until double in size.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
When dough has risen, take 1/3 of dough and roll out in rectangular shape, about 6 to 8 inches wide, 12 inches long.
Pour melted oleo over dough and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up narrow side.
Cut circular roll in 1-inch slices.
Place slices side by side in pie pans (makes 6 pans).
Let rise double in size; bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Ice while rolls are warm.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa; remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and beaten eggs.
Add flour, salt, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spoon batter into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows over hot cake.
Frost cake.

title: sweet potato pudding(diabetic)
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to mix well.
Pour into well-greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until set and top is lightly browned. Yields 10 servings.
Exchange, serving equals 1 bread, 1/2 high-fat meat.
Calories:

title: chicken a la king
directions: Saute mushrooms and bell pepper in butter.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat, slowly stir in broth and cream. Add chicken and pimiento.
Continue cooking until meat is heated through.
Serve over biscuits, chow mein noodles, or pastry shells.
Serves 4.

title: norwegian pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Lightly grease pan.
Heat pan to medium and pour about 1/4 cup batter.
Rotate pan until batter covers bottom.
Brown - Flip - Brown.
Makes 12 pancakes.

title: small cakes (cookies) for christmas
directions: Cream sugar and butter, then eggs.
Add other ingredients. Mix well.
Chill, then roll out on floured board into a thin layer.
Use cookie cutters to make desired shapes.
Bake at 400° until just lightly browned, about 7 minutes.
Sprinkle with colored sugar before baking or spread with icing when cool or good just so.

title: one-dish pork chops with rice
directions: Heat oil in a skillet that can go into the oven.
Add onions, green peppers and rice.
Saute until rice is translucent.
Add sugar and tomatoes; blend.

title: pinto beans and ground meat
directions: Cook beans until done.
Cook meat until light brown.
Drain off grease.
Add to beans.
Put tomatoes in bowl and chop up.
Add to beans.
Cook about 30 or 40 minutes on low heat.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Put rhubarb in greased 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle with sugar and jello. Spread with marshmallows next. Prepare cake mix as directed and spread over marshmallows evenly. Bake at 350° about 55 minutes. Cool for 5 minutes and turn pan upside down on serving tray. Serve warm with whip cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: ketchup
directions: Cook to desired consistency.
Immediately place in canning jars and seal.
Makes about 7 pints.

title: step-by-step fried chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper. Place chicken in a shallow dish or zip-top plastic bag and add buttermilk. Cover and chill at least 2 hours. Remove chicken from buttermilk, discarding buttermilk. Dredge chicken in flour. Pour oil to a depth of 1 1/2-inches in a deep skillet or Dutch oven and heat to 360°. Add chicken a few pieces at a time; cover and cook 6 minutes. Uncover chicken and cook 9 minutes. Turn chicken; cover and cook 6 minutes. Uncover and cook 5 to 9 minutes, turning chicken the last 3 minutes for even browning, if necessary. Drain on paper towels.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs and add all ingredients. Grease and flour Bundt pan; fold in mixture.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: sweet and hot and spicy pickles
directions: Drain pickles and slice.
Put back in jar.
Add sugar, garlic and Tabasco sauce.
Seal jar real well.
Leave out 4 days, turning often (up or upside down).
On fifth day, put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: delmonico potatoes(10 to 15 servings)
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on.
After the potatoes have boiled 15 minutes, cool slightly, then peel and grate.
Place into 3-quart baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.

title: egg-sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Crumble and drain.
Mix cheese and sausage.
Place in pie shell.
Beat eggs and combine remaining ingredients.
Add to egg mixture.
Pour in shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes.

title: oven baked french toast
directions: Brown sausage; drain and set aside.
Butter bread on one side. Place one layer of bread in a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan, buttered side down.
Spoon sausage over first layer of bread. Place second layer of bread over sausage.
Mix together eggs, milk, sugar, salt and cinnamon; pour over bread.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes, or until set.
Serve with syrup.

title: overnight salad
directions: Combine mushrooms, celery, carrots, broccoli, cauliflower and olives in a medium size bowl.
Combine vinegar, oil, onion, garlic, basil, oregano and honey in a small saucepan; bring to boiling.
Pour hot marinade over vegetables in bowl; stir gently but thoroughly.
Cover; refrigerate overnight, stirring several times, if possible.
Drain vegetables before serving.

title: sugar cookie hearts
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with sour cream, mixing well after each addition.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill until firm enough to roll.
Roll on lightly floured surface to about 1/2-inch thickness; cut with floured cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Sprinkle with plain or colored sugar.
Bake in preheated 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until cookies are lightly browned.
Place on wire rack to cool. Makes 6 dozen.

title: "souperior" meat loaf and sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, combine all ingredients. In large shallow baking pan, shape mixture into loaf. Bake 1 hour or until done. Serves 8.

title: hamburger and macaroni
directions: Brown hamburger with onions; add tomatoes.
Mix 1/4 cup milk with macaroni; add to hamburger mixture.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Heat 1 quart of milk while mixing eggs, cornstarch and sugar. Stir mixture into milk and cook until it comes to a boil.
Add vanilla and pint of cream.
Pour all into 6-quart freezer can and pour the rest of the milk in freezer can to the fill line.
Freeze in electric freezer.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken with onion, celery and salt (optional) until tender.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Place broccoli in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cut chicken in small pieces and place over broccoli. Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle grated cheese over soup mixture.
Crush Ritz crackers and sprinkle over cheese to make thin crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fried green beans
directions: Drain green beans well.
Add to medium hot skillet with the Crisco.
Sprinkle flour
over
top of beans.
Add salt and pepper. Turn
easy,
so as to not break beans.
Let flour get brown and crisp
over
beans.
Fry only until beans and flour are hot and most of flour is brown.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In saucepan melt butter.
Remove from heat; blend in flour and salt.
Add milk; heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens a little and is smooth.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese; heat until melted, stirring occasionally.
Meanwhile, cook macaroni as directed; drain.
Combine with sauce in a 2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese, bread crumbs and paprika.
Bake at 375° about 20 to 25 minutes or until nicely browned and bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: prune tarts
directions: Combine prunes, lemon juice, water and sugar in a small saucepan. Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until water is almost entirely evaporated and absorbed by the prunes.
Transfer mixture into work bowl of food processor with steel blade in place or into blender container.
Process until pureed.
Set aside. Roll out each puff pastry sheet to about 10 x 18-inch rectangle.
Spread each sheet lengthwise with half the prune mixture. Fold pastry over prune mixture.
Cut each sheet into 6 pastries that are 3-inches wide. Place on greased baking sheet.
Mix egg and milk. Brush tops of pastries with mixture. Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan. Make sauce of soups, milk, olives and chilies. Cut tortillas into 3/4-inch strips. Make layers of sauce, chicken, tortillas and Monterey Jack cheese. Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly. Best if made in morning or day before and refrigerated until ready to cook.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, 1 stick melted butter, onion, cheese, soup and sour cream.
Put in greased 9 x 13 inch glass baking dish.
Mix remaining 1/2 stick melted butter and cornflakes.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: granny cake
directions: Mix together and add one large can of pineapple.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup brown sugar on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.

Then add eggs and mix until creamy. Sift the two flours together and alternately add the milk and flour to the creamed mixture, mixing well between two additions. Add flavoring. Bake in tube pan about 1 hour at 325°.
Test to see if cake is done.

title: grandma jessie musselman's banana cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in lightly greased cake pan at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: harvest bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, potatoes and orange juice.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake in 4 greased and floured 1 pound coffee cans.
Do not use pans, bread will not turn out right. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield: 4 cakes.

title: wild rice-pecan casserole
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet; add mushrooms, onion, green pepper, and garlic. Cook 5 minutes. Add pecans; cook 1 minute. Rinse and drain rice; mix rice into the mushroom mixture; add broth. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Pour into a well-greased 2 qt. casserole dish; cover and bake in preheated oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix and bake in buttered and sugared tube pan at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: easter cake
directions: Cut pepperoni and cheese into small pieces.
Beat eggs, then add flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix well, then stir in pepperoni and cheese. Pour into flat baking pan lined with aluminum foil.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Reduce temperature to 325° and bake an additional 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream first 2 ingredients.
Add next 2 ingredients.
Blend well and add pumpkin.
Sift together remaining ingredients. Blend into mixture and drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top for decoration.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add to batter alternating flour and buttermilk; add extract.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: vegetable strata supreme
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Arrange frozen vegetables in bottom of greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread cubes and ham. In medium bowl, combine milk, eggs, mustard, garlic powder and onion powder.
Beat well.
Pour egg mixture over bread cubes and ham.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.

title: linguine salad
directions: Break linguine in half and cook about 10 minutes in boiling water.
Rinse and drain well. Mix with dressing and seasoning. Add diced vegetables and olives. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: oatmeal crisp cookies
directions: Melt together butter and water.
Add syrup.
Sift together flour, sugar, soda and baking powder; add to butter ingredients. Chill.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased sheet and flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: texas apple pie
directions: Prepare pie crust for 2 pies.
Roll out 1/2 the pastry and place in a 9-inch pie plate.
Combine all the ingredients, except apples, in bowl and mix well.
Peel and core apples.
Slice apples and arrange in unbaked crust.
Pour batter over apples. Cover with top crust and seal edges.
Brush with brown sugar glaze, consisting of 1 tablespoon evaporated milk and 1 tablespoon brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan pound cake
directions: Stir flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter and sugar; beat until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla and eggs, one at a time; beat 1 minute after each egg.
Blend in dry ingredients and stir in nuts.
Bake in 9 x 5 x 3-inch dish at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Shred cabbage and cook in a small amount of water with the green peppers and celery, about 5 minutes in a Dutch oven on top of stove.
Cook garlic in melted butter.
Mix the garlic butter mixture in with the vegetables; also stir in the milk, cheese, salt and pepper.
After mixing, spoon into a 2-quart baking dish.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 300° about 30 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cereal cookies
directions: Mix in order given (shortening, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and flour, first; then soda, salt, vanilla, oatmeal and cornflakes, second).
Form into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and press flat with tines of fork.
Bake in moderate oven on lightly greased cookie sheet.

title: tuna blushing bunny
directions: Fifteen minutes before serving, split and toast English muffins.
In medium saucepan, with spoon or wire whisk, stir undiluted soups, Worcestershire, mustard and tuna.
Heat until well mixed.
Spoon over toasted muffins.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Cut pork chops long ways through middle so as to make them 1/4-inch thick.
Keep each chop slightly together by not cutting completely apart, but go very close to edge.
(Most butterfly chops are sliced down middle so this will be a 2 part experience for each chop.)
Mix stuffing according to instructions for convection oven cooking except add 1/2 of juice from peaches in place of an equal amount of water.
Place 1/2 of stuffing on bottom of lightly greased baking dish.

title: fresh coconut cake frosting
directions: Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Chop onions and pepper.
Saute in oleo until transparent.
Add ground beef or chuck; cook, but do not brown.
Combine with beef and onions all other ingredients, except cheese and corn chips. Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish at least 2-inches deep.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (15 to 18 minutes in microwave and covered).
Add cheese and corn chips.
Place in oven again until cheese has melted well.
Can run under broiler to brown.

title: fast apple crisp
directions: Dice apples and put into buttered dish.
Add water to apples and sprinkle some cinnamon on top.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly; put on top of apples.
Bake 35 minutes at 400°. Other fruit may also be used.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place in 9 x 13 casserole dish.
Melt the oleo and mix with crackers.
Spread on vegetable mixture and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate drop fudge
directions: Melt candy in microwave.
Add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Cook in microwave until the mixture boils.
Stir.
Cook 1 more time until it boils.
Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Let cool.

title: egg dumplings - hard
directions: Drop by teaspoonfuls into boiling liquid.

title: ham and swiss mini sandwiches
directions: Combine margarine, mustard, poppy seed, onion and Worcestershire.
Take rolls out of pan carefully; slice through (keeping attached).
Put the bottom back in the pan.
Spread both top and bottom halves with margarine mixture.
Sprinkle ham and cheese on roll (bottom half).
Put top half back on.

title: pepperoni pizza sticks
directions: Place breadsticks in single layer on baking sheets. Top each with 5 slices of pepperoni and 1 tablespoon shredded cheese. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until cooked through. Serve breadsticks with warm pizza sauce, for dipping.

title: partridge in red wine
directions: Combine flour and 1 teaspoon salt in paper or plastic bag.
Add 2 or 3 pieces partridge at a time and shake to coat.
Brown partridge pieces in butter in Dutch oven.
Add onion and beef broth.
Cook, covered, over low heat 50 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Remove birds to warm serving dish.
Add wine to Dutch oven and simmer 5 minutes, stirring and scraping brown bits from bottom of pan.
Pour sauce over partridge.
Makes 2 or 3 servings.

title: cheese vegetable soup
directions: Whisk Half and Half into can of soup in a large pot or crock-pot.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Cube Velveeta into large cubes and add to soup.
Cook over low heat.
Put frozen vegetables in a little water in microwave for 5 to 8 minutes.
Drain.
Add to soup.
Cook on stove for 30 to 45 minutes at low heat, stirring frequently or on low in crock-pot all day.

title: key lime pie
directions: Boil 1/3 cup of water; blend in jello.
Add Key lime yogurt. Blend in Cool Whip. Pour into pie shell. Refrigerate overnight and serve.

title: lemon ice cream sandwiches
directions: Line pan with graham crackers.
Mix pudding mix on low until thickened.
Chill about 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread mix over graham crackers.
Top with graham crackers.
Freeze until firm.
Wrap in individual sandwiches.
Keep frozen.

title: cherry salad
directions: Stir jello and water together.
Let set until it starts to thicken.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator until thick.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix
apples,
tablespoons
sugar
and
cinnamon; set aside. Beat
eggs;
add sugar, vanilla, orange juice and oil. Mix
well, then add all dry ingredients, mixing well.
Grease and
flour tube pan.
Add batter, then apples and finish with batter.	Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: For sauce, saute onion in butter.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Place a layer of sliced potatoes in greased 1 qt. casserole dish.
Add a layer of sauce and a layer of cheese.
Repeat until all sauce is used.
End with cheese on top. Bake 25 min. uncovered.
Check for tenderness, may need to cook longer.

title: rise-n-shine shake
directions: Blend well until smooth.

title: country ham muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in muffin tins at 350° until lightly browned.

title: abe lincoln favorite nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and creamy.
Sift flour, baking powder,
and salt 3 times, then add to butter and sugar, vanilla with milk.
Then after you have this well beaten, add 1 cup of Hickory nuts chopped fine.
I usually put about half of the nuts in the blender and make them real fine; other half I chop. Last fold in beaten egg whites, beat egg whites till stand in peaks before you fold them in.
Bake in long pan or 3 - 8 inch pans at 350 degrees until it leaves the pans or until it springs back when touched in center.

title: frogmore stew
directions: In a 5-quart stockpot, bring water and potatoes to a boil.
Add corn and lower heat.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add sausage and seasonings and cook another 20 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook on medium heat 3 minutes or until all shrimp are pink.
Spread newspapers.
Drain off water and dump on papers.

title: whole wheat muffins(from the tassajara cookbook)
directions: Combine dry ingredients and sift.
Combine wet ingredients. Fold quickly together, just until flour is moistened.
Add raisins, dates, etc., if desired.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: frozen passion pops
directions: Pour sweetened condensed milk into a bowl.
Add the soda pop, then add the lemon juice. Stir.
Freeze mixture in popsicle molds or paper cups with popsicle sticks. Store any leftover mixture in the refrigerator for the next batch of passion pops.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients in casserole dish.
Top with chips.
Cover with chopped or sliced eggs.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: mexican cheese dip(microwave)
directions: Microwave peppers and onion in margarine on High until tender (2 to 3 minutes).
Add Velveeta and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Stir. Microwave on Medium until smooth, approximately 8 or 9 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown the meat and onion. Salt and pepper.
Heat the oil and heat tortillas.
Put meat and cheese in tortilla and roll up. Place in pan.
Pour chili over top and cover with cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts and warmed through.

title: brownies
directions: In a saucepan, melt margarine.
Then slowly add flour and cocoa; mix well.
Remove from heat and add remainder of ingredients.

title: spaghettini with seafood and sundried tomatoes
directions: Cook pasta until al dente.
Drain and rinse.
Toss with olive oil.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Add garlic and saute 3 minutes.
Turn heat to medium-high, add shrimp and scallops; saute 3 minutes.
Add clam juice and pasta to skillet.
Increase heat to high.
Cook until pasta absorbs liquid and is hot.
Add tomatoes, parsley and lemon; toss gently.
Season and salt.

title: chile rellenos casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a casserole.
One with center hole is preferable.
Microwave for 10 minutes, turning dish every 3 minutes and stirring from sides after 5 minutes. Serves 6.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Cut margarine into flour.
Add buttermilk, stirring well. Turn onto a lightly floured surface and knead lightly 3 to 4 times.
Roll to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter. Bake at 325° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Brush with melted butter.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix thoroughly the first 10 ingredients and refrigerate 2 hours.
Shape mixture by rounded tablespoonfuls into balls.
In large skillet, slowly brown meatballs in oil.
Remove from skillet and keep warm.

title: darla's texas hash
directions: Brown meat with onion and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and let simmer about 15 minutes.
Spread mixture over bread and top with slice of cheese.
Bake in 350° oven on cookie sheet for 10 to 15 minutes, or until cheese is melted.

title: maritata soup
directions: Bring broth to a boil.
Add noodles (broken) and cook 5 to 8 minutes.
In bowl, blend butter, Parmesan cheese and egg yolks with heavy cream.
Spoon a small amount of hot broth into cream mixture, stirring constantly.
Add to broth and remove from heat. Serve immediately.

title: miss sissy crooms cabbage casserole
directions: Make a white sauce of the milk, flour, butter, salt and black pepper.
Boil cabbage in salt water until tender.
Place cabbage in	casserole
dish.
Cover
with
white sauce and add onion rings and cheese.
Bake until bubbly.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry for 2-crust pie.
Stir together sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Mix lightly with apples.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Dot with butter. Cover with top crust and cut slits.
Seal and flute.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until crust is brown and juices bubble through slits.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: In small saucepan, heat first 3 ingredients until very warm (120° to 130°).
In large bowl, blend warm liquid, flour; salt and yeast at low speed until moistened.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.

By hand stir in whole wheat flour to form a stiff dough. Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes. Place dough in greased bowl; let rise in warm place until light and double in size; 45 to 60 minutes.
Generously grease 2 loaf pans. Punch down dough, divide and shape into 2 loaves.
Cover; let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until deep golden brown and loaves sound hollow when lightly tapped.
Immediately remove from pans; cool.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Pound chicken breasts until 1/4-inch thick.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top each piece of chicken with 1 slice of ham and 1 slice of cheese.
Fold chicken over ham and cheese.
Wrap each bundle with a slice of bacon.
Place bundles in a shallow baking dish and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Mix soda and buttermilk and then dissolve sugar.
Use a big saucepan and boil slowly to soft ball stage, 234°.
Mixture turns brown as it cooks, but stir constantly to prevent scorching. Remove from fire and add vanilla, oleo and pecans.
Stir until it begins to look like it is ready to cream.
Drop in small cakes on waxed paper.
Makes about 30 pralines.

title: party cheese krispies
directions: Mix all thoroughly.
Form into small balls.
Flatten slightly with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: pommes de terre fondantes(potatoes)
directions: Put potatoes in a kettle.
Add water to cover and salt.
Bring to boil; cook about 3 minutes.
Drain.
Heat oil in a saucepan large enough to hold the potatoes in one layer.
Add potatoes. Cover and cook, turning often, until potatoes are golden brown on all sides, about 5 minutes.
Pour off fat.
Add broth.
Cover closely and cook over moderately low heat, about 10 minutes.
Add butter and stir.
Uncover and cook until all liquid is evaporated from the pan.
Yields 4 servings.

title: tropical fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Allow to set and thicken, then serve.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Beat eggs and oleo; add cake mix, chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: brown sugar crisps
directions: Beat sugar, shortening, egg, vanilla, allspice and cinnamon until smooth and creamy.
Stir in baking mix and nuts.
Drop dough by slightly rounded spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Bake until light brown, for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Fry ground turkey.
Add celery, green pepper, onions, salt and pepper.
Add can of soup.
Heat through.
Pour into casserole and cover with a layer of sliced cheese, and a layer of Tater Tots. Bake at 350° until potatoes are golden brown and casserole is bubbly.

title: tuna burgers(club member: christy hosey)
directions: Combine ingredients for filling. Salt and pepper to taste. Butter inside of rolls. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/3 cup juice and set aside.
In a small bowl, combine broth, soy sauce, vinegar, sugar, cornstarch, pepper and reserved pineapple juice.
Set aside.
In a wok or large skillet, heat oil until hot.
Add celery, red peppers, green peppers and garlic.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Add pork, cook and stir until pork turns white, about 2 minutes.
Stir in reserved cornstarch mixture and pineapple chunks.
Cook and stir until it thickens and boils, about 1 minute.
Serve over steamed unconverted rice.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat, peppers, onions and mushrooms.
Layer noodles in pan with meat sauce and cheeses.
Repeat.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, oleo and chocolate chips (chocolate chips will look glossy, but will be melted).

title: huevos rancheros
directions: In a pan, put sauce and onion to heat, then put tortillas in hot oil and let them fry.
Put tortillas on a plate, then make sunny side up eggs; put them on top of tortillas.
Put picante or tomato sauce on top, then add cheese.

title: pecan sandies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream together butter and 3/4 cup of the sugar with electric beater.
Add vanilla, flour, pecans and salt.
Beat until well blended.
Wrap dough in plastic wrap and chill for 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Scoop up dough with a teaspoon and form into balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake about 15 minutes until cookies are slightly colored, but not golden.
Remove from cookie sheet, then roll in rest of the sugar.

title: blue cheese dip
directions: Grate cheese and mix all ingredients together; chill.

title: magic meat balls
directions: Combine ingredients in bowl.
Make small 1-inch meatballs. Place in baking dish; set aside.

title: cherry pecan bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine the flour, baking soda and salt; add to the creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in pecans, cherries and vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan to a wire rack.
Yield: 1 loaf.

title: swiss and crab quiche
directions: Put cheese on bottom of pie shell.
Top with crab, then add onions.
Combine eggs, cream, salt, mustard and salt; pour over crab.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Let set for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: creamy egg salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, mayonnaise, salt and pepper until smooth.
Add green pepper, celery and relish.
Fold in eggs.
Refrigerate until serving. Yield: 3 cups.

title: lasagna pie
directions: Cook noodles.
Combine ricotta, milk, basil & pepper and set aside.

title: petite turkey loaf
directions: Combine egg yolk, bread crumbs, green onion, water, parsley, salt, sage and ground turkey in bowl; mix well.
Shape into 1 x 4 1/2-inch loaf.
Place in small shallow baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes; drain and spoon relish on top.
Bake for 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Serve with baked sweet potato and fresh garden salad.
Yields 1 serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles; rinse and drain.
Heat oil in pan and brown beef.
Stir in the next 6 ingredients.
Cover; simmer for 15 minutes.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1/3 noodles, then 1/3 sauce and cheese, another 1/3 noodles, 1/3 sauce and cheese and, last, 1/3 noodles, sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon punch
directions: Bring first 2 ingredients to a boil, cool then add pineapple and lemon juice.
Mix together.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale and almond extract.

title: bread pudding(my mother's)
directions: Blend ingredients
and	pour
over
3 cups bread crumbs which have been buttered and toasted.
Bake in buttered pan at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: ozark apple pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in greased and floured pan for 1 hour at 325°.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: remarkable fudge
directions: Butter saucepan.
Combine sugar, milk and butter.
Cook over medium heat to soft ball stage (236°).
Stir often.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips, vanilla and marshmallow cream.
Beat until creamy.
Add nuts.
Mix well.
Pour in greased pan.
Let cool.
Cut.

title: chicken and sausage casserole
directions: Cook rice using package directions.
Brown sausage with hot pepper flakes in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Combine rice and sausage in bowl; mix well.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery in oil in skillet.
Add sauteed vegetables, chicken, water chestnuts and mixture of bouillon cubes and water to sausage and rice mixture; mix well.
Spoon into baking dish.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: hamburger vegetable casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add vegetables; mix well with tomato soup, which has been mixed with equal parts of water. Place mixture into 3-quart casserole; pour the mushroom soup over the top.
Bake at 350° until vegetables are done, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Put everything in a large buttered casserole and mix.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Take cover off and stir a few times. Cook until done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Prepare fruit and put in a large bowl.
Mix juice with vanilla pudding.
Stir together and chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender; debone.
Save broth.
Layer chicken in casserole dish.
Pour 1 can cream of celery, mixed with 1 can of chicken broth, over chicken.
Use 1/2 Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix.
Layer second row of chicken; pour 1 can cream of chicken, mixed with can of chicken broth.
Use rest of stuffing mix and 1 stick of butter on top (melted well).
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: basic refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix 1/4 c warm water and yeast together, stir.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Saute in heavy skillet, butter, onions and garlic.
When tender, add ground chuck and Worcestershire.
Cook until meat is brown.
Remove from heat and add tomatoes, rice, cheese and spices. Return to heat and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
While this is cooking, steam 6 bell peppers.
Salt and pepper cooked peppers, fill with meat mixture and top with butter.
Bake 15 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stew
directions: Cook beef tender and add vegetables:
6 to 8 potatoes, 5 to 6 carrots and 5 to 6 stalks celery.
Add vegetables according to what you like and thickness you want.
You can make as much as you like. I coat the beef cubes with a little flour before I brown it.
This helps thicken the broth.

title: corn casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Mix all other ingredients, except cheese, in casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: savory yogurt chicken
directions: In a pie plate, stir together bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, onion, garlic powder, seasoned salt, oregano, thyme and pepper. Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Coat chicken with yogurt; roll in crumb mixture.
Place chicken, meaty side up, in a lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Drizzle margarine atop.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 45 to 55 minutes or until tender.
Serve with creamy yogurt sauce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Empty gelatin into small bowl; add boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Add cold water, salt and pineapple.
Chill until mixture is slightly thickened.
Fold into gelatin mixture the shredded carrots.
Pour into 4 cup molds or 1 (8 x 8 x 2-inch) baking pan.
Chill until set.
Serve in the pan or molds.
Can also be cut into squares.
Makes 6 servings.

title: terry's old settlers beans
directions: Brown hamburger and cook bacon.
Crumble bacon in hamburger and mix rest of ingredients into meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice and spinach casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and place into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until done.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except tomatoes.
Marinate overnight. Chill.
Stir every once in awhile to coat.
Pour into serving bowl and add tomatoes.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Bake in an unbaked pie shell.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Boil water.
Add chicken, carrots, potatoes and onion; cook until done.
Debone chicken; dice up.
Drain juice and save.
Add canned vegetables.
Add some of the juice back to pan.
Heat all together.
Thicken with cornstarch and water.

title: earthquake cake dessert(this is unusual and very good)
directions: Grease 9 x 13 x 3-inch pan.
(If you use 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, you will have run-over in your oven.)
Cover bottom with coconut, as much as you desire.
Cover coconut with chopped nuts.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In saucepan, bring sugar and water to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Jell-O until dissolved. Chill until mixture is slightly thickened.
Fold in cranberries, apples, oranges and pecans.
Put in 6 1/2-cup mold or 11 x 7 x 2-inch dish and chill.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, adding sugar gradually.
Beat very well. Add eggs alternately with flour which has been sifted before measuring.
Beat well after each addition. Add flavoring.
Grease tube or Bundt pan. Sprinkle lightly with flour. Bake approximately 1 hour in 350° oven. Cool before removing.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients until fluffy.
Sift together dry ingredients; stir into molasses mixture.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove from pan.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: cinnamon pudding
directions: Cover with nuts.
Mix and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Scald milk and add sugar, butter and salt.
Let cool.
Add beaten egg, then yeast.
Mix in flour.
Don't knead!
Mix with wooden spoon; it should be sticky.
Let rise until double (1 hour).
Flour counter as dough will be sticky! Shape into rolls; let rise.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.

title: four layer pie(easy and delicious!)
directions: Mix all ingredients, thoroughly. Place crust mixture in a 9 x 13 baking pan and bake at 350 degrees until slightly golden brown.

title: strawberry refrigerator dessert
directions: Beat butter until creamy.
Add sugar, then eggs and beat. Place 1/2 of crumbs in a 7 x 11-inch pan.
Spread cream mixture on top.
Cover with strawberries, then the whipped cream.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Chill thoroughly.

title: lunch box surprises(child-approved)
directions: When school starts in the fall, make the transition easier for your kids, especially the younger ones, with special lunch box surprises.
It's a nice treat to continue throughout the year, too!

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cut
carrots
in half crosswise, then lengthwise into 2 or 3 sticks.
Simmer,
covered, in a small amount of boiling, salted water
about 10 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain. Melt the butter;
stir
in
brown sugar until dissolved.
Add carrots. Cook
over medium-low heat about 10 minutes, turning often. Sprinkle with snipped parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 35 minutes until golden.
Serve with crackers.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Line bottom of 1 1/2-quart baking dish with 1 pound of your butter.
Sprinkle 1/2 of all seasonings, dry and liquids, over butter that lines pan.
Add cleaned shrimp with heads on.
Add remainder of ingredients over shrimp, dotting the remaining butter on top last.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Check one of the larger shrimp for doneness.
When serving, put the sauce from the shrimp in bowls and dip with hot French bread.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry pie filling
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until clear and thick.
Cool and add jello and strawberries.
Mix well and pour into pie crust.

title: spaghetti squash with spicy meat sauce
directions: About 1 hour before serving, cut spaghetti squash lengthwise in half.
Discard seeds.
In 12-inch skillet over high heat, in 1-inch boiling water, place squash, cut side up.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 40 minutes or until squash is fork-tender.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix as pie dough.
Press into 9 x 7 x 11-inch dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: flounder stuffed with crabmeat
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients in 1/2 cup butter.
Add crumbs, eggs, pepper and parsley.
Add crabmeat and toss lightly.
Place 2 to 3 tablespoons stuffing on each flounder fillet; top with a pat of butter and lemon juice.
Lap ends across stuffing and secure with a toothpick.
Place in a greased baking dish.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes (cover with foil).
Serve with White Wine Sauce.

title: creole shrimp
directions: Saute celery, onion, garlic and green pepper.
Add remaining ingredients (except shrimp) and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add cooked shrimp and serve over rice.

title: apple pie
directions: In a large size mixing bowl, thoroughly combine all ingredients except butter.
Do not drain liquid from apples.
It is necessary for juice.
(Mix all filling ingredients and let them marinate while preparing pie crust.)
Turn apples into pastry lined pie plate, dot with butter and cover with top crust.
Make slits to allow steam to escape, seal and flute edges of crust.
Bake in 425° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: stuffed peppers(peperoni ripieni)
directions: Cut top off of
pepper and discard pulp and seeds.
Set aside. Combine in
mixing
bowl:
beef, garlic, parsley, egg, salt, pepper, rice and 4 ounces tomato sauce.
Mix well.
Fill cavity of pepper
with
meat
filling
and replace top.
Saute onion in oil until tender.
Remove onion and set aside.

title: sloppy kielbasi
directions: Cut kielbasi lengthwise and into bite-size pieces.
Cook kielbasi in frying pan with a little water and some of the pineapple juice.
Add pork and beans to a 2-quart baking dish along with drained pineapple and kielbasi; drain off fat.
Bake in oven at 350° until bubbly.

title: velvety cheesecake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press into bottom of a 9-inch spring form pan.
Bake 325° for 10 minutes. Combine cream cheese, sugar, flour and vanilla in a mixer; beat until smooth.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add sour cream.
Pour into a cooled crust.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Cool before removing sides of pan.
Chill before serving.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts for 1 hour.
Let cool and remove chicken from bone in small strips.
Mix together in a large bowl Ro-Tel tomatoes, cream of chicken soup and cream of mushroom soup.
Add boiled chicken strips to mixture.
Crush a layer of Tostitos chips on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour mixture over chips.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Remove and top with grated cheese.
Return to the oven and bake until cheese is nice and melted.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients, adding chicken last and stirring gently.
Turn into a large Pyrex baking dish.
Mix 1 package (1 roll) Ritz crackers (crushed) and 1/4 cup margarine (melted).
Sprinkle on casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: baked ham
directions: Place ham in baking pan.
Add water.
Bake 6 to 8 hours at 350°.
Cover ham in aluminum foil.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles in unsalted water.
Drain and mix with the remaining
ingredients.
Put in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Top with potato chips, paprika and more grated cheese.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes, until bubbly hot.

title: orzo pasta salad
directions: Drain pineapple chunks and mandarin oranges.
Retain syrup. Cook pasta.
Drain and cool, then combine with fruit.
Combine in saucepan, sugar, eggs, salt and fruit syrup.
Cook until thickened.
Cool and add to pasta.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add Cool Whip and serve.

title: orange tea muffins
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar and orange juice.
Set aside.
Cream butter and remaining sugar; blend in sour cream. Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Beat at low just until ingredients are combined.
Stir in orange peel, raisins and nuts. The batter will be stiff.
Spoon batter into greased muffin cups, filling each cup completely.
Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes or until done.
While still warm, dip each muffin into reserved sugar/orange juice mixture.
Cool.

title: lima bean delicious
directions: Soak beans overnight; next morning, cook until water is almost gone.
Pour into a baking dish and add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake 2 hours in a moderate oven, 350°, or until nice, thick and caramel-like.

title: crumb coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Stir in milk, flour, baking powder and vanilla and combine well.
Pour into 10 x 13 baking dish.
For topping, combine sugar, flour and cinnamon, cut in butter until crumbly.
Scatter topping evenly over cake and bake at 325 F for 30-40 minutes, testing for doneness.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel.
Reserve 4 tablespoons drippings.
Saute onion in bacon drippings until tender.
Blend in flour slowly; then stir in vinegar and water. Cook until mixture boils and thickens slightly.
Add sugar, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Layer potatoes, bacon and sauce in casserole dish.
Keep warm for several hours to allow flavors to blend.
A 275° oven works best.

title: noodle pudding(kugle)
directions: With 4 eggs and 1/2 cup of milk, mix the first 6 ingredients. Add to cooked noodles and add raisins.
In a separate bowl, mix 2 cups of milk, 2 eggs, sugar and salt and pour over noodles. Sprinkle crushed corn flakes on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour in a large roasting pan. Test with dinner knife. Should be a little moist.

title: strawberry chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water in saucepan.
Blend together sugar, flour and salt.
Add to softened gelatin; mix thoroughly. Place over medium heat and stir constantly until gelatin is dissolved and mixture thickened.
Add crushed strawberries and lemon juice.
Chill until mixture is slightly thicker than the consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold into this the whipped cream.
Turn into baked pastry shell.
Garnish with additional strawberries and whipped cream.

title: fruit delight
directions: Mix the ingredients and chill thoroughly overnight.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: combination punch
directions: Mix the juices and let stand an hour or two to blend the flavors.
Pour in ginger ale and serve over ice.
Serves 50 to 60.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Combine eggs, corn muffin mix, corns, sour cream and oleo. Spread in an 11 x 7 x 1 3/4-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes more or until knife comes out clean.

title: butch's meat pie
directions: Cook Worcestershire sauce, meat, onion (cut up), garlic powder and lemon pepper until brown.
Drain.
Put in bottom of pan. Spread potatoes (mashed) over meat, evenly.
Bake cheese evenly; spread over potatoes.
Pour melted butter on top and serve.

title: crepes
directions: Use 6-inch skillet, lightly greased, medium heat. Spoon in 3 tablespoons batter.
When batter bubbles, flip and cook on other side a few seconds.
Roll favorite filling into middle: ham, broccoli and cheese and fresh fruit, etc. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need one plastic flower pot (3-inch to 4-inch).
Cream together the butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Set aside. Mix milk, pudding and whipped cream.
Fold into butter, cheese and sugar mixture.
Cover drainage hole of flower pot with wax paper. Put 1/3 of the crushed cookies in bottom of pot.
Cover cookies with 1/2 the filling mixture.
Cover with the rest of the filling. Cover with the remaining third of the cookies.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pork chops with tomatoes and creole mustard
directions: Allow the chops to come to room temperature.
Heat the oil over moderate heat.
Brown the chops on both sides and reduce heat.
Cook slowly until done.
Do not overcook.
Remove chops and set aside.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Butter a 9-inch square pan.
Cover with chopped nuts.
Butter the sides of a 2-quart saucepan.
Add sugar, milk and salt.
Stir and bring to boiling about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips and vanilla. Stir until well blended. Spread the chocolate mixture over the nuts.
Add marshmallows.
Press into the chocolate.
Add remaining chocolate mixture.
Cool and cut into pieces.

title: seven layered salad
directions: Layer all ingredients exactly in order, starting with the lettuce and ending with the bacon.
Do not toss.
Serve as is. Looks best in a clear glass salad bowl.

title: super pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in hot fat.
Mix soup, seasoning and diced onion together.
Pour mixture over chops. Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana bread (no sugar)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch bread pan.
Cream butter and sweetener until light and fluffy.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift all purpose flour, baking soda and salt together; stir in whole wheat flour and add it to cream mixture.
Mix well.
Fold in bananas, vanilla and nuts.
Pour in pan and bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: banana layer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time with electric mixer, beating well after each addition. Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add to creamed mixture alternately with flour, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in bananas, vanilla and pecans.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into batter.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9 inch pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Remove cakes from pans and cover cakes immediately until cool to retain moisture.
Ice with caramel frosting.

title: pink salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water. Add tomato sauce. Heat on low, stirring until gelatin is dissolved. Gradually add mayonnaise to cream cheese until softened. Add celery, green peppers and olives to tomato mixture. Combine the two mixtures and pour into 1 1/2 quart mold. Serves 8 or 10.

title: high fiber bran muffins
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and raisins. Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine All-Bran, wheat bran and milk.
Let stand about 5 minutes or until bran softens. Add egg white and orange juice.
Mix well. Add flour mixture, stirring only until combined and moistened.
Don't overmix. Bake in foil baking cups, 400° for about 20 minutes or until golden brown. Yields 12 muffins.

title: cocoa garden cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Set grated zucchini between paper towels and press to remove excess moisture.

title: refrigerator muffins
directions: Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs.
Blend in buttermilk. Add bran and mix well. This may be kept in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.

title: delicious texas quick one pan cake
directions: Just dump in the pan with the cooked cocoa and stir.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes at 375° in greased and floured pan.

title: chocolate strawberry torte
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line jelly roll pan with aluminum foil or wax paper, and grease foil or paper.
tags: recipe of your favorite chocolate cake batter

title: frosty pumpkin pie
directions: Spoon 3 cups of the topping into a 9-inch pie plate.
Using back of spoon, spread and shape topping into a shell.
Freeze until firm.
Combine pumpkin, sugar and spice, mixing until well blended. Fold in remaining 1 1/2 cups thawed topping.
Spoon into frozen shell; sprinkle with pecans.
Freeze until firm.

title: microwave heavenly caramels
directions: Scald tomatoes, peel, core and cut up or leave whole.
Put in scalded jars.
Fill jar with hot water or hot juice.
Seal well and put in cold oven at 250° for 45 minutes.
Don't open oven until cold.

title: almond flavor frosting
directions: In a large bowl, beat together sugar, butter, extract and milk until smooth.
If necessary, add more milk until frosting is spreading consistency.

title: white bread or rolls
directions: Mix the yeast in the warm water.
Heat the milk and margarine until scalded.
In bowl, beat the eggs.
Add yeast, salt, sugar, milk and margarine, a little at a time.
Add flour until dough is elastic.
Grease hands and bowl; knead just a little.
Put in bowl; let rise until triple in size.
Work down; form loaves or rolls. Let rise again until they fill pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until golden brown.
Brush top with butter.
Serve cool or hot.

title: chicken fettuccine
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cook spaghetti or fettuccine. Combine chicken, pasta, cheese, pimentos, salt, pepper and soups; mix well.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Place hash browns in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt the rest of the ingredients in a saucepan.
Pour over potatoes and bake almost 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in blueberries.
Add milk, egg and butter or margarine.
Mix until moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin cups.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. In large plastic bag, add all ingredients. Shake bag until evenly coated. Bake on shallow pan for 40 minutes, until tender and golden brown. Stir potatoes occasionally.

title: pineapple congealed salad
directions: Make Jell-O and when practically set, add Pet milk, cottage cheese, crushed pineapple, mayonnaise and nuts.
Mix well. Refrigerate until set.

title: juicy hamburgers
directions: Mix all ingredient and shape into patties.
Broil, grill or cook in skillet as desired.
(Do not press out juices while cooking.)
This simple hamburger recipe never fails to win compliments.

title: cranberry punch for 1
directions: Place a scoop of lime sherbet in a 6 ounce glass.
Pour cranberry juice over sherbet, filling glass.
Serve immediately.

title: wild rice with chicken and oranges
directions: Cook wild rice in chicken broth approximately 30 to 40 minutes.
Lay thighs, skin side up, in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan or dish.
Bake at 375° until skin is brown and meat is no longer pink at bone, approximately 40 minutes.
Remove and drain all juice, keep 2 tablespoons.
Blend with marmalade and brush over chicken. Bake another 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, the rice is cooking in the broth and should be done at same time as chicken.
While these are cooking, melt the butter in a frying pan with sliced onions and cinnamon.
Cook about 25 to 30 minutes.
Add rice and stir gently. Pour rice and onion into casserole.
Lay chicken on top with oranges and parsley.
Take orange half and squeeze juice over top. Serve hot.

title: karri banana bread
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and vanilla and add to bananas and beaten eggs.
Fold in flour, salt and soda.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mystery bars
directions: Line a large cookie sheet with crackers.
Boil margarine and sugar for 3 minutes.
Pour over saltine crackers and bake for 5 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate chips, spread chips as they melt.
Cut on lines while warm.

title: six layer casserole
directions: Alternate layers of potatoes, celery, beef, onions, and tomatoes in greased 2-quart casserole, sprinkling each layer with salt and pepper. Garnish with green pepper rings.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order by hand.
Pour into ungreased, unfloured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry crumb cake
directions: Blend flour, margarine, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Remove 1 cup into small bowl.
Blend eggs, vanilla and milk.
Blend these two mixtures.
Do not overbeat.
(Batter will be lumpy!)
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Drop carefully by teaspoonfuls the pie filling.
Add cinnamon to reserved cup. Sprinkle over top of cherries and cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Good served warm.

title: pignoli cookies
directions: Beat egg whites with sugar.
Beat almond paste until smooth. Gradually add egg whites and sugar mixture to almond paste.

title: chocolate peanut butter surprise cookies
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa powder, baking powder and baking soda. Set aside.

title: mozzarella bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bread.
Slice loaf of bread diagonally every 2-inches, but do not cut all the way through.
Spread mixture in between slices. Wrap bread with foil and heat in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Or you can double wrap in foil and put bread on grill at a cook out.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Beat sugar, eggs and flour.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes.
Pour over chocolate mixture.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Pour in pan.
Bake, then cool 8 hours in refrigerator.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dirt dessert
directions: You will also need a 7-inch flowerpot.

title: salt pickles
directions: Makes 1 quart.
If you want more than this, double the recipe.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Combine flour and melted margarine.
Press into a pizza pan. Sprinkle nuts over top; press into dough.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until lightly brown.
Cool completely.
Blend cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping. Spread over cooled crust, leaving a 1/4 inch border of crust showing.
Combine pie filling and drained tropical fruit; spread over the cream cheese layer.
Top with sliced strawberries and if desired, nuts.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: Crumble beef into a 4 to 5-quart Dutch oven.
Add onions; cook over medium heat for 5 to 6 minutes.
Quarter and core cabbage. Cut crosswise into 1-inch strips.
You should have about 8 cups. Add to meat mixture.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 5 to 7 minutes, until the cabbage wilts.
Stir in tomatoes, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, until cabbage is tender.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix cheese, soup and sour cream, then add onion and hash browns.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes and melt the cheese on the top.

title: canned beans
directions: Will also need 7 quart jars, 7 new lids and rings and 1 (7-quart) pressure cooker.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix together.
This mixture should be crumbly.
Put apples in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle flour mixture and pecans over top of apples.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
You can also top this with sour cream.

title: no knead bread sticks or soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Stir in oil, honey, salt and 1 cup flour.
Beat until smooth, stir in enough remaining flour, scraping dough from side of bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double, 45 minutes.
Heat oven to 400°. Stir down by beating about 25 strokes.
Turn dough onto floured surface, divide into 24 equal parts.
Roll and shape each part into rope about 9 inches long.
Place onto greased cookie sheet.
Brush with egg white and salt.
Bake about 15 minutes.

title: mama barringer's red slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients; pack into glass jars and refrigerate. Will keep for weeks.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs in serving pieces.
Place them in skillet and brown on both sides; drain.
Transfer ribs to deep pan and add remaining ingredients.
Cook on high until steaming.
Reduce heat to low and cook for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix all together well. Roll into balls the size of a walnut. Roll in a mixture of 1 Tbsp. cinnamon and 1 tsp. sugar. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart for 8-10 minutes at 375°.

title: linguini with white clam sauce(serves 4)
directions: Place all ingredients, except linguini, in a saucepan and heat to a simmer.
Cook linguini according to directions on package. Toss hot cooked spaghetti with clam sauce.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook about 2 hours.
You can also add other vegetables, just add more water.
This is an unlimited choice on Weight Watchers food plan.

title: chicken teriyaki salad
directions: Cube chicken or in strips.
Cook in small amount of oil until tender.
Add teriyaki sauce and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal softies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder into small bowl.
Cream butter in large bowl until light and fluffy. Beat eggs and vanilla into butter.
Mix in the sifted ingredients one third at a time.
Stir in nuts and oats.
Drop dough by teaspoon.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: apple brown betty
directions: If fresh apples are used, cook over low heat, adding sugar or sweetener, 1/2 cube butter, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cook for 10 minutes or until apples are soft.
If using canned apples, mix spices, sugar, vanilla and butter into apples and heat.

title: california potato casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except for the cornflakes and 1/2 stick of butter in a large mixing bowl. Pour into a 9 x 13 pan. Top with the cornflakes and remaining 1/2 stick of butter on top of cornflakes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bettie's chillie
directions: Brown hamburger.
About halfway through browning process, sprinkle flour over meat.
Stir constantly.
When brown, put into crock-pot; add chili powder, salt, onion, ketchup and water.
Start on high setting.
When it gets hot through, cut back on low setting.
Cook 3 to 4 hours.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni, then chill in water and drain.
Combine French dressing with macaroni.
Toss lightly.
Chill.
Add remaining ingredients, mix and chill.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Fry sausage, green pepper and onion.
Mix crust as directed. Spread crust on cookie sheet.
Layer with scrambled eggs.
Next layer sausage mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until browned.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients.
Pour in buttered 11 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until thick. Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Make a well in center and stir well beaten eggs and oil.
Stir until moist.
Fold in strawberries and nuts.
Bake in loaf pans at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: raisin pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add boiling water slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook over hot water until thick and clear. Add raisins, lemon juice and butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into pastry lined tin.
Cover with top crust.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for about 25 minutes.

title: rice salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Chill until starts to congeal.
Fold in rice, milk, whipped cream, pineapple and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: easy lemon chicken appetizers
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken in oil.
Pour off fat.
Add gravy, lemon juice, crushed thyme and vegetables to skillet. Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until done.
Spoon into pastry shells and serve.

title: chicken n rice
directions: Sprinkle rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan, sprayed with Pam.
Mix cream of celery soup, cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Pour evenly over rice.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle dried onion soup mix over chicken.
Seal pan with aluminum foil and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup milk with beaten eggs.
Heat 2 cups of the milk, then dissolve sugar in the milk.
Add salt, vanilla and almond. Pour into a pie shell that has been baked for 5 minutes.
Top with nutmeg.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 400°.
Cool.

title: sweet strawberry vinegar
directions: Place strawberries in a 3-quart glass or plastic bowl and crush berries.
Add vinegar; cover and let stand 24 hours.
Strain into a nonaluminum pan, pressing berries to extract as much juice as possible.
You should have approximately 6 cups juice.
Add sugar; bring to a simmer, stirring constantly.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Let cool slightly, then strain through a coffee filter or several layers of cheesecloth.

title: irish potato candy
directions: Mix together in a large bowl all ingredients except the cinnamon.
You may need to use your hands because this is a stiff mixture.
Break off pieces the size of large marbles and shape like potatoes.
Sprinkle a small pile of cinnamon on wax paper, and roll each potato in the cinnamon to coat it.
Do not stack the candy or put it in a covered container until the outer surface is no longer soft and sticky.
This takes a few hours.

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine ingredients.
Form into patties (about 6).
Cover with flour.
Fry in a small amount of oil until brown on each side.

title: mocha chocolate frosting
directions: Combine cocoa, coffee, butter and vanilla.
Beat until smooth. Add sugar gradually until of spreading consistency.
Will frost top and sides of a 9-inch large cake.

title: soy-ginger dressing(for both chinese chicken salad and spinach salad)
directions: In a jar with lid, mix ingredients.
Makes 2 cups.

title: cinnamon breakfast cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle bottom with nuts. Combine cake mix, pudding, oleo, eggs and water.
Mix well.
Pour half of batter over nuts in pan.
Mix sugar with cinnamon and sprinkle on batter in pan.
Top with remaining batter and bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes until done.
Let cool 15 minutes. Meanwhile, mix powdered sugar with milk to make glaze.
Drizzle over cake and serve warm.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Press potatoes through a ricer.
Add other ingredients, then follow with the milk.
Fold in lightly beaten eggs last.
Pour into uncooked pastry shell of white flour or graham crackers and bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.
This may also be garnished with marshmallows, nuts or coconut as desired.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken
until
tender.
Cool
and
remove
bones. Cook rice in chicken
broth.
Mix
cooked rice and 1 can cream of mushroom soup together.
Spread in buttered casserole dish. Put chicken on top
of	rice.
Spread
other
can
of cream of mushroom soup over chicken.
Spread the can of cream of celery soup over mixture.	Top
with
grated cheese.
Cover casserole dish with aluminum foil
and
bake in 350° oven until soup and cheese bubbles and cheese melts.

title: mom's coleslaw
directions: Wash and shred cabbage for slaw. In large bowl, combine all ingredients. Refrigerate to get maximum flavor.

title: festive snack mix
directions: God creates babies.
Abortion?
Search the scriptures for the answer:
Psalms 10:14, Matthew 18:1-6, Jeremiah 1:5, Galatians 1:15, Job 10:8-12, Psalms 139:13-16 and Exodus 21:22-23.

title: miss stella magee's millionaire pie
directions: Beat eggs well; add other ingredients.
Spices are added to taste.
Cook until thickened.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with meringue made with egg whites.
Beat whites stiff; add sugar and vanilla to taste.
Bake until golden brown.

title: hot corned beef sandwich
directions: Mix well; fill hamburger buns.
Wrap in foil.
Heat 25 minutes at 375°.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Finely crush crackers; add butter and sugar.
Press mixture into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
Reserve some crumbs for garnish. Blend orange juice and milk in a bowl.
Stir in Cool Whip and oranges.
Fold in, do not beat.
Pour mixture over crumb crust. Top with reserved crumbs.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Brown ground round; set aside (don't drain).
Over medium heat, cook celery, 1 cup pepper and onion in cooking oil (enough to cover bottom of pan) until soft.
Add to ground round.
Cook over medium heat.
Add chicken broth and 1 cup bread crumbs; season to taste with red and black pepper and seasoning salt.
Let cook about 1/2 hour.
Add shrimp.
Let cook about 1/2 hour.
Boil or steam rice; drain.
Add to meat and vegetable mixture; stir. Core and deseed peppers.
Boil until soft.
Do not overcook. Stuff peppers full of mixture; top with cheese and rest of bread crumbs.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover at end to lightly brown.

title: quiche
directions: Drain veggies.
Grate cheese.
Mix ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to an hour.
Serves 6.

title: rummy holiday fruitcake
directions: Read directions carefully before starting.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Arrange drummettes in pan or casserole dish.
Heat remaining ingredients until butter and sugar dissolve.
Pour over drummettes; allow to marinate for at least 2 hours or longer, turning occasionally.
Place in oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, turning and basting.
Can be frozen and reheated.

title: country stew
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut meat into bite-sized pieces.
Peel and cut potatoes into pieces larger than meat.
Clean carrots, celery and onion and cut into 1-inch pieces.
In a large, heavy roasting pan or ceramic crock-pot, combine all ingredients.
Bake, covered, for 5 hours without stirring.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat margarine and sugar together.
To mixture beat in eggs and gradually add flour.
Add flavoring.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 325°
for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli hamburger pie
directions: For crust, mix Bisquick, milk and 1/2 c. cheese. Spread into bottom of 12 by 15 pan.
Then layer hamburger, onion, mushrooms, broccoli and the other shredded cheese in that order.
Beat eggs and milk; pour over the top.
Bake at 325° for one hour.
You can add more cheese to the top if so desired.
If a glass pan is used adjust cooking time to less.

title: jello pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Crusts:
Mix melted butter and graham cracker crumbs.
Press in 2 pie pans and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Then chill.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Boil molasses and syrup to firm ball.
Add butter.
Mix in popped corn and nuts; press hard in greased tube pan.
Let stand at least 2 hours.
Remove from pan.
Decorate with small (or cut up large) gumdrops.
If warm enough, decorate sides also.
Slice like cake.

title: aunt erna's egg custard
directions: Combine eggs, salt and flavoring.
Beat, beat, beat until mixture begins to look thick.
Gradually add sugar and beat constantly.
Scald milk and pour into mixture, stirring as you pour milk in.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
This will seem to be too much, but add it all.
It does not bubble or run over.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
The pie will shake like jello when done. Sprinkle top with nutmeg if desired.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Blend cream cheese, garlic salt, onion, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and mayonnaise in mixer.
Spread over a glass pie plate.
Pour 1/2 bottle chili sauce over spread.
Spread thawed, rinsed and drained crabmeat over chili sauce.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate 8 hours.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Mix taco mix and add 1/2 cup water.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour into casserole.
In separate bowl, mix Jiffy mixes.
Pour over top.
Prick with a fork.
Cook at 375° for 1 hour or until done.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13 pan, place cherries on bottom.
Spread pineapple over cherries.
Sprinkle DRY cake mix over fruit, breaking up large lumps. Sprinkle mix with pecans.
Place slices of butter on top. Bake at 350° for about and hour.
Cake should be golden brown.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray.
Pour cake mixture into pan.
Top with 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
(Sprinkle mixture over cake.) Bake at 350°.

title: chicken enchilada pie
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add peppers, soups, broth, chicken. In baking dish, layer flour tortillas, chicken mixture and cheese. Make 2 layers of each.
Bake until cheese melts at 350°.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and add vinegar.
Add salad dressing to taste.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: no cook marshmallow frosting
directions: Add salt to egg whites and beat until frothy.
Gradually add sugar beating until smooth and glossy.
Slowly add Karo beating until frosting stands in peaks.
Fold in vanilla.

title: orange roughy delight
directions: Spray baking pan with "Pam".
Place fish on pan.
Sprinkle lemon juice, garlic, parsley, pepper and salt over each piece of fish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until flaky.
Serve over steamed white rice.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli and drain and place in a baking dish.
Layer ham and cheese over broccoli.
Beat remaining ingredients with hand mixer until smooth.
Slowly pour over cheese.
Bake 1 hour.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Spread nuts and coconut in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Pour over nuts and coconut. Melt margarine.
Add cream cheese and sugar.
Blend well and pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening, white and brown sugar.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and mix well.
Add nuts and potato chips.
Mix well.
Drop on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Press with fork that has been dipped in hot water.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream together brown sugar, white sugar, shortening and egg. Add vanilla, sour milk and flour to creamed mixture.
Stir in rhubarb.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: dinner in a pumpkin
directions: Cut off top of pumpkin and clean out.
Mix ingredients together and stuff the pumpkin with mixture.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate gravy and biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in a saucepan, then add butter and milk.
Bring to a boil until thickened.
Pour over biscuits.

title: crab hors d'oeuvres
directions: Blend ingredients.
Blend in a 6 1/2 ounce can of strained crabmeat. Split 6 English muffins and spread mixture on each half. Cut each half into 4 pieces. Brown under broiler.

title: curry dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve with vegetable strips.

title: pizza boats
directions: Split buns lengthwise.
Spread with light layer of sauce.
Top with pizza fixings and cheese.
Broil until cheese is lightly browned.

title: party meat balls
directions: Combine and mix these thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch meat balls.
Shake 4 to 5 balls at a time in Shake 'n Bake (chicken) coating mix.
Place in an ungreased shallow baking pan.
Bake at 450° about 5 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve on wooden toothpicks.
Can be frozen before baking.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes when frozen or until lightly brown.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: spinach dip with hawaiian bread
directions: Thaw and drain spinach in strainer.
Mix together vegetable soup mix, onions, mayonnaise, sour cream, chestnuts and spinach. Cover and let set overnight in fridge.
Cut center out of a round loaf of Hawaiian bread to make a bowl to put dip in.
Tear apart bread that was used to make bowl.
Place bread bowl on serving platter along with torn bread to use to dip.

title: rice with smoked sausage
directions: Cook rice as directed on box.
Fry sausage in skillet.
Put nuts in food processor and chop up.
Add sausage and nuts to rice mixture after cooked.
"Great dish."

title: baked steak
directions: Run cold water over steak.
Sprinkle tenderizer over on both sides; set	overnight
or
to 2 hours.
Cover with wax paper. Brown on
both
sides in little oleo.
Place in baking pan.
Top with
catsup,
chopped
onion and mushrooms. Bake 2 hours at	325°.
Last
20 minutes of baking time, pour black coffee over and
baste
several times.
Last 5 minutes, rake toppings into gravy.

title: reese's peanut butter squares(candy)
directions: Melt together over low heat the peanut butter and butter or margarine.
Take off the heat and add the powdered sugar.
Press this mixture in a 9 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Over very low heat, melt the Crisco and chocolate chips.
Spread over mixture in pan. Chill.
When cool, cut into small squares.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons butter, add flour and salt.
Add milk slowly and cook until sauce thickens.
Melt cheese in sauce if used.
Add sliced potatoes; bring to a boil.
Put into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and dot with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Yields 15 servings.

title: broccoli in yogurt cheese
directions: Brush broccoli with 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Arrange broccoli in a shallow baking dish.
Stir together the remaining ingredients, except croutons, and spread over the broccoli. Sprinkle top with garlic crouton crumbs.
Heat at 350° for 15 minutes or until heated through.
