Broil crumbs for a few seconds to brown and serve at once.
Serves 8.

title: savory brunch pull-apart
directions: Thoroughly grease a 10-inch fluted tube pan.
In a small bowl, combine Parmesan cheese, sesame seed and basil.
Add about one-third of the mixture to greased pan. Lift and turn pan to coat the sides and bottom.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Prepare dressing of mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and a little water. Refrigerate overnight.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Mix well.
Pour half of mixture in 7 x 11-inch greased pan.
Put half of cheese on top; pour remainder of mixture in; then top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: jello mold
directions: Mix all ingredients together; let set for 2 hours before serving.

title: scandinavian walnut cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla together.
Add flour to make a stiff dough.
Using 1 tablespoon of dough at a time, shape dough into pieces 2 1/2 inches long.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Brush top of cookie with slightly beaten egg white. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 14 to 18 minutes.

title: mountain house corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into hot greased iron skillet. Bake in a hot 400° oven for 20 minutes or until done.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and add broth to make very soft. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour in greased pan and bake until firm.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: Mix together and simmer until thoroughly heated. Serve.

title: roast chicken and gravy
directions: Mix all ingredients together in roasting pan.
Place metal rack in pan.
Place chicken (either stuffed or unstuffed) in pan. Cook about 2 hours, uncovered, at 350°.
After bird is cooked, mix pan drippings with Wondra sauce and gravy flour (regular flour may be used).
Serve over dressing and/or potatoes.

title: cherry fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cool 2 hours before serving.

title: grebel
directions: Mix all ingredients together (dough will be sticky).
Roll out on a heavily floured board to about 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut in slices about 2 inches apart.
Then cut in opposite direction about 4 inches.
Make a slit in the middle long way and pull one end through the middle.
Deep fry in hot oil until browned on both sides.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar or plain sugar.

title: fudgy chocolate cake
directions: Place butter, milk and cocoa in pan.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add sugar; stir well.
Add vanilla and nuts. Pour over cake while both are hot.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients together.
Add 1/2 to 3/4 grated onion.
Add few dashes of garlic salt to taste. Form into 2 balls and roll into nuts. Serve with favorite cracker.

title: monkey cake
directions: Mix the two sugars and cinnamon together; set aside.
Spray the baking pan with Pam.
Arrange the quartered biscuits around the pan.
Drizzle the butter over the biscuits.
Sprinkle sugar cinnamon mixture on top.
Bake in oven at 325° for 25 minutes. Serve warm.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients and pat on 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 325° until light brown.

title: sunshine pickles
directions: Soak cukes, onions and peppers in mixture of 1/4 cup salt to 1 quart water for 2 hours.
Drain for 1 hour.
Cook in the rest of ingredients until tender.
Seal hot.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: In large bowl, combine sugars, margarine and vegetable oil. Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla and soured milk; beat until smooth.
Sift flour, cocoa, baking soda, allspice and cinnamon together and add gradually to mixture, beating until smooth.
Fold in zucchini, chocolate bits and nuts.
Beat until well incorporated.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine butter Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat egg into cream mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda into mixture until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop dough in a round shape, about 2 tablespoons, 3 inches apart, onto ungreased cooking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes (for chewy cookies).
Cookies will appear moist.
Do not overbake.
Leave cool on cookie sheet for 2 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan. Crush Doritos in bottom of pan to fully cover it.
In a bowl, mix soups, Milnot, Ro-Tel, onion, green pepper and chili powder. Spread chicken over Doritos, then soup mixture. Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash the bananas with a fork. Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour in a 325° preheated oven.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Brown meat in butter in frypan until done.
In a bowl, mix other ingredients.
Mix hamburger and mixture together and place in covered casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Place drained Veg-All into casserole dish and top with Cheez Whiz.
Sprinkle with Ritz crackers and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: ham and swiss casserole
directions: Layer 1/3 of the noodles, ham and cheese in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine soup, sour cream, peppers and onions in small bowl. Spread half of soup mix over top of noodles, ham and cheese. Repeat layers. Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: no peek casserole
directions: Combine ingredients well in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Don't peek until it's done!
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: pakistan curry(very spicy)
directions: Saute onion in fat; add seasoning and a little water.
Stir. Add meat and brown in the seasoned sauce; add more water and cook until tender.
For a little thicker gravy, dust the meat with flour before browning.
Serve with oven-boiled rice, a side dish of chepaties (tortillas), green beans or any vegetable of your choice.

title: potato bacon chowder
directions: Microwave bacon.
Pop into freezer to help cool for crumbling later.
In saucepan, place potatoes, water, salt, onion and bacon and cook until potatoes fall apart and liquid is thickened.
Lower heat and add sour cream and soup.
Gradually add milk.
Add pepper and parsley.
Heat to serving temperature.
Do not boil!!

title: dried beef hot dish
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots until tender.
Make white sauce with margarine, flour and milk.
Add cream cheese.
Stir until smooth. Mix all ingredients.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: ham ball
directions: In the bowl of a processor or mixing bowl, combine all but paprika and sweet gherkin pickles.
Chill for easy handling.
Form into a ball on a serving plate.
Dust with paprika and surround with whole baby pickles.
Serve with celery, carrots, summer squash rounds and crackers.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Combine cheese and butter.
Add flour and mix well.
Shape into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten each ball with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: cajun-fried turkey
directions: You will need a 36 to 40 quart pot with either wire net or metal rack of some type (to keep turkey off bottom), thermometer (clip-on type), fish cooker and a wire coat hanger.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and margarine. Add eggs one at a time. Add flour and milk alternately. Fold in flavoring. Bake in tube pan, greased and floured, for 1 hour and 45 minutes in 325° oven.

title: cheese pennies
directions: Mix Rice Krispies, flour and salt with fork.
Add cheese and butter.
Form into balls and flatten with fork dipped in cold water.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt margarine (save 3 tablespoons for cornflakes) and saute onion until tender.
Mix potatoes, sauteed onion and butter.
Pour into a large casserole dish.
Combine soup, milk and sour cream. Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Melt reserved 3 tablespoons of butter.
Add crushed cornflakes and stir until well coated.
Spread over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients except Blue cheese at low speed for 1/2 minute and then 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add Blue cheese and blend for 4 minutes at low speed.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Slightly beat eggs; add sugar, syrup and flour.
Mix well.
Add vanilla, melted butter, pecans and salt.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake approximately one hour at 350°.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Clean lettuce and cauliflower.
Shred lettuce in the bottom of a large bowl.
Slice cauliflower on top.
Crumble bacon on top. Spread mayonnaise over all to "seal." Sprinkle sugar on top. Cover.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Toss before serving.

title: cains mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, and soda.
Add water and mayonnaise.
Blend well.
Add vanilla and lemon.
Grease and flour bunt pan or square pan.
Pour mixture into prepared pan and bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.
Serve warm or cooled with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: pam's macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix together milk, mustard, Cheddar cheese soup and pepper. Stir in macaroni and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Stir and sprinkle the remaining 1/2 cup of cheese and top with French fried onions.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Mix soup, cheese and sour cream.
Add potatoes.
Mix.
Put in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: date roll
directions: Crush crackers into fine crumbs.
Add chopped dates, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix well and add cream.
Form into a roll, wrap in wax paper or foil and store in refrigerator.
Slice and serve with Cool Whip.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ivory cashew chews
directions: Place the chocolate and condensed milk in the top of a double boiler.
Combine natural cereal and nuts in large mixing bowl. Pour the chocolate mixture over dry mixture.
Stir to evenly coat dry mixture.
Form mixture into 1-inch diameter balls.
Place on waxed paper covered cookie sheet.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
(Can be frozen in covered container up to 1 month.
Thaw and store in refrigerator.)

title: chicken salad filling for pocket bread
directions: Mix mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice and salt together.
Add the remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: pepper steak
directions: Pound steak and roll in flour.
Cut in strips or pieces. Brown in Crisco.
Add beef broth or water, garlic, salt and pepper.
Simmer until meat is tender, about 20 minutes.
Add together soy sauce, water and cornstarch.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add chopped onion and green pepper.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Add molasses, sugar and eggs to melted margarine; beat well. Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, ginger and cloves and add to creamed mixture.
Refrigerate the dough for several hours.
Make off into small balls; roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° until firm or brown, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields approximately 6 dozen.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine ingredients in order.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: world famous potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in large cubes.
Melt margarine in water; add soup mix.
Layer potatoes and liquid in a 2-quart casserole dish, ending with liquid.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.
Will keep in warm oven.
Very good the next day.

title: easy lemon meringue pie
directions: Stir pudding mix with sugar, 1/2 cup water and egg yolks in a medium saucepan.
Stir in 2 cups water and lemon juice.
Follow rest of directions on pudding box.
Garnish top of pie with slivers of lemon peel.

title: blueberry sour cream dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, nuts, graham cracker crumbs and margarine until crumbly.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups for topping.
Press remaining mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan; spread with pie filling.
In small bowl, mix sour cream, egg and nutmeg.
Pour over pie filling.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Toss apples with lemon juice.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Let sit for 5-10 minutes, occasionally stirring. Pour into pie crust.
Dot top of pie with pieces of butter.
Place top crust over pie.
Cut vents in top crust.
Crimp edges together.
Bake 45 minutes on top rack at 425°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion for 5 minutes.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly greased and flour a 8 x 8-inch or loaf pan.
In bowl, blend dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until well combined.
Turn batter into prepared pan.
Bake about 40 minutes.
Cool in pan on rack about 10 minutes.
Turn cake out and cool completely before frosting as desired.

title: pretzel-jello salad
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and margarine and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes; cool.
Beat well the cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip and blend well.
Spread over cooled pretzels and refrigerate 30 minutes.
Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Add strawberries and pineapple. Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate in covered dish.
Drain as used.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Mix pretzels with melted margarine and 1/3 cup sugar.
Bake 8 minutes as crust in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and whipped topping.
Spread on crust. Prepare Jell-O and stir in strawberries.
Pour over cheese mix. Chill for several hours.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant; cut in pieces and cook in water until tender. Drain and mash; add 1/4 stick oleo, milk, egg, onion, cheese and soup.
Mix well and pour in casserole.
Mix cracker crumbs and 1 stick oleo.
Pour over top of casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until bubbles good.

title: dried apricot cake
directions: Simmer first 3 ingredients together 30 minutes.
Mash and measure 1/2 cup pulp.
Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly, add yolks and vanilla;
beat.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with water and pulp.
Bake in a cake pan (8x8 inches), lined with waxed paper, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by tablespoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Put on wax paper to cool.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, sour cream and beef; beat with mixer.
Melt butter with salt and brown pecans.
Stir 1/2 of pecans into beef mixture.
Add onion, green pepper and seasonings. Put into small baking dish and sprinkle with remaining pecans. Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: sweet-and-sour slaw
directions: Mix vinegar, oil, salt and celery seed together.
Pour over cabbage, pepper and onion; mix together.
Let stand 2 or 3 hours. Will keep 3 or 4 days in refrigerator.

title: coconut rhubarb cake
directions: Cream oleo and brown sugar; add egg and beat well.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda.
Add vanilla to milk.
Add wet and dry ingredients alternately to egg mixture, mixing well.
Add rhubarb.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 7 ounces coconut over top. Mix 1/2 cup sugar with cinnamon and sprinkle on top of coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: decorator icing
directions: In
large
mixing
bowl, beat with electric mixer until smooth and fluffy.
Spread on cooled cake and decorate.

title: cheesy broccoli soup
directions: In large stockpot, put water, potatoes, celery, onions, carrots, broccoli, chicken bouillon, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil and simmer until vegetables are tender, 15 to 20 minutes. Blend flour with milk; slowly add to vegetables, stirring until thickens.
Add cheese cubes and stir until melted.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken soup with papaya
directions: In large saucepot, heat oil and brown chicken.
Add ginger and onion; cook until onion is transparent.
Add broth and water. Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Cut papaya into 2 x 1/2-inch pieces. Put into soup and cook 5 to 10 minutes or until papaya is tender. Add greens; turn off heat and let stand for 2 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: favorite bread dressing
directions: Cook onion and celery in shortening over low heat until onion is soft, but not browned, stirring occasionally.

title: best ever cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Make balls desired shape and roll in fine chopped pecans.

title: aunt bea's puppy chow
directions: Melt butter; add chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
Pour Rice Chex; mix well.
Put powdered sugar in bag.
Add cereal and shake until pieces are covered.
Cool and store in container with lid.

title: blueberry-nut freezer bread
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine oil, sugar, eggs, milk, lemon juice and pineapple.
Mix thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients and beat until thoroughly blended.
Fold in blueberries and nuts.
Pour dough into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until tests done.
Remove from pans at once and cool on rack.

title: cottage cheese dill bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast on warm water.
Stir in 2 teaspoons of sugar. Set aside.
Combine cottage cheese, onion, dill weed, baking powder, salt, 2 tablespoons of sugar and eggs.
Mix thoroughly. Add yeast mixture and mix well.
Add flour to make a stiff dough. Knead until smooth and elastic.
Cover and let rise to double in size.
Punch down.
Knead a few times on lightly floured surface. Shape into loaves in 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: toffee turtle bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix 1/2 cup butter, 1 cup brown sugar and flour until texture of fine crumbs.
Press mixture firmly into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans over top and set aside. Meanwhile combine 2/3 cup butter and 1/2 cup brown sugar in small heavy saucepan.
Cook, stirring until mixture comes to a boil; boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour over pecans.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes, until set.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Cool in pan and cut into bars.

title: sourdough cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll dough out on floured surface.
Brush with melted butter. Mix sugar and cinnamon together; sprinkle over butter.
Place raisins on top.
Roll as for jelly roll.
Cut into 2-inch slices; place in greased baking pan.
Let rise for 4 to 5 hours or all day (cover with wax paper).
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until light brown, at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or glaze with powdered sugar icing.
Very good.

title: minestrone
directions: Bring to a boil the peas, celery, carrots, onion and tomatoes. Simmer about 45 minutes. Add lima beans, macaroni and seasoning. Cook until macaroni is tender. Serve with freshly grated Parmesan cheese.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together and pat firmly into bottom of 9 X 13-inch pan.

title: lime cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix in order as listed.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: blackened fish
directions: In a small bowl, combine all spices.
Roll fish fillets in spices and saute.
Serve with butter and lemon wedges.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put in baking dish.
Cover top with cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes or until brown.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix the ingredients and bring to a boil (approximately 5 minutes).
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and beat until creamy.
(Add more cream, if necessary.)

title: cheese bread
directions: Stir Bisquick, cheese and 1/2 teaspoon poppy seed.
Add milk and eggs.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle more poppy seed on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Blend all ingredients (except squash) in blender container. Blend on low for 3 minutes.
Cook squash and cut in 1/4-inch pieces.
Spoon squash evenly into a deep, sprayed 10-inch pie plate.
Pour egg mixture over squash.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 minutes.
Makes 4 servings; 1/4 pie equals 1/2 milk, 1 egg, 1/2 fat (optional), 3 extras or 1/2 bread.
This came from Weight Watchers.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar in mixing bowl.
Add Crisco, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cake cool in pan.
Top with pineapple, chopped nuts and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut. Let cake set before serving.
Very good!

title: chili
directions: Cook beans (ahead); fry in oil, onions and garlic until soft. Add vegeburger and fry until browned.
Add tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes and spices.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add beans and simmer 15 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cucumber salad
directions: 1. Slice cucumber and onion.
2. Mix vinegar oil and spices. Add sliced cucumbers and
onions. Let stand for 1 hour.
3. Chill and serve cold. Add green chili peppers or hot
peppers if you like a zestier salad.

title: fried ice cream
directions: Slice ice cream into 1-inch thick pieces.
Place on jelly roll pan.
Place in freezer.
Grate pound cake into crumbs.
Combine whipping cream and egg.
This recipe will serve 4 people.

title: meat vegetable pie
directions: Lightly brown beef in hot oil, stirring frequently.
Add onions; cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in green pepper, celery, carrots, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Dissolve bouillon cube in water; add to meat mixture.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Mash potatoes; blend in egg, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Line greased 9-inch pie pan with even layer of potato mixture, about 1-inch thick, building edge up to 1/2-inch above edge of pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Pour in meat mixture.
Serve.

title: nearly snickers
directions: Mix and form patty on wax paper.
Chill.
(Raisins and coconut are optional.)

title: brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add chocolate syrup and flour.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° in greased jelly roll pan.

title: rum nut squares
directions: Put margarine in a large saucepan with sugar, milk and slightly beaten egg.
Stir and bring to boil, then boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat to cool slightly.
Line a broiler pan or cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Cover this with whole graham crackers (use 1 of the 3 packs in a 1 pound box).
Line them up row after row.
Crush enough crackers from the second pack to make 1 1/2 cup crumbs.
Add these to the saucepan mixture.
Add can of coconut and pecans.
Mix just until blended and pour or spoon over layer of graham crackers.
This makes a thick filling.
Top it with a layer of whole graham crackers (the third pack).
Frost with Icing.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Slice open rolls lengthwise so that you have 2 layers.
Mix together the butter, mustard, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Spread mixture over both inside parts of bread.
Layer ham and cheese on bottom part of rolls.
Cover with top part of bread. Return rolls to foil pans.
Place foil over top of rolls.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
When ready to serve, cut between rolls to make finger sandwiches.
Great appetizers.

title: fruit punch(great for showers)
directions: Heat together, but do not boil, pineapple, orange, lemonade and grapefruit juices.
Cool and mix in bananas; freeze.
I usually freeze in 1/2 gallon milk cartons.
To serve, place in punch bowl and add 6 quarts water and ice or decrease water to 3 quarts and add 2 or 3 liter bottle of 7-Up or lemon lime soda.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, lemonade and Eagle Brand milk for the filling. Pour into pie shells.
Put in icebox and chill.
When ready to serve, can put cherry pie filling on top.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar, squash, oil and eggs.
Beat with spoon until well blended.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; mix well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour in a greased and floured Bundt pan or 2 small loaf pans.

title: strawberry cheese cake
directions: Stir cream cheese until very soft.
Then blend 1/2 cup milk. Add instant pudding mix to the other 1 1/2 cups milk and beat for about 1 minute.
Do not overmix.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.
Mix the tapioca with thawed berries and sugar.
Boil gently for 2 minutes.
Allow to cool.
Spread over the cheese cake before serving.

title: cold sweet relish
directions: Combine the first six ingredients and soak in ice water for 1 hour.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over the first mixture and seal.

title: mom's banana nut bread
directions: Cream salad oil and sugar. Mash bananas and add 2 eggs; beat well. Add dry ingredients. Stir in chopped nuts. Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Dip apple slices in lemon juice or Fruit Fresh to prevent browning.
Combine all ingredients and heat over low heat until all ingredients are well blended and heated through.
(Stir frequently to prevent burning!)

title: fiesta red
directions: Cook bacon in large saucepan until crisp.
Remove to paper towel.
Drain off all but one tablespoon drippings; slowly cook onion in drippings until tender, not brown.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Ladle into soup bowls.
Garnish with lime slices.
Serve with corn chips. Serves 6.

title: party potatoes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add mixture to potatoes; mix thoroughly.
Transfer to ungreased 8 x 12 baking dish.
Sprinkle generously with paprika and parsley flakes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: creamy garlic dressing
directions: In a bowl, combine until smooth.
Refrigerate.
Yields 1 2/3 cup.

title: delicious meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine ground beef, sausage, 3 eggs, bread crumbs, chopped onion and peppers.
Mix this up really good, using hands is best.
Put this in a pan and form it into the shape of a loaf.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Serve with tostados or other chips.

title: garden medley rice
directions: Stir together broth, vegetables, onion flakes, rosemary and garlic powder in saucepan and bring to boil.
Stir in rice. Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork and sprinkle with pepper.
Serve with chicken.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ann's rolls
directions: Mix 1 package yeast and 1/2 cup warm water. Stir until dissolved. Set aside. Pour 2 cups warm water over 1/2 cup Crisco and 1/2 cup sugar. Stir until Crisco has dissolved. Mix yeast water and Crisco water together, then stir in flour to make soft dough. Cover. Let rise. When ready to use, punch down and roll on floured board. Make rolls in any shape you desire. Place on greased baking pan. Brush with melted butter. Allow to rise in a warm place until double in bulk (about 1 hour). Bake in hot oven at 375° until brown.

title: squash supreme
directions: Slice squash.
Steam with onion in pot until tender.
Add other ingredients, except oleo and stuffing.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Layer 1/2 stuffing.
Dot evenly with oleo on top. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cream cheese yogurt dip
directions: With
electric	mixer,	whip
the
cream
cheese
until fluffy;
stir
in
yogurt, garlic, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, tomato
sauce,
hot pepper sauce and salt.
Transfer to serving bowl.
Lightly
mix in sliced olives.
Cover and chill about 2
hours.
To
serve,
offer	vegetables as suggested in amounts suited to your needs.
This dip is also good served as a dressing for
a
crisp
green salad with a variety of thinly sliced vegetables.	Extra dip can be stored for several days.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar in pan.
Drain pineapple.
Arrange pineapple and maraschino cherry halves on the sugar mixture.
Mix cake mix as directed on label. Pour batter over fruit.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes after removing from oven for topping to begin to set.
Then turn upside down on cookie sheet.

title: strawberry refresher
directions: In blender, combine the strawberries, lemonade concentrate, banana extract and orange extract.
Add the ice cubes; blend until smooth.

title: apricot mist punch
directions: Pour nectar, pineapple juice and limeade concentrate into a large punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale down side of punch bowl; stir gently to mix.
Add ice.
Makes 38 (5 ounce) servings.

title: oyster stew
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, pour oysters and juice.
Salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until simmering.
Add 1 stick of butter and stir until it's melted.
Do not boil.
Pour in milk. Stir until warm.
Be careful it doesn't get too hot or milk will curdle.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs after beating with sugar.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Add syrup and mix well. Add nuts and mix well.
Pour in two (2) uncooked pie shells (regular).
Cook at 350 degrees until done (about one hour).

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In a large kettle, bring to a boil the sugar, cornstarch and water.
Boil for 1 minute.
Slightly beat the yolks in a medium bowl.
Mix in some of the boiled pudding into the egg yolks; stir constantly.
Put back in kettle and boil for 1 minute.
Add the butter, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Pour in the pie shell.
Top with meringue and bake.

title: seasoned crackers
directions: Mix together in covered bowl or Ziploc bag.
Let set 24 hours and it's ready to eat.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Mix 5 ingredients together.
Cook very well in electric frypan.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend ingredients together and serve with raw vegetables.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cover bottom of baking dish with Tater Tots.
Layer with frozen veggies, then mix soup and onion and pour over over vegetables.
Then cover last layer with Tater Tots.
Cook in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Then the last 10 minutes cover with cheese on top.
Quick and easy.

title: rolls
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Cook and stir mushrooms and green pepper in margarine over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is bubbly; remove from heat.
Stir in instant bouillon, milk, water and reserved mushroom liquid.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and pimento; heat through.
Makes 6 servings.
Serve over toast, hot mashed potatoes, waffles, cooked rice or noodles.

title: roast with barbecue gravy
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
In a Dutch oven, brown meat on all sides in hot oil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine barbecue sauce, marmalade, vinegar and 1/2 cup water; pour over meat. Cover, simmer about 2 1/4 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat to a platter, keep warm.
Pour meat juices and fat into a large glass measure.
Skim off excess fat.
Measure 2 cups liquid (if necessary, add water).
Return to Dutch oven.
Combine cornstarch and 2 tablespoons cold water; stir into pan juices. Cook and stir until bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more. Spoon some gravy over meat; pass remaining gravy.

title: mini sub sandwiches
directions: For each sandwich, spread roll with spread and fill with remaining ingredients.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, tossing well.
Serve with taco sauce, sour cream and guacamole.

title: meatball casserole
directions: Combine meat, oatmeal, milk, onion flakes, salt and pepper. Mix well and shape into meatballs.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine catsup, vinegar, water and sugar.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Note:
If you wet carrots, then use 4 1/2 cups of flour.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and margarine in a large bowl.
Add salt, flavorings and baking powder.
In blender, blend eggs and milk for 1 minute on high speed.
Add mixture to large bowl, alternating with flour.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: pork and pears with raisin sauce
directions: Melt butter and cook pork chops until tender and lightly browned.
Remove chops to warm plate; keep warm.

title: fast and easy stir-fry
directions: Saute 1/4 cup onion in small amount of vegetable oil in frypan or wok.
Add chicken breast, cut in small pieces, and brown on all sides.
Add 1 package of frozen mixed vegetables (Italian or California Blend).
Add 1/2 cup chicken broth.
Add 1/2 cup Minute rice and 1/4 teaspoon of Italian seasoning. Simmer, covered, until vegetables and rice are done (15 to 20 minutes).
Add 1/2 teaspoon fresh or dried parsley just before serving.
Serve with garlic toast.

title: sweetened condensed milk substitute
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend well.

title: date pecan roll
directions: Cook until forms soft ball.
Let stand 25 minutes. Beat until creamy. Add chopped nuts and dates. Roll in damp cloth and chill. Slice.

title: party peanuts
directions: Combine
grated Cheddar cheese, cream cheese and butter or margarine
and
cream well.
Sift flour and red pepper (or combination of spices) twice.
Add flour mixture a little at a time
to the cheese mixture.
Continue mixing until you have a soft
dough.
Place
dough in refrigerator until ready to use. (It will
keep
to	5 weeks.) When ready to shape peanuts, remove 1/3
of
the dough at a time.
Pinch off the dough the size
of
a peanut (about 1/4 teaspoon).
Press flat and wrap around
peanut (skins need not be removed).
Press two peanuts firmly
together to	form
peanut shape.
(Note:
This can be done
while watching TV or relaxing.) Continue until all dough is
used.
In
a	small bowl
blend
egg and water.
Dip each peanut
quickly in egg mixture and roll in sesame seed.
Place 1
inch
apart
on greased baking sheet.
Bake immediately in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until crisp.
Yields 9 to 10 dozen.

title: layered pudding dessert
directions: Pat into cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool crust.

title: sinfully delicious chocolate dessert
directions: Slice cake in half and into small pieces for layering as needed.
Using a large glass bowl (I use a punch bowl), layer chocolate cake, chocolate pudding and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips, lightly.
Continue layering until bowl is filled. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: potatoes in sour cream sauce
directions: Place potatoes in 2-quart baking dish.
Add salt and water. Cook, covered, 12 minutes; stir twice.
Let stand 10 minutes, covered.
Melt margarine; add flour, then milk.
Cook 2 minutes or until thickens on Full power.
Add sour cream, salt and pepper to taste.
Stir into drained potatoes.
Stir in parsley.
Sprinkle paprika on top for garnish.
Cook for 2 minutes on Full power.

title: white chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugars, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add egg and beat well. Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing well. Stir in vanilla.
Stir in white chocolate and macadamia nuts. Chill dough 1 hour.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together.
Crumble bread crumbs into mix (toast bread to make it dry).
Mix thoroughly; shape into 1-inch balls.
Melt shortening in skillet and brown meatballs. Pour off excess shortening.
Add jelly in skillet and melt.
Add chili sauce, stirring constantly.
Add meatballs; stir until thoroughly coated.
Pour all into chafing dish.
Serve.

title: spinach and cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream together brown sugar and Crisco.
Add
rest of ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and add topping made of 1/2 cup sugar mixed with cinnamon.
Sprinkle over top and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve cold or warm with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: nutty butty delight
directions: Pastry:
Melt butter and mix flour and nuts.
Press with fork in oblong dish and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: crescent chicken rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread mixture into each individual crescent roll, pinching ends together to seal.
Brush melted butter onto crescent rolls.
Bake as directed on crescent roll can or until brown.

title: spirited chicken
directions: Cut roaster in 8 pieces.
Brown in deep kettle.
Add seasonings.
Brown 10 minutes on each side.
When chicken is browned, remove fat and add the mixture of wine, whiskey and tomato paste.
Add mushrooms and liquid from can.
Simmer until tender. Do not cover pot.
Add additional wine or water as needed.
Turn chicken pieces once in a while.
Serves 4. All alcohol evaporates. Diners are sober with this chicken.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix first five ingredients, then fold in gently pie filling.

title: broccoli noodle casserole(umm umm great!)
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
(Do not cook too long as noodles will mush in casserole.
Saute onion in a little olive oil or oleo.
Add mushrooms, soup, cheese and milk. Also, add liquid from mushrooms.
Blend well.
Add broccoli.
Toss noodles and sauce in greased (or use spray Pam) casserole dish. Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until hot and bubbly. Uncover towards the end, if you'd like it browned.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cream together.
Spread over cooled cookies.
Top with pineapple, strawberries, grapes and bananas.
Heat 8 ounces of apricot preserves in microwave until runny.
Drizzle over fruit.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Do not cook anything.
Mix ingredients and let set for 24 hours.
Store in refrigerator.

title: hot cheese biscuits
directions: Mash cheese spread and butter; cream well.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Chill at least 1 hour. Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Balls will flatten as they cook.
Serve hot.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown
pork
chops.
Place
in
baking
dish.
Peel and slice potatoes
and onion and layer over pork chops.
Sprinkle with a dash of
thyme.
Salt and pepper if desired.
Pour soup over this. Then pour 1/2 soup can filled with water over all. Cover with foil;
bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: pistachio fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail, add pineapple before mixing other ingredients.
Mix other ingredients together thoroughly.
Pour in serving bowl or ring mold.
Let congeal in refrigerator 4 to 6 hours.

title: the best sugar cookies
directions: Mix and cream first four ingredients.
Add mixed dry ingredients and chill dough.
Roll into 1-inch ball and press onto cookie sheet with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Sprinkle with more sugar if desired.
Bake for 7 to 8 minutes on 400° oven.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Roll into a ball, then roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with any kind of cracker.

title: kisses
directions: Beat egg whites and sugar until light like meringue.
Add vinegar, vanilla and nuts.
Bake at least 45 minutes.

title: spinach brownies(vegetable)
directions: Drain spinach; squeeze out moisture.
Combine cheese, spinach and onion in a large bowl.
Stir salt, baking powder and nutmeg into flour, then mix with spinach.
Mix together the eggs, butter and milk.
Add to the other ingredients.
Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with foil; spray with Pam.
Pour mixture into pan; bake for 35 minutes in a 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar.
Melt butter and chocolate together. Combine mixtures by beating.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a shallow pan for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: texas style chili
directions: Brown stew meat in vegetable oil; remove from skillet.
Saute onions, bell pepper and garlic until tender.
Combine all ingredients.
Cook in slow cooker 5 to 6 hours or on stove top (bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 2 hours).
Garnish with cheese and serve with tortilla chips.

title: shell chicken salad
directions: Blend mayo and mustard.
Mix all other ingredients.
Add mayo and mustard; toss.
Serve with garlic cheese bread.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in an oblong dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice. Sift dry ingredients together and combine with egg, mixing until crumbly.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Cover with margarine and bake in a 375° oven for 35 to 45 minutes or until crusty and brown.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: Cook mostaccioli as directed; drain.
Coat with vegetable oil. Chop cucumber, onion and pimentos.
Mix with macaroni.
Heat together the vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper, Accent and garlic powder.
Pour over mostaccioli mixture; mix well.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Steam broccoli 3 to 4 minutes; set aside.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in large frying pan.
Add onion and saute until soft but not brown.
Add broccoli and cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir in stock, salt and pepper to taste, lemon juice and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
(Remove bay leaf after first 5 minutes.)
Puree in blender.
Melt remaining butter in another saucepan.
Add flour and cook, stirring, for 1 minute.
Gradually stir in pureed broccoli mixture and bring to a boil, stirring. Simmer for a few minutes.
Add cream and serve.

title: sicilian supper
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion.
Cook until tender.
Add tomato paste, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Heat milk and cream cheese; blend well.
Stir in 1/4 cup Parmesan, garlic salt, green pepper and noodles.
In casserole, alternate rows or layers of noodles and meat sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle on remaining cheese.
Serves 6.
